text:
The best Hindu temple complex I ever visited, and the biggest in southeast Asia after Angkor Wat. Going there is relatively easier than Borobodur. You can buy the tickets directly on site for around 25 dollars, and you get to roam the temple site and go inside the shrines as long as you wish. The entrance to the shrines is made of steep steps, which could be bent or very narrow so take care not to fall

The best time to visit is late afternoon to avoid the scorching sun, and most tourists would combine the tour after with Ramayana Ballet Show which starts after sunset. There will be a lot of people praying, so make sure to be respectful and not disturb them. I was able to go inside the main shrines where you will see the Hindu gods such as Wisnu, Brahma and Shiva

I really enjoyed my time there admiring the beauty of this ancient temple, it is a must visit and pictures would never do it justice

text:
Come early so it won't feel hot, prepare for hat, sunscreen, sunglasses, or umbrella, you may bring your water bottle, but no food allowed. You have to walk about 3-5 mins from parking lot to gate/entrance. They have different gate for domestic and international tourists. You may buy the ticket on the spot or using travel apps in advance. There are different price for different attraction, like if you want to reach Ratu Boko temple. It takes 5-10 mins walk from the gate to reach Prambanan temple. The main stupa is so majestic, and there are guides who offer to guide you, and also there are just guides stand nearby the stupa to let you come or climb it. Routes are shown by them and signs are orderly put there to help you so you won't get lost. Clean places and there are many spots you can take pictures out. Also, I recommend you to come like 7 am and on weekday because it's very crowded on weekends and hot at 9 am. I didn't go to Ratu Boko so I got back to parking lot which took about 10 mins walk, and I had to pass the souvenir market first.

I'm still amazed how they managed to make that temple hundreds years ago.

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Tainá Domingues
text:
Definitely worth the visit! I was very impressed about the Temple and the whole complex built around it. They have a good infrastructure, restaurant and some shops inside. You’ll be given water and a map as part of your foreign ticket.

HOW TO GET THERE:

- Public Transport:
We went to Prambanan from Yogyakarta (a bit out of the city centre) by ourselves with local buses following Google Maps and I found quite easy to do it. We also made sure to ask locals in bus stops to confirm that was the best route.
We took the bus 3B to “TJ Bandara Adisucipto” (station at the airport) and from there changed to bus 1A to “Terminal Prambanan”. The total cost for both buses was IDR 7,200 as stated on Google Maps. From the Terminal, you have to walk for 16 min.
The full trip took about 2 hours, even though Google was saying that would take a bit longer than that.

- Grab:
On the way back we decided to catch a Grab as it was pouring down rain and it cost about IDR 130,000 back into our accommodation.
Just be aware if you choose to go there by Grab, the driver might offer to wait for you to take you back into town. Take into consideration what’s best for you.

- DAMRI bus:
Just after we’ve been to Prambanan we found out that was a third option how to get there that we didn’t know about it.
The DAMRI buses/minivans run everyday in specific times leaving from “Bank Indonesia Yogyakarta” (located in Malioboro city centre).
As the timetables are fixed and they don’t have many buses running, I would highly recommend you to go in their stand in person the day before and book your bus in advance, once you have bought your ticket to the Temple. Also double check how long the journey would take, as you don’t want to miss your ticket entrance time.
We ended up not using this option as we couldn’t find much information online, the website was a bit confusing and not translated to English, so I found the best option is to ask them in person.

I hope those tips are useful, I wish I knew them before going there :)
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Andin
text:
My favourite version of The Prambanan background story is that Jonggrang asked Bandung to make her a 1000 temples and of course, that's a folklore. Side note: I love folklores, that's like Indonesian Disney's stories of some short.
So today I visited The Prambanan, a 14 years after my last one and this beautiful temple just had a touch ups nonetheless still have that inner beauty that always have a special spot in my heart. Bunch of school kids grouping around their tour guides and none of all the guides I've heard today talked about the temple's romance romance that I'd always love to hear, obviously. Because it's not necessary. History is precise and prescious. Even my nonsense brain agrees.
Let me quote one of the guide's introduction to these kids that I overheard: "then why people speak about 1000 temples when it's only 200something temples? 1000 marks the greatness of something; 1000 temples, 1000 islands, the centipede we call in Bahasa Indonesia a kaki seribu (a thousand legged). The Prambanan was made specifically for worship before Buddha came, before Christian came, before Islam came, before any religion ever mentioned. There used to be Brahmanas, the Hindu priests who came here to pray to God."

🌺✨

name: Arief Rahman
text: As the largest Hindu temple complex in Indonesia (and the second largest after Angkor Wat), Prambanan is a marker of the shift in Mataram court patronage, from Mahayana Buddhism to Shaivite Hinduism.  Built around 850 AD by the Hindu king of Mataram, Rakai Pikatan, Prambanan is dedicated to the Trimurti, the 3 main Hindu gods: Bhrahma, Vishnu and the main god of Shaivite Hinduism, Shiva.  Prambanan Temple (apart from Borobudur and other temples) is proof of the architectural grandeur of the ancient Mataram period.

text: The temple itself is a sight to see. Efforts to preserve it are well appreciated. But the fact that foreigners have to pay 3x more than locals is uncalled for. The disorganization when lining up for a guide is abysmal. You literally have to rush and jostle with other visitors when you hear English tours being announced. If you're lucky, then you'll join the group. If not, then you'll have to wait for the next opportunity. Then there is the exit. Good luck in finding your way out while going through the gamut of vendors. They literally made it into a maze and you have to go through them. This makes the Cozumel cruise gamut seem pleasant. Another thing they don't tell you is that the flipflops you have to wear for the temple come with the ticket and you don't have to wear them until you reach the temple entrance. It's such a shame that the process of getting in and getting out ruins the actual place itself as it is a beautiful temple. Let's hope the administration will fix this for the future of tourism in the Yogyakarta area.

text:
Borobudur Temple Complex is one of the most impressive and important archaeological sites in Indonesia, located in the province of Yogyakarta on the island of Java. This ancient Buddhist temple complex was built in the 8th and 9th centuries, during the Sailendra dynasty, and is considered one of the greatest Buddhist monuments in the world.

The temple complex consists of nine stacked platforms, six square and three circular, decorated with 2,672 relief panels and 504 Buddha statues. The complex is topped by a large central dome, which represents enlightenment. The entire structure is made of volcanic stone, with no mortar used in its construction. It is estimated that the temple was built by around 1 million workers over a period of 75 years.

The Borobudur Temple Complex was abandoned for centuries and was rediscovered in 1814 by Sir Thomas Stamford Raffles, the British ruler of Java. The temple underwent extensive restoration in the 20th century, and in 1991, it was declared a UNESCO World Heritage site.

Today, Borobudur Temple Complex is one of Indonesia's most popular tourist attractions, drawing millions of visitors each year. Visitors can explore the temple complex and take in the stunning views of the surrounding mountains and lush countryside. It is also a popular destination for sunrise and sunset views.

In addition to its cultural and historical significance, Borobudur Temple Complex is also an important site for Buddhists. It is believed that walking clockwise around the temple complex while meditating can bring blessings and good fortune.

In conclusion, the Borobudur Temple Complex is a must-see destination for anyone visiting Yogyakarta or Indonesia in general. Its rich history, stunning architecture, and cultural significance make it a truly unique and unforgettable experience.

name: Eric Jensen
text:
Ok, just finished the visit here. I am hoping I can help people have an easier experience than I did.

Visit date: 11 June 2023

1. I strongly recommend you visit as early as possible to avoid the heat (and to some extent crowds). This means 6.30am ticket office for 7am entry to the Temple Grounds.

2. For foreigners, it is not much extra cost to take the guided tour up to the top (not much more, because base ticket already expensive). I recommend doing this.
If you happen to be able to go the day before to the ticket office, reserve space on the first tour up (8am ticket office to pay, then tour starts 8.30). They won't let you pay for it at that time, but you can leave your name.
After seeing the temple grounds (see 1.), you will need to get back to the ticket office to pay for the tour to the top of the temple at 8am.

Bottom line:
They have made this a chaotic and very unclear visitor experience for what would otherwise be a 5 star historic temple.
I hope they get their act together eventually because this is probably the worst-run UNESCO world heritage site I have been to in the world. It is still worth seeing but do arrive very well prepared, with water and well-fed already. Don't expect any helpful amenities to smooth the experience.

Extra note:
For transport in the area, I recommend using Grab. It is well priced, professional and easy to access throughout the area around the temple (and beyond).

name: AnilKumar Bijjahalli
text:
Located in the heart of Yogyakarta, Indonesia, the Prambanan Temple is a remarkable cultural landmark that has been attracting visitors from around the world for centuries. This stunning temple complex is a true masterpiece of ancient architecture and is considered one of the most impressive Hindu temples in Southeast Asia.

The temple complex dates back to the 9th century and was built during the reign of the Sanjaya Dynasty. It is believed that the temple was constructed to honor the Hindu god Shiva, as well as other deities such as Brahma and Vishnu. The temple was also built as a symbol of the power and influence of the Sanjaya Dynasty, which ruled over central Java at the time.

The Prambanan Temple complex consists of 240 temples, including eight main shrines, which are dedicated to different Hindu deities. The largest and most impressive of these is the central temple, which is dedicated to Shiva and stands at a height of 47 meters. The temple is surrounded by smaller temples, which are decorated with intricate carvings and sculptures that depict scenes from Hindu mythology.

One of the most impressive features of the Prambanan Temple complex is the level of detail and craftsmanship that went into its construction. The temples are adorned with exquisite carvings and sculptures, which are believed to have been created by master craftsmen from India. These intricate carvings and sculptures depict scenes from Hindu mythology and provide a fascinating insight into the beliefs and culture of the people who built the temple.

Despite being over a thousand years old, the Prambanan Temple complex remains remarkably well-preserved. This is thanks to the ongoing efforts of the Indonesian government and local communities to maintain and protect the temple from damage caused by natural disasters and human activity.

Today, the Prambanan Temple complex is a popular tourist destination and a symbol of Indonesia's rich cultural heritage. Visitors can explore the temple grounds, marvel at the stunning architecture and carvings, and learn about the history and significance of this remarkable landmark.

In conclusion, the Prambanan Temple complex is a true masterpiece of ancient architecture and a testament to the skill and creativity of the people who built it. Its impressive size, intricate carvings, and rich history make it a must-see destination for anyone visiting Yogyakarta or Indonesia.

name: KH Chong
text:
Compared to more than 20 years ago right after Prambanan was awarded UNESCO World Heritage, it’s commendable that the preservation work is still continuing and that the surrounding land has been redeveloped into park for the locals. We went on a rainy day but the site was still overcrowded. Though still better than Borobudur, the management should seriously start to implement crowd control to prevent further deterioration of the monument.

Advanced booking and queueing system in other renowned world heritage sites could be adopted, so that it’s still open to public, keep the ticket affordable, while controlling the number of visitors at any one time. This would also greatly enhance visitors’ experience.

Museum and audiovisual show could be further enhanced and made into compulsory introduction, so that all visitors would truly understand the history and treasure the monument.

Finally, the surrounding urban context has great potential to be further developed into cultural-ecological district, enhancing the environment and business opportunities for the locals. More public parks should be built across the town so as to disperse the current concentration of both the visitors and small businesses at the heritage site itself, and at the same time enhance the image of the city and create better well-being for the people.

We actually enjoyed the ruin much more, leaving room for imagination. It was a good decision not to reconstruct all the other 240 shrines and only to have a few as examples. Perhaps virtual reality could even complement the experience in future.

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Taufiqqurrahman NS
text:
Harus banget booking online untuk pengunjung luar kota terutama yang sampai naik candinya.

Harga naik candi sama yang di pelataran emang jauh banget cuma untuk yang belum pernah naik, worth banget. Dapet sandal dan tasnya, air mineral 300 mL, sama tour guide kelompok yang bisa menjelaskan dengan baik jadi gak cuma liat-liat doang tapi ga tau apa-apa 😂

Sebelum covid melanda memang naik ke candi gak dibatasi dan cenderung bebas. Sekarang atas alasan konservasi, pengunjung dibatasi. Sisi positifnya diatas gak crowded banget jadi kalo mau foto masih bisa “bersih” la 😂

Parkiran kendaraan luas banget jadi pinter-pinter milih tempat aja daripada jauh dari pintu masuk/keluar candi

Setelah perbaikan candi dan sekitarnya jadi lebih tertata dan lebih baik 👍
textTranslated:
You really have to book online for out-of-town visitors, especially those going up to the temple.

The price for going up to the temple is the same as the one in the courtyard, but for those who have never gone up, it's really worth it. Get sandals and a bag, 300 mL mineral water, and a group tour guide who can explain well so you don't just look around but don't know anything 😂

Before Covid hit, going to the temple was not restricted and tended to be free. Now for conservation reasons, visitors are limited. The positive side is that it's not very crowded, so if you want to take photos you can still be "clean" 😂

The vehicle parking area is very spacious, so be smart in choosing a place rather than far from the entrance/exit of the temple

After repairs, the temple and its surroundings became more organized and better 👍
title: Borobudur Temple

Bergabung dengan kloter WNI semua. Saya sendirian dan tour guide nya tetap adil ke semua turis.

Ada beberapa bagian/area. Pintu masuk akan melewati lapak UMKM. Lewati tempat penitipan barang. Makanan tidak boleh masuk, minuman/air putih boleh. Ke loket tiket dan diarahkan ke penukaran sandal/anupat (akan jadi souvenir)
textTranslated:
The first time I came here when it was a bit cloudy, but it was still hot. Order on the ticket application by climbing to the top of the temple Rp. 120K.

Join the all Indonesian citizen group. I was alone and the tour guide remained fair to all tourists.

There are several sections/areas. The entrance will pass through the MSME stall. Skip the luggage storage area. Food is not allowed, drinks/water are allowed. Go to the ticket counter and be directed to exchange sandals/anupat (will be a souvenir)
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: 稲田千里
text:
昨年の10月から、出入口や駐車場がガラッと変わったようです。最初そのことを知らず、ホテルは旧入り口近くにしてしまったので、慌てて取り直しました。

無料で預けられる荷物クロークがあったのでとても助かりました。

【流れ】
チケットカウンター（購入済のQRを見せるとリストバンドをしてくれます）→
荷物チェック→カートにのる→受け付け（ガイドのグループ札と草履、水の引換書をもらう）→草履、水の引換→待合室で時間が来るのを待ってガイドさんと合流。

私達は朝一の8:30の登頂ツアーに参加。
受け付けは8:00オープンだったので、開くまで少し待ちました。

基本は英語でのガイドでしたが、少しだけ日本語もできる方だったので、要所要所の単語を日本語でも説明して下さり、理解が深まりました。
20分程フリータイムがあり、集合後はサクッと写真撮影のベストポイントの説明と挨拶があり、ぴったり10時にはツアー終了！

カート（無料）は、往復共に空いていてほとんど待たずに乗れました。10時半頃入り口に戻った時には、人が増えて来ていたのでどうかな？という感じでした。

登頂ツアーは、1人約4500円と値ははりますが、ストゥーパを間近で見てこそ価値があると思うので、お勧めします。
textTranslated:
It seems that the entrance and parking lot have changed completely since October of last year. I didn't know this at first, and the hotel was located near the old entrance, so I hurriedly reinstalled it.

There was a cloakroom where you could leave your luggage for free, which was very helpful.

【flow】
Ticket counter (show your purchased QR and they will give you a wristband) →
Check your luggage → Put it in the cart → Receive the guide's group tag, sandals, and water exchange form → Exchange sandals and water → Wait in the waiting room until the time comes and meet up with the guide.

We took the first climbing tour at 8:30 in the morning.
The reception opened at 8:00, so I had to wait a little while until it opened.

The guide was basically in English, but since he was also able to speak a little Japanese, he explained important words in Japanese, which deepened my understanding.
We had about 20 minutes of free time, and after meeting, we quickly explained the best spots for photos and greeted each other, and the tour ended exactly at 10 o'clock!

The carts (free of charge) were empty on both the round trip and I didn't have to wait much. When I returned to the entrance around 10:30, the number of people had increased, so I wondered what was going on. That's what it felt like.

The summit tour is expensive at about 4,500 yen per person, but I think it's worth it when you see the stupa up close, so I recommend it.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Anidya Fista Wibyanti
text:
Untuk mau naik ke Candi Borobudur harus beli tiket online, dan sampai area Candi tepat waktu sesuai jadwal yang ada di ticket.

Buat saya worth it sih beli ticket untuk naik ke atas Candi, walaupun lumayan ya bedanya sama ticket pelataran.

Yang didapat jika beli ticket untuk naik ke atas Candi, air mineral botol, tas untuk simpan sepatu dan souvenir berupa Upanat atau sandal khusus untuk naik ke struktur candi. Kita harus ganti sepatu atau sandal kita dengan Upanat ini. Tour guide yang jelasinnya enak banget, sampai gak berasa tau-tau udah sampai bagian atas Candi Borobudur. Jadi gak hanya melihat-lihat Candi saja, tapi juga dijelaskan sejarah dan filsafat Candi Borobudur ini. Jadi menambah pengetahuan juga, terutama untuk anak-anak.

Naik ke struktur Candi ini diberikan waktu 1 jam, karena harus bergantian dengan pengunjung lain. Namun, mulai dari naik Candi hingga turun tidak terlalu terburu-buru, karena masih bisa menikmati pemandangan indah dari atas Candi.
textTranslated:
To go up to Borobudur Temple, you have to buy a ticket online, and arrive at the temple area on time according to the schedule on the ticket.

For me, it's worth it to buy a ticket to go up to the top of the temple, even though it's quite different from the ticket to the courtyard.

What you get if you buy a ticket to climb to the top of the temple, bottled mineral water, a bag to store your shoes and a souvenir in the form of Upanat or special sandals for climbing to the temple structure. We have to change our shoes or sandals with this Upanat. The tour guide explained it so well, you didn't even feel like you had reached the top of Borobudur Temple. So you don't just look at the temple, but also explain the history and philosophy of Borobudur Temple. So it increases knowledge too, especially for children.

Climbing to this temple structure is given 1 hour, because you have to take turns with other visitors. However, from going up the temple to going down, there is no rush, because you can still enjoy the beautiful view from the top of the temple.

text:
Candhi Båråbudhur) adalah sebuah candi Buddha yang terletak di Borobudur, Magelang, Jawa Tengah. Candi ini terletak kurang lebih 100 kilometer di sebelah barat daya Semarang, 86 km di sebelah barat Surakarta, dan 40 km di sebelah barat laut Yogyakarta. Candi Borobudur merupakan salah satu Candi Budha terbesar di dunia dan diresmikan menjadi salah satu dari 7 keajaiban dunia. Karena itu Candi Borobudur termasuk destinasi yang kami kunjungi untuk studi literasi lapangan bagi siswa.
Lokasi di Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah
textTranslated:
Candhi Båråbudhur) is a Buddhist temple located in Borobudur, Magelang, Central Java. This temple is located approximately 100 kilometers southwest of Semarang, 86 km west of Surakarta, and 40 km northwest of Yogyakarta. Borobudur Temple is one of the largest Buddhist temples in the world and was inaugurated as one of the 7 wonders of the world. Because of this, Borobudur Temple is one of the destinations we visit for field literacy studies for students.
Location on Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Borobudur Temple, Borobudur, Magelang Regency, Central Java
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Marlous
text:
Was mega mooi om mee te maken, wij hadden een tour met gids en hij vertelde veel over de geschiedenis, wederopbouw enzovoort.
Als je gaat adviseer ik om zeker ook tickets te kopen om helemaal bovenop de tempel te komen, adembenemend uitzicht.
Op warme dagen neem een paraplu mee, en vergeet geen water mee te nemen, het is best nog een klip om op de tempel te komen, maar het is zeker te doen!
textTranslated:
It was very nice to experience, we had a tour with a guide and he told a lot about the history, reconstruction and so on.
If you go, I recommend that you definitely buy tickets to get right on top of the temple, breathtaking views.
On hot days take an umbrella with you and don't forget to take water with you, it is quite a climb to get to the temple, but it is certainly doable!
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Habibi Bahruddin
text:
26 Jan 2025
Kondisi saat ini
Parkir lumayan luas, tapi jauh bayar 15.000 tapi kalau mau yang didalam deket tiketing bayar lagi 20.000
Mushola bagus dan tersedia cukup banyak
Toilet tersebar banyak, bayar 2 ribu
Perjalanan menuju tiketing cukup jauh, enak bagi yg suka olahraga, tapi untuk orang tua kurang baik, walaupun dutawarkan kursi Roda
Menuju Candi pakai Shuttle karena jauh
Tidak ada teduhan jika hujan
Sewa payung 10.000 sepuasnya
Biaya masuk 50.000 dewasa
Biaya masuk 35.000 anak anak
Agak kecewa pada saat pesen makan,
Diminta untuk melihat menu dan memilih, eh pas dateng semuanya disamakan, jadi buat apa ngasih memu
Harga 20.000 perporsi, minuman 10.000
Disarankan pakai aplikasi untuk pembelian tiket biar tidak antri
Naik ahuttle antri panjang
Baju baju kaos murah
100.000 dapat 7 pcs
Tinggal tawar, ya pastinya kualitas seperti laos partai
Cukup bintang 4 saja
textTranslated:
Jan. 26, 2025
Present condiition
Parking is quite spacious, but far away you pay 15,000 but if you want one near the ticketing area you pay another 20,000
The prayer room is good and there are quite a lot of them available
There are lots of toilets, pay 2 thousand
The journey to ticketing is quite far, good for those who like sports, but not so good for older people, even though they offer wheelchairs
To get to the temple, use a shuttle because it's far away
There is no shade if it rains
Rent an umbrella for 10,000 as much as you like
Entry fee 50,000 adults
Entrance fee is 35,000 children
A bit disappointed when ordering food,
Asked to look at the menu and choose, but when they arrived everything was the same, so why give me a menu
Price 20,000 per portion, drinks 10,000
It is recommended to use the application to purchase tickets so you don't queue
Take a shuttle with long queues
Cheap t-shirts
100,000 get 7 pcs
Just bargain, of course the quality is like Laos party
Just 4 stars
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: 天啓
text:
バイクの駐車料金5000rp

①外国人とインドネシア人でチケットカウンターが違います。

私は事前に、オンライン上で予約していきました。
（4000円しないぐらい）
ボロブドゥール内のホテルに泊まれば入場料はかかりませんが、かなり前から予約が埋まっています。

②カウンターでおしゃれなサンダルがもらえます。
サイズを聞かれます。
タイプが2種類あるみたいです。（選べません）
このサンダルは、
寺院を観光するのに履かなければなりません。
靴はエコバッグがもらえるのでそれに入れます。

③チケットの処理をされると、カートに乗って、待合室まで行きます。
そこで、番号の書いたカードがもらえます。
時間になると順々に呼ばれ、
8人ぐらいのグループでガイドさんと一緒に行動します。

（必ず予約時間前には着いておきましょう。時間厳守です。）

④私のガイドさんはとても気さくで面白い人で、たくさん冗談を言ってました。
私は英語が、できないのですが、日本語で話してくれてとても助かりましたし、
楽しめました。

いたるところをガイドしながらゆっくり上まで登っていきます。

⑤一番上で20分、自由時間が与えられ、散策ができます。
ボロブドゥールは巨大で、
造りもすごくて、目を見張ります。
感動です。

銅像の首がほとんどないですが、地震によって壊れたそうです。
時間になると、再び集まり下まで戻って現地で解散しました。

⑥帰りは同じようにカートに乗って戻ります。

カートが着いてから行きと同じ方向では帰れず、
お土産屋を通って帰らなければなりません。
出口までとても距離があります。

ジョグジャカルタから少し遠いし、入場料も高いけどぜひ。上まで行くことをオススメします。
textTranslated:
Motorcycle parking fee 5000rp

①The ticket counters are different for foreigners and Indonesians.

I made a reservation online in advance.
(less than 4000 yen)
There is no entrance fee if you stay at a hotel in Borobudur, but it is booked up well in advance.

②You can get stylish sandals at the counter.
You will be asked for your size.
There seem to be two types. (Cannot choose)
This sandal is
Must wear to visit temples.
You can get an eco bag for your shoes, so put them in that bag.

③Once your ticket has been processed, you will get on the cart and go to the waiting room.
There you will receive a card with a number written on it.
When the time came, they were called one after another,
You will be working with a guide in a group of about 8 people.

(Be sure to arrive before your reservation time. Be punctual.)

④My guide was a very friendly and funny person and joked a lot.
I can't speak English, but he spoke to me in Japanese, which was very helpful.
I enjoyed it.

We will slowly climb to the top while guiding you everywhere.

⑤You will be given 20 minutes of free time at the top to take a walk.
Borobudur is huge;
The construction is amazing, and it's a sight to behold.
I'm impressed.

The statue's head is almost missing, but it seems that it was destroyed by an earthquake.
When the time came, we gathered again and returned to the bottom to disperse.

⑥ On the way back, ride the cart in the same way.

Once the cart arrived, I couldn't go home in the same direction as I went.
I have to go back through the souvenir shop.
It's very far to the exit.

It's a little far from Yogyakarta and the entrance fee is expensive, but I highly recommend it. I recommend going all the way to the top.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Nevy Kawulusan
text:
Cukup baik dgn konsep baru. Tpi blm ada petunjuk arah pagi pengunjung baik parkir apalgi pejlan kaki... dri parkiran ke loket dan pintu masuk jauh.
Jika mau naik sampi atas harus registrasi on line dulu, tpi jika hanya pelatran bisa langsung masuk dgn pembelian tiket terlebih dahulu di loket dgn hrga utk wisatawan lokal Rp. 50.000. Dan setelah itu kita naik sutle bus listrik terbuka sampi pd tak pengantaran dan kita masih berjalan cukup jauh sampi di pelatran borobudur, tdk ada petunjuk jln menuju ke akses poin borobudur. Desain lansekapnya kurang baik
textTranslated:
Pretty good with the new concept. But there are no directions yet for morning visitors, whether parking or walking... from the parking lot to the counter and the entrance is far away.
If you want to go up to the top you have to register online first, but if it's just a platform you can go straight in by purchasing a ticket in advance at the counter with the price for local tourists being IDR. 50,000. And after that we took an open-air electric bus until it was not delivered and we still walked quite a distance until we reached the Borobudur parking lot, there were no signs on the road to the Borobudur access point. The landscape design is not good
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Septiani
text: First time datang ke sini, biasanya cuma lewat doang😆. Tempat yang luar biasa dan bertemu guide yang ramah. Candinya penuh nilai historis dan banyak penjelasan ilmiah dibalik terbentuknya bangunan candi. Saya dan teman beli tiket lewat website resmi. Kami beli tiket dharma dan mulai dari jam 08.30. Untuk harga naik ke candi/templenya 120 rb (dapat upanat, air mineral dan tas) serta di dampingi guide yang akan memandu dan memberi penjelasan. Upanat dan tasnya bisa dibawa pulang juga, ya. Kalau cuma di bawah dan tidak naik ke candi, bisa beli tiket yang 45rb. Di sini juga banyak penjual souvenir dan ada food courtnya. Oh iya ada museumnya juga, sayangnya pas kami ke sini museumnya tutup (sepertinya di renov).
textTranslated: First time coming here, usually just passing through😆. An extraordinary place and met a friendly guide. The temple is full of historical value and there are many scientific explanations behind the formation of the temple building. My friend and I bought tickets via the official website. We bought dharma tickets and started at 08.30. The price for going up to the temple/temple is 120 thousand (you get upanat, mineral water and a bag) and accompanied by a guide who will guide you and give explanations. You can take the upanat and bag home too, OK? If you only go downstairs and don't go up to the temple, you can buy a ticket for 45 thousand. There are also many souvenir sellers here and there is a food court. Oh yes, there is a museum too, unfortunately when we came here the museum was closed (it looked like it was being renovated).
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Evi Miharliani
text:
Candi yg penuh dgn sejarah.. thn 2024 bulan desember ini saya mengajak anak anak dan suami… mereka happy bgt karena tempatnya semakin nyaman.. alhamdulillah nya meskipun sedang liburan tp tdk terlalu mengantre panjang banget.. karena loket tiket banyak,

moda si tayo untuk mengantar juga banyak jd ga menunggu trlalu lama utk naik tayonya.. tempat bersih dan nyaman juga.

Saran kl mau agak sepi dtg lebih pagi yaa.. karena makin siang pasti pengunjung makin banyak aplagi musim liburan ky gini…
Mungkin kl musim biasa ga akan trlalu ramai..
textTranslated:
A temple full of history... in December 2024, I invited my children and husband... they were really happy because the place was getting more comfortable... thank God, even though it was a holiday, there wasn't a really long queue... because there were lots of ticket counters,

There are also lots of ways for Tayo to deliver so you don't have to wait too long to get on the Tayo... the place is clean and comfortable too.

If you want it to be a bit quiet, it's a suggestion to come early... because as the afternoon goes on, there will definitely be more visitors, especially during the holiday season like this...
Maybe in normal season it won't be so busy...
title: Borobudur Temple

text: Keren, penataan tata ruang sudah rapi. Pengunjung juga terkontrol. Semoga warisan budaya ini tetap terjaga. Kendaraan antar jemput mungkin perlu diperbanyak dan trotoar perlu diperlebar agar orang tertarik utk berjalan. Kondisi sekarang sulit utk bergerak cepat kalau ada orang yg berjalan lanmbat didepan kita.
textTranslated: Cool, the layout is neat. Visitors are also controlled. Hopefully this cultural heritage will be maintained. Shuttle vehicles may need to be increased and sidewalks may need to be widened so that people are interested in walking. Current conditions make it difficult to move quickly if there are people walking slowly in front of us.
title: Borobudur Temple

text: 素晴らしいいの一言、土地も広大で入口から電気自動車でツアーの開始地点まで行きます。現在はツアーでのみ廻ることだ出来て、20人に一人ぐらい英語のガイドが付きます、興味深い説明をタイミングよくしてくれます。ジョグジャカルタの市内からは遠いですが一度来る価値ありだと思います
textTranslated: The land is vast and you can go from the entrance to the starting point of the tour by electric car. Currently, it can only be visited on a tour, and about one out of every 20 people is accompanied by an English-speaking guide, who provides interesting explanations in a timely manner. Although it is far from Yogyakarta city, I think it is worth coming once.
title: Borobudur Temple

name: NABILA RIZQA DAMAYANTI
text: Sangat cantik, sekarang sudah ada shuttle untuk mengangkut penumpang. Jadi, mobil di parkir dan jalan ke area candinya diantar dengan shuttle bus. Tiket untuk pelataran Rp 50.000 per orang.
textTranslated: Very beautiful, now there is a shuttle to transport passengers. So, the car is parked and the road to the temple area is taken by shuttle bus. Tickets for the grounds are IDR 50,000 per person.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Atika Rahmadini
text:
Tempat wisata candi terbesar di dunia, cocok untuk wisata edukatif untuk anak-anak. Sekarang wisatanya tambah luas  bersih, dan rapi. Tidak semua bisa naik ke candinya, untuk tiket reguler, cuma bisa sampai di pelataran candi saja. jika mau naik ke candinya, harus membeli tiket khusus. Untuk tiket masuk domestik yang reguler, dewasa 50K, dan anak 25K

Dari tempat parkiran menuju ke loket tiket, melewati kios-kios penjual yang sangat tertata rapi. Minusnya sangaaat jauh. Setelah masuk dari gerbang tiket, bisa naik kereta yang disediakan, alhamdulillah masih gratis pas saya ke sana. Cuma untuk pulangnya menuju pintu keliar bisa pakai golf car 25K per orang, atau buggy car 20K per orang. Dari pintu keluar ke parkiran tetap jalan dulu cukup jauh melewati kios-kios penjual.
textTranslated:
The largest temple tourist attraction in the world, suitable for educational tourism for children. Now the tourist area is more spacious, clean and tidy. Not everyone can go up to the temple, for regular tickets, you can only get to the temple grounds. If you want to go up to the temple, you have to buy a special ticket. For regular domestic entry tickets, adults 50K, and children 25K

From the parking lot to the ticket counter, past the neatly arranged sales stalls. The minuses are very far. After entering from the ticket gate, you can take the train provided, thank God it was still free when I got there. Just to return to the wild gate, you can use a golf car, 25K per person, or a buggy car, 20K per person. From the exit to the parking lot, walk a long way past the seller's stalls.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Tom Geinitz
text:
Sehr interessantes Bauwerk. Die Anlage drum herum ist sauber und ordentlich. Leider sind die Tickets um den Tempel zu besteigen limitiert und sehr schnell ausverkauft. Bei uns war es der Fall das wir nur Tickets bekommen haben die es dir erlauben um den Tempel zu laufen für 400k pro Person!
Ein recht frecher Preis dafür!
Überlegt es euch ob es euch das Wert ist.
textTranslated:
Very interesting building. The area around it is clean and tidy. Unfortunately, tickets to climb the temple are limited and sell out very quickly. In our case, we only got tickets that allowed you to walk around the temple for 400k per person!
A pretty cheeky price for that!
Think about whether it's worth it to you.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Benjamin Caud
text:
Un temple magnifique, qui a de belles histoires à raconter ! Prenez absolument le ticket qui vous permet d'accéder au sommet et qui vous donne accès à une visite guidée très intéressante.
Venez très en avance pour avoir le temps de rentrer dans le parc avant et de faire le musée consacré au temple avant la visite, c'est mieux dans cet ordre. Et n'hésitez pas à prendre le temps dans le parc après la visite du temple.
textTranslated:
A magnificent temple, which has beautiful stories to tell! Absolutely take the ticket which allows you to access the summit and which gives you access to a very interesting guided tour.
Come very early to have time to enter the park beforehand and visit the museum dedicated to the temple before the visit, it is better in this order. And don't hesitate to take some time in the park after visiting the temple.
title: Borobudur Temple

text: when you come to here, please join ballet ramayana. It's a musical drama without dialogue.

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Bakhtiar
text:
Candi Prambanan is an absolute marvel. This ancient Hindu temple complex took my breath away with its intricate stone carvings and towering spires. But what made my visit even more special was the Prambanan Jazz Festival 2023 happening simultaneously. The fusion of music and the temple's majestic backdrop was simply enchanting. The organizers did a fantastic job, and the atmosphere was magical.

Overall even without any event happening this place is still a masterpiece and a must visit when you visit Yogyakarta.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Keziah Tuerah
text: Love this place. If you go to Jogja, you must at least visit one of the temples...  You pay 50rb/person to get in. This place is more than just a temple. So much walking space. If you love leisure walks, this is the perfect place. Also they have some interesting photo spots. Theres also a place to buy souvenirs, and guess what? Its actually cheaper than souvenirs in Malioboro. So while youre here, get as much souvenirs as you can, to help out the sellers here. Also theres like some kind of space for festivals to be held here. So in that area, theres loads of food tents too. Interesting place. Worth going to if youre in Jogja.
title: Prambanan Temple

Prambanan is a huge Hindu temple and one of the must visit attraction in jogja.

Best time to visit it during sunset. You can also see the local dance performances and other shows.

The tickets for foreigners cost around 350k Rp and they do not have online payments.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Jack Willyanto
text: One of destination must visit when you go to Jogjakarta, beautiful temple, clean area and have many spot to take a photo 👍🏻
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Suciani Arta
text: Before you go all judge-y with the unattractive ruins and black stone temple, let me remind you this site is listed on UNESCO World Heritage Site. The story that engulfed around the building of this temple is embedded in every blood of Javanese people, even I dare say Indonesian. This temple was build on 850 CE, during the peak time of Hindu Empire and still stand to the test of time until now. Not to mention, sunset here is magnificent.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Shahril Affandi Radzali
text:
Prambanan Temple complex is an impressive ancient Hindu religion temple located in the Special Region of Jogjakarta. It a must visit place if you are first time visiting Jogjakarta and wants to learn about the history of religion and old kingdom of Java.

This is a huge temple complex therefore, please plan to spend time at least half a day there. The temple located a little bit far from the entrance therefore, be prepare to walk a distance there. Please bring umbrella if the weather forecast a rain because shelter is hard to find. Or otherwise you'll be wet running to the exit area.

If you want less crowd, please come during the weekdays and avoid local public holidays. Anyhow, this is a must visit place if you in Jogjakarta no matter you are a backpacker or with family.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Sky Stalker
text: This Temple can say loudly what is real Indonesia and how rich it was... Many things have been looted and now we can just see 30%. Stonework is really near the 9th century Cholas Dynasty and Chalukya dynasty in India. Temple represented people's faith on Bramha. Vishnu and Mahesh. Beautiful structure. Avoid local guide they're fooling people. All information available in Wikipedia just read it before you visit.

name: BAHARI
text:
Candi Borobudur sebuah candi Buddha yang terletak di Borobudur, Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia. Candi ini terletak kurang lebih 100 km di sebelah barat daya Semarang, 86 km di sebelah barat Surakarta, dan 40 km di sebelah barat laut Yogyakarta. Candi dengan banyak stupa ini didirikan oleh para penganut agama Buddha Mahayana sekitar tahun 800-an Masehi pada masa pemerintahan wangsa Syailendra. Borobudur adalah candi atau kuil Buddha terbesar di dunia,sekaligus salah satu monumen Buddha terbesar di dunia.
Harga tiket nya cukup mahal ya, dan tidak bisa naik ke atas ya, kecuali booking dulu
textTranslated:
Borobudur Temple is a Buddhist temple located in Borobudur, Magelang, Central Java, Indonesia. This temple is located approximately 100 km southwest of Semarang, 86 km west of Surakarta, and 40 km northwest of Yogyakarta. This temple with many stupas was founded by followers of Mahayana Buddhism around 800 AD during the reign of the Syailendra dynasty. Borobudur is the largest Buddhist temple or shrine in the world, as well as one of the largest Buddhist monuments in the world.
The ticket price is quite expensive, and you can't go up, unless you book first
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Eugeniya Tikhonova
text:
Этот храм является целью посещения для многих путешественников. Храм с длинной и очень необычной историей прост по своей философиии и представляет собой уровни восхождения к нирване от мира желаний. Довольно хорошо восстановлен и есть на что посмотреть. У многих статуй Будды нет головы - это результат набегов сиамцев и головы теперь хранятся в музее в Бангкоке, так что за головами в Бангкок. В храм попасть без предварительной подготовки не получится. Нужно покупать билеты на сайте онлайн. Для иностранца один билет стоит 440 тысяч в него входят ещё бутылка воды и сандалии, в которые нужно переобуваться чтобы ходить по храму. Посетителей разбивают по группам и группа идёт в сопровождении гида. Время, которое можно находиться в пределах храма - 1 час, время, которе можно по билету оставаться в окрестностях храма - целый день. Без гида не получится, гид присматривает чтобы не писали надписи и не ковыряли.
На выходе с территории храма есть много сувенирных магазинов. Сувениры на любой вкус. Также можно перекусить, есть столовая с местной кухней. Такси, если по приложению, то только Grab. Я вызывала через приложение, приехал через 3 минуты, но они не могут проехать через шлагбаум, нужно выйти за него. Туалетов на уровне храма нет, поэтому или на входе или придётся спускаться далеко на выход. Начинала свой день с рассвета на Punthuk Setumbu, потом приехала сюда (мой билет был по времени на 9-30). Рекомендую так планировать эту поездку. Красиво получается.
textTranslated:
This temple is a destination for many travelers. The temple with a long and very unusual history is simple in its philosophy and represents the levels of ascent to nirvana from the world of desires. Quite well restored and a lot to look at. Many Buddha statues do not have a head - this is the result of raids by the Siamese and the heads are now kept in a museum in Bangkok, so go to Bangkok for the heads. You won’t be able to get into the temple without prior preparation. You need to buy tickets online. For a foreigner, one ticket costs 440 thousand; it also includes a bottle of water and sandals, which you need to change your shoes to walk around the temple. Visitors are divided into groups and the group is accompanied by a guide. The time that you can stay within the temple is 1 hour, the time that you can stay in the vicinity of the temple with a ticket is the whole day. It won’t be possible without a guide; the guide makes sure that they don’t write signs or pick around.
There are many souvenir shops at the exit from the temple grounds. Souvenirs for every taste. You can also have a snack; there is a dining room with local cuisine. Taxi, if using the app, then only Grab. I called through the app, arrived in 3 minutes, but they can’t get through the barrier, you need to go beyond it. There are no toilets at the temple level, so either at the entrance or you have to go down a long way to the exit. I started my day at dawn at Punthuk Setumbu, then came here (my ticket was for 9:30). I recommend planning your trip this way. It turns out beautifully.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: HALHIL CHANNEL
text:
Jalan2 kali ini aku berkunjung ke Candi yang sangat istimewa.... ya, Candi Borobudur... kebetulan habis acara study ke salah satu SMK Negeri di Bawen yang memakan waktu (waktu emang bisa dimakan) selama 4 hari. Sebelum balik ke Kalimantan Tengah, aku dan kawan2 menyempatkan untuk mampir kesana...
Buat kamu yang belum pernah kesana, atau ada rencana kesana.. ini aku kasih sedikit informasi tentang candi Borobudur...
Borobudur adalah salah satu mahakarya dunia yang wajib kamu kunjungi, terutama jika kamu pecinta sejarah, seni, atau hanya sekadar ingin merasakan kedamaian di tengah kemegahan masa lalu. Letaknya di Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Borobudur adalah candi Buddha terbesaaaaar di dunia dan menjadi salah satu ikon wisata Indonesia. Begitu kira2 tentang candi ini...
Candi ini seperti teka-teki raksasa dari batu. Dibangun pada abad ke-8 dan ke-9 oleh Dinasti Syailendra katanya, lama juga kan ya... soalnya besar banget... Setiap relief di Borobudur menceritakan kisah perjalanan hidup Buddha. Kamu bisa menghabiskan waktu berjam-jam hanya mengagumi detailnya, bahkan seharian juga gak cukup.
Lokasinya yang dikelilingi perbukitan membuat Borobudur semakin cantik, terutama saat matahari terbit. Kalau datang pagi-pagi, kamu bisa menikmati momen sunrise yang magis, dengan kabut tipis menyelimuti area sekitar. Keren banget, dah...
Terdapat museum, area parkir luas, dan toko suvenir dengan banyak pilihan menarik (saya waktu itu beli kaos dan beberapa gantungan kunci dengan bentuk candi Borobudur, buat oleh2 untuk kawan2 di kalimantan).
Panduan tur tersedia jika ingin memahami sejarah dan makna relief dengan lebih baik. (ada satu larangan yang disampaikan pemandunya.. "jangan sampai menyentuh reliefnya ya.... karna tangan kita berkeringat dan mengandung garam yang bisa membuat korosi pada relief, cukup di lihat saja" Pemandu kami waktu itu namanya Pak Soni. orangnya baik dan sabar menjawab pertanyaan2 dari ku...
Banyak warung makan di sekitar, jadi kamu bisa mencoba kuliner lokal setelah berkeliling. Es kelapa muda faforitku. segerrrrrr
Dan ini sedikit tips dari aku ya....
Datanglah pagi atau sore hari... Selain lebih sejuk, momen sunrise atau sunset di Borobudur benar-benar tak terlupakan. Karna klo siang hari dan kebetulan lagi panas terik menyengat, buat cewek2 bisa gosong nanti kulitmu yang putih mulus itu.... hehehe... dan satu lagi... Jaga Kebersihan, meski pengunjung banyak, pastikan kamu tetap menjaga keindahan situs ini dengan tidak membuang sampah sembarangan....
Oh iya... tiket masuknya biar kamu bisa naik sampai atas candi hanya cukup Rp 120K, aja... murah kan... Begitulah ceritaku di Candi Borobudur...
textTranslated:
This time I visited a very special temple.... yes, Borobudur Temple... coincidentally after a study program at one of the State Vocational Schools in Bawen which took (the time could be eaten) for 4 days. Before returning to Central Kalimantan, my friends and I took the time to stop by there...
For those of you who have never been there, or have plans to go there... here I will give you a little information about Borobudur temple...
Borobudur is one of the world's masterpieces that you must visit, especially if you are a lover of history, art, or just want to feel peace amidst the splendor of the past. Located in Magelang, Central Java, Borobudur is the largest Buddhist temple in the world and is one of Indonesia's tourist icons. That's all about this temple...
This temple is like a giant puzzle made of stone. It was built in the 8th and 9th centuries by the Syailendra Dynasty, he said, it's also a long time ago... because it's really big... Every relief on Borobudur tells the story of Buddha's life journey. You can spend hours just admiring the details, even a whole day isn't enough.
Its location surrounded by hills makes Borobudur even more beautiful, especially at sunrise. If you come early in the morning, you can enjoy a magical sunrise moment, with a thin mist covering the surrounding area. Really cool, yeah...
There is a museum, a large parking area, and a souvenir shop with lots of interesting choices (at that time I bought a t-shirt and several key chains in the shape of the Borobudur temple, as souvenirs for friends in Kalimantan).
Tour guides are available if you wish to better understand the history and meaning of the reliefs. (There was one prohibition conveyed by the guide... "Don't touch the reliefs, okay... because our hands are sweaty and contain salt which can corrode the reliefs, just look at it." Our guide at that time was Mr Soni. He was a kind and patient person. answer my questions...
There are lots of food stalls around, so you can try local culinary delights after walking around. My favorite young coconut ice. freshrrrrrr
And here are a few tips from me...
Come in the morning or evening... Apart from being cooler, the sunrise or sunset moments at Borobudur are truly unforgettable. Because if it's midday and it happens to be scorching hot, girls can burn your smooth white skin... hehehe... and one more thing... Maintain cleanliness, even though there are lots of visitors, make sure you maintain the beauty of this site by do not litter....
Oh yes... the entrance ticket so you can climb to the top of the temple is only IDR 120K, that's all... cheap right... That's my story at Borobudur Temple...
title: Borobudur Temple

text:
Ini kali ketiga saya ke Borubudur setelah waktu yang lama. Sekitar 2 dekade lalu jadi banyak perubahan.
1. Parkir mobil sekarang untuk mobil ada tempat parkir yang cukup luas tinggal mengikuti arahan petunjuk dr sekitar pintu masuk.
2. Kalau berminat untuk naik ke candi lebih baik beli tiket online apalagi di peak season karena sekarang ada pembatasan untuk naik ke candi kalau beli go show bisa hanya kebagian tiket sampai pelataran/ halaman nya saja sebesar 50 rb untuk turis domestik.
3. Untuk bisa ke candi dr tempat pembelian tiket disediakan golfcart/ kereta bugy gratis. Hanya dr tempat penurunan ke area candi ada tersedia berbayar. Hanya sebetulnya itu sudah dekat hanya sekitar 300mtr. Jadi kalau tidak panas saya rasa jalan kaki akan menyenangkan sambil melihat pemandangan.
4. Dilarang membawa makanan ke area candi kalau minuman masih boleh.
5. Toilet tersedia di area pembelian tiket jadi disarankan menggunakan toilet sebwlum naik ke Candi
textTranslated:
This is my third time to Borubudur after a long time. About 2 decades ago there were a lot of changes.
1. Car parking: Now for cars there is quite a large parking space, just follow the directions around the entrance.
2. If you are interested in going up to the temple, it is better to buy tickets online, especially during peak season because now there are restrictions on going up to the temple. If you buy a go show, you can only get a ticket up to the courtyard/yard for 50 thousand for domestic tourists.
3. To get to the temple from the place where the ticket was purchased, a free golf cart/ buggy is provided. Only from the drop-off point to the temple area is there a fee available. Only actually it is close, only around 300mtr. So if it's not hot I think it would be fun to walk while looking at the view.
4. It is prohibited to bring food into the temple area if drinks are still allowed.
5. Toilets are available in the ticket purchasing area so it is recommended to use the toilet before going up to the temple
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Rata Cameng
text:
Kompleks percandian Prambanan secara keseluruhan terletak di Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta, tetapi pintu administrasinya terletak di Jawa Tengah. Hal ini yang membuat Candi Prambanan terletak di 2 tempat yakni di Desa Bokoharjo, Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta,[1][2] dan di Tlogo, Prambanan, Kabupaten Klaten, Jawa Tengah, atau kurang lebih 17 kilometer timur laut dari Kota Yogya, 50 kilometer barat daya dari Kota Surakarta dan 120 kilometer selatan dari Kota Semarang, persis di perbatasan antara Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta dan Jawa Tengah.[3]
Candi ini adalah termasuk Situs Warisan Dunia UNESCO, candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia, sekaligus salah satu candi terindah di Asia Tenggara. Arsitektur bangunan ini berbentuk tinggi dan ramping sesuai dengan arsitektur Hindu pada umumnya dengan candi Siwa sebagai candi utama memiliki ketinggian mencapai 47 meter menjulang di tengah kompleks gugusan candi-candi yang lebih kecil.[4] Sebagai salah satu candi termegah di Asia Tenggara, candi Prambanan menjadi daya tarik kunjungan wisatawan dari seluruh dunia.[5]
Menurut prasasti Siwagrha, candi ini mulai dibangun pada sekitar tahun 850 masehi oleh Rakai Pikatan, dan terus dikembangkan dan diperluas oleh Balitung Maha Sambu, pada masa Kerajaan Medang Mataram.
Etimologi
sunting
Nama Prambanan, berasal dari nama desa tempat candi ini berdiri, diduga merupakan perubahan nama dialek bahasa Jawa dari istilah teologi Hindu Para Brahman yang bermakna "Brahman Agung" yaitu Brahman atau realitas abadi tertinggi dan teragung yang tak dapat digambarkan, yang kerap disamakan dengan konsep Tuhan dalam agama Hindu. Pendapat lain menganggap Para Brahman mungkin merujuk kepada masa jaya candi ini yang dahulu dipenuhi oleh para brahmana. Pendapat lain mengajukan anggapan bahwa nama "Prambanan" berasal dari akar kata mban dalam Bahasa Jawa yang bermakna menanggung atau memikul tugas, merujuk kepada para dewa Hindu yang mengemban tugas menata dan menjalankan keselarasan jagat.
Nama lain dari Prambanan dapat berarti 5 (lima) gunung yang dalam bahasa Khmer/Kamboja 5 (lima) adalah Pram dan banam adalah gunung (ប្រាំភ្នំ). Hal ini menggambarkan 5 puncak gunung dari Himalaya di India. Mengingat pada saat yang sama dalam kronik Khmer bahwa Bangsa Jawa pernah menjajah Khmer selama 200 tahun dan Jayawarman ke 2 yang pernah di Jawa merupakan pahlawan yang membebaskan Khmer dari dominasi Jawa.
Nama asli kompleks candi Hindu ini adalah nama dari Bahasa Sanskerta; Siwagrha (Rumah Siwa) atau Siwalaya (Alam Siwa), berdasarkan Prasasti Siwagrha yang bertarikh 778 Saka (856 Masehi). Trimurti dimuliakan dalam kompleks candi ini dengan tiga candi utamanya memuliakan Brahma, Siwa, dan Wisnu. Akan tetapi Siwa Mahadewa yang menempati ruang utama di candi Siwa adalah dewa yang paling dimuliakan dalam kompleks candi ini.
textTranslated:
The Prambanan temple complex as a whole is located in the Special Region of Yogyakarta, but the administrative gate is located in Central Java. This is why Prambanan Temple is located in 2 places, namely in Bokoharjo Village, Prambanan, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta Special Region,[1][2] and in Tlogo, Prambanan, Klaten Regency, Central Java, or approximately 17 kilometers northeast of Yogya City, 50 kilometers southwest of Surakarta City and 120 kilometers south of Semarang City, right on the border between the Special Regions. Yogyakarta and Central Java.[3]
This temple is a UNESCO World Heritage Site, the largest Hindu temple in Indonesia, as well as one of the most beautiful temples in Southeast Asia. The architecture of this building is tall and slender in accordance with Hindu architecture in general with the Shiva temple as the main temple having a height of up to 47 meters standing in the middle of a complex of smaller temples.[4] As one of the grandest temples in Southeast Asia, Prambanan temple is an attraction for tourists from all over the world.[5]
According to the Siwagrha inscription, this temple began to be built around 850 AD by Rakai Pikatan, and continued to be developed and expanded by Balitung Maha Sambu, during the Medang Mataram Kingdom.
Etymology
edit
The name Prambanan, derived from the name of the village where this temple stands, is thought to be a change in the name of the Javanese dialect of the Hindu theological term Para Brahman which means "Great Brahman", namely Brahman or the highest and greatest eternal reality that cannot be described, which is often equated with the concept of God in Hinduism. Another opinion is that Para Brahmans may refer to the heyday of this temple which was once filled with Brahmans. Another opinion suggests that the name "Prambanan" comes from the root word mban in Javanese which means to bear or carry a task, referring to the Hindu gods who carry out the task of organizing and maintaining harmony in the universe.
Another name for Prambanan can mean 5 (five) mountains, which in Khmer/Cambodian language 5 (five) is Pram and banam is mountain (ប្រាំភ្នំ). It depicts the 5 mountain peaks of the Himalayas in India. Remembering at the same time in the Khmer chronicle that the Javanese had colonized the Khmer for 200 years and Jayawarman the 2nd who was in Java was the hero who freed the Khmer from Javanese domination.
The original name of this Hindu temple complex is a Sanskrit name; Siwagrha (House of Shiva) or Siwalaya (Nature of Shiva), based on the Siwagrha Inscription which is dated 778 Saka (856 AD). The Trimurti is glorified in this temple complex with the three main temples glorifying Brahma, Shiva and Vishnu. However, Shiva Mahadewa who occupies the main room in the Shiva temple is the god most glorified in this temple complex.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Mazaya Galva
text:
Candi Prambanan: Kencan Budaya yang Nggak Pernah Membosankan Kalau kamu mau liburan yang bukan cuma asyik tapi juga berfaedah.

Candi Prambanan wajib banget masuk bucket list-mu. Begitu sampai, siap-siap dibuat terpukau sama keagungan candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia ini. Percayalah, aura megahnya langsung bikin kamu merasa kecil… dan mungkin sedikit kepikiran, “Dulu mereka bangun ini pakai apa ya? Magic?!”

Perjalanan ke Prambanan cukup mudah. Lokasinya strategis, sekitar 17 km dari pusat Kota Yogyakarta. Tapi kalau kamu tim yang selalu nyasar meskipun pakai Google Maps, jangan khawatir. Tanya aja penduduk lokal, dan mereka bakal senyum ramah sambil kasih arahan detail (bonus cerita sejarah singkat kadang-kadang!). Di sepanjang jalan menuju candi, kamu juga bisa nemu banyak jajanan tradisional, jadi mampir beli bakpia buat bekal itu ide yang oke.

Begitu masuk kompleks candi, suasananya langsung bikin tenang. Ada banyak candi besar dan kecil yang berdiri megah, tapi pusat perhatian jelas ada di Candi Siwa, candi utama setinggi 47 meter. Di sini, aku sempat mikir, “Gimana caranya mereka angkat batu-batu segede ini ke atas tanpa alat berat?!” Tapi ya sudahlah, nikmati aja keajaibannya. Kamu juga bisa jalan-jalan ke candi-candi lain seperti Candi Brahma dan Candi Wisnu. Kalau lagi malas jalan kaki (atau sudah capek foto-foto), kamu bisa sewa kereta mini yang ada di area ini. Santai, nggak usah malu, banyak kok orang dewasa yang naik karena gemes sama keretanya.

Jangan lupa bawa kamera atau HP yang baterainya penuh! Candi Prambanan itu surganya foto estetik, dari sudut mana pun. Mulai dari detail ukiran di dinding sampai pemandangan sunset yang cantiknya nggak main-main. Kalau cuaca cerah, warna jingga matahari berpadu sama siluet candi itu rasanya bikin ingin langsung bikin caption puitis.

Pro tip: Kalau mau foto tanpa banyak orang di latar belakang, datanglah pagi-pagi banget. Tapi ya siap-siap juga, udaranya masih dingin. Jadi jaket itu teman terbaikmu.

Kalau kamu datang malam hari, jangan lewatkan Sendratari Ramayana. Pertunjukan ini menceritakan kisah epik Ramayana dengan latar belakang langsung Candi Prambanan. Serius, vibes-nya seperti nonton drama Korea… tapi versi Jawa kuno. Oh, dan kalau lapar, ada banyak penjaja makanan di sekitar area parkir. Cobain sate kelinci, kalau berani, karena katanya dagingnya lebih empuk dari ayam!

Candi Prambanan bukan cuma destinasi wisata, tapi juga pengalaman belajar sejarah yang fun dan bikin bangga. Kamu bakal keluar dari sana sambil mikir, “Kok aku baru ke sini sekarang?” Tapi ya, better late than never, kan?

Ratingku? 4.9/5. Sisa 0.1 itu cuma karena panasnya Jogja yang bikin keringetan, tapi itu bisa diatasi dengan bawa topi dan air minum. Jadi, kapan kita ke Prambanan bareng? 😄
textTranslated:
Prambanan Temple: Cultural Dating that is Never Boring If you want a holiday that is not only fun but also useful.

Prambanan Temple really must be on your bucket list. Once you arrive, get ready to be amazed by the majesty of this largest Hindu temple in Indonesia. Believe me, its majestic aura will immediately make you feel small... and maybe think a little, "What did they wear when they woke up? Magic?!”

The trip to Prambanan is quite easy. The location is strategic, around 17 km from the center of Yogyakarta City. But if you are a team that always gets lost even though you use Google Maps, don't worry. Just ask a local, and they'll have a friendly smile and give you detailed directions (bonus for a quick history story sometimes!). Along the road to the temple, you can also find lots of traditional snacks, so stopping to buy bakpia for lunch is a good idea.

As soon as you enter the temple complex, the atmosphere is immediately calm. There are many large and small temples that stand majestically, but the center of attention is clearly the Shiva Temple, the main temple which is 47 meters high. Here, I thought, "How do they lift these big rocks up without heavy equipment?!" But never mind, just enjoy the magic. You can also visit other temples such as the Brahma Temple and the Vishnu Temple. If you don't feel like walking (or are tired of taking photos), you can rent a mini train in this area. Relax, don't be embarrassed, there are lots of adults who ride because they are excited about the train.

Don't forget to bring a camera or cellphone with a full battery! Prambanan Temple is a paradise for aesthetic photos, from any angle. Starting from the detailed carvings on the walls to the beautiful sunset views that are no joke. If the weather is sunny, the orange color of the sun combined with the silhouette of the temple makes you want to immediately write a poetic caption.

Pro tip: If you want photos without lots of people in the background, come really early in the morning. But yeah, get ready, the air is still cold. So the jacket is your best friend.

If you come at night, don't miss the Ramayana Ballet. This show tells the epic story of the Ramayana with the direct backdrop of Prambanan Temple. Seriously, the vibes are like watching a Korean drama... but the old Javanese version. Oh, and if you're hungry, there are lots of food vendors around the parking area. Try the rabbit satay, if you dare, because the meat is said to be more tender than chicken!

Prambanan Temple is not only a tourist destination, but also a fun and proud history learning experience. You'll leave there thinking, "How come I'm only here now?" But yeah, better late than never, right?

My rating? 4.9/5. The remaining 0.1 is just because of the Jogja heat which makes you sweat, but that can be overcome by bringing a hat and drinking water. So, when are we going to Prambanan together? 😄
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia

text:
26 Jan 2025, kali ke-2 kesini. pertamanya waktu 2015 Masi bocil banget sama BPK dan adek. sampe Prambanan sekitar jam 10, banyak yang sewain payung (10 atau 20 ribu) tapi aku ga sewa karna bawa payung sendiri hehehee
waktu kesini baru tersadar bahwa Roro Jonggrang itu fiktif, Prambanan lebih menceritakan tentang Hindu, dilihat dari relief yang ada pada candi, dan patun dewa Dewi Hindu yang ada di dalamnya. tapi waktu keluar ada yang lucu, ada ibu" yang lewat sama ibu" lain dan anak" mereka, dia ngarang cerita baru -> "jadi ini dibuat dalam 1 malam sama jin, tapi karna keburu pagi jadi batunya dibuang2in sama jin, makanya ini banyak baru berserakan" 🤣🤣
padahal batu" yang berserakan itu akibat gempa Jogja sekitar 2006 (kl gk salah) tp malah jadi cerita baru 🤣

kita sempat minta fotografer lokal untuk fotoin, 1 foto 20k, kualitasnya bagus dan menurutku ini masih tergolong murah :)
waktu jalan keluar, ada panahan jadi kita main itu 1 orangnya ramah 20k. dan terakhir kita beli souvenir. murah bangettt ganci seribuan dan gelang 5000. kemarin beli gelang 3+ ganci 1 harusnya 16k tapi ibunya diskon jadi 15k atau bisa dibilang gancinya gratis wkwkwk

seru banget Prambanan walau kita dtgnya siang bolong tapi tetap bahagia bisa kesana.
Nb: pesan tiket online biar gak ngantri, kalo offline antri nya sangat panjang.
textTranslated:
26 Jan 2025, 2nd time here. The first time was in 2015. Masi was really small with BPK and his younger brother. arrived at Prambanan around 10, many people rented umbrellas (10 or 20 thousand) but I didn't rent one because I brought my own umbrella hehehee
When I came here I realized that Roro Jonggrang was fictional, Prambanan tells more about Hinduism, seen from the reliefs on the temple, and the statues of Hindu gods and goddesses in it. but when I came out there was something funny, there was a mother who passed by with another mother and their child, she made up a new story -> "So this was made in one night by the genie, but because of the rush in the morning the stones were thrown away by the genie, that's why there are a lot of these just scattered" 🤣🤣
Even though the scattered stones were caused by the Jogja earthquake around 2006 (if I'm not mistaken) it's actually become a new story 🤣

we asked a local photographer to take photos, 1 photo costs 20k, the quality is good and I think this is still relatively cheap :)
On our way out, there was archery so we played, 1 person was friendly, 20k. and finally we bought souvenirs. really cheap, a thousand bracelets and a 5000 bracelet. Yesterday I bought 3 bracelets + 1 bracelet, it should have been 16k but my mother had a discount so it was 15k or you could say the bracelet was free hahaha

Prambanan was really exciting, even though we arrived in broad daylight, we were still happy to be able to go there.
Nb: order tickets online so you don't have to queue, if you're offline the queue is very long.
title: Prambanan Temple

text:

It is recommended to use an umbrella because during the dry season the road is quite far and hot... wear comfortable footwear... make sure you have eaten because there are no food sellers in the temple area... there is only one seller selling mineral water and it is far away. 1 bottle of mineral water costs 10 thousand.

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Winda Chewy
text:
Pertama kalinya liburan keluarga ke kota Yogyakarta dan tempat pertama yg dituju adalah Candi Prambanan. Lokasinya sangat strategis karena berada dipinggir jalan raya Solo-Yogyakarta. Tapi kemarin pas kesini belokan pertigaan ke arah candi belum ditutup, memang macet banget karena bertepatan dgn hari libur nataru dan libur sekolah. Pas pulang dari candi pertigaannya setengah tertutup utk menghindari penumpukan kemacetan di lampu merah.

Saya beli tiketnya lewat tiket.com dpt potongan yg cukup gede jadi cuman bayar 142k (4 org dewasa dan 1 org anak). Worth it kan.
Harga tiket dewasa : 50k/orang
Harga tiket anak : 25k/anak
Kalau beli tiket lewat marketplace gak perlu antri tinggal scan barcode trus diprint tiketnya. Yg antri panjang tuh kl kita beli tiket masuknya on the spot (disediakan tenda dan tempat duduk utk mengantri)

textTranslated:
First time on family holiday to the city of Yogyakarta and the first place to go was Prambanan Temple. The location is very strategic because it is on the side of the Solo-Yogyakarta highway. But yesterday when we got here the turn at the T-junction towards the temple wasn't closed yet, it was really jammed because it coincided with the Christmas holidays and school holidays. When returning from the temple, the T-junction was half closed to avoid the buildup of traffic jams at the red lights.

I bought the tickets via tiket.com and got a pretty big discount so I only paid 142k (4 adults and 1 child). Worth it, right?
Adult ticket price: 50k/person
Child ticket price: 25k/child
If you buy tickets via the marketplace, you don't need to queue, just scan the barcode and then print the ticket. The long queue is if we buy entry tickets on the spot (tents and seating are provided for queuing)

There is also a traditional market event in the temple grounds. There is also a photo service that says 'Prambanan Temple' with a price per photo of 50k but if you use a cellphone it's free (the father said so). On the right side of the temple, there are children's toys, old school toys (dakon, engkle, etc.), painting, bicycles, and many more, just a short walk from the exit of the temple. There are other temples there too, but the one most visited by people is the Prambanan temple.

textTranslated:
Came here on a long weekend. It's dense, but quite comfortable for traveling, because the area is very large. Adult tickets cost IDR 50,000 and children IDR 25,000. If you want to bundle it with an entrance ticket to Borobudur temple and/or Ratu Boko temple, you can. To get to Ratu Boko Temple, there is a free shuttle directly from Prambanan Temple.

There are also bicycle rentals here to get around the temple area.

If you visit during the day and want to have lunch, there is an entrance ticket plus meal package of IDR 85,000. Only yesterday when I arrived at Prambanan it was quite late, so I couldn't try the meal package.

It's nice to visit here in the morning or afternoon. If it is afternoon and the weather is favorable, you can also see the sunset.

textTranslated:
Visiting Prambanan Temple was a childhood dream. Thank God, towards the end of last year I was able to visit.
The first impression is that Masya Allah, it is majestic and beautiful, spacious too, lots of local and foreign tourists visit.
Because when I visited during the holidays it was busy and there were queues too.
It is recommended to go there early so it's not hot when you want to go around.

Very good for educating children too. The facilities are also good... There is a mini zoo too, so children can feed the deer by buying water spinach for 5000 rupiah / bunch.
Continue to obey the existing regulations, guys.
The ticket price is really worth it.
Adult: 50 thousand/person
Children over 3 years old: 25 thousand/child.
The service at the counter is also friendly, kind and informative.
There is a play area around the park for children
comfortable and happy.
If you are tired of walking around the temple and want to go out, you can stop by for a moment to buy souvenirs and eat and drink... Judging from the menu list, the prices are still affordable.
It is recommended that if you want to visit Prambanan Temple, bring an umbrella, drinking water, hat or glasses, guys. (There are also umbrella rentals if you forget not to bring an umbrella)
Hopefully we can visit Prambanan Temple again. .❤️❤️
The toilets and prayer room are also clean 👍🏻👍🏻
It is a mandatory tourist destination if you are in Jogyakarta.

name: Gathut Imam Gunadi
text:
Candi Prambanan adalah kompleks candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia yang terletak di dekat Yogyakarta, tepatnya di Kabupaten Sleman, Provinsi Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta. Candi ini dibangun pada abad ke-9 Masehi, pada masa pemerintahan Raja Rakai Pikatan dari Kerajaan Mataram Hindu. Candi Prambanan terkenal dengan arsitektur yang megah dan artistik, serta memiliki relief yang menggambarkan kisah-kisah dari epos Ramayana dan Bhagavata Purana.

Kompleks candi utama terdiri dari tiga candi besar yang didedikasikan untuk Trimurti, yaitu Siwa, Wisnu, dan Brahma. Candi Siwa, yang merupakan candi terbesar di antara ketiganya, memiliki arca Siwa Mahadewa yang menonjol sebagai simbol keagungan dewa dalam agama Hindu. Di sekitarnya, terdapat candi-candi kecil yang juga memiliki fungsi serupa, masing-masing untuk dewa Wisnu dan Brahma.

Candi Prambanan tidak hanya dikenal karena nilai sejarah dan keagungannya, tetapi juga karena keindahan desainnya yang mencerminkan kebudayaan Hindu kuno di Nusantara. Relief yang terukir pada dinding candi menggambarkan berbagai cerita mitologi Hindu, seperti kisah Ramayana yang sangat terkenal dan kisah Dewi Durga.

Pada abad ke-16, Candi Prambanan mulai ditinggalkan dan terbengkalai akibat serangan musuh dan bencana alam, termasuk gempa bumi yang merusak struktur candi. Meski demikian, pada abad ke-19, restorasi besar-besaran dimulai, yang hingga kini terus dilakukan untuk menjaga keutuhan situs ini.

Kini, Candi Prambanan menjadi salah satu destinasi wisata budaya yang sangat populer di Indonesia dan telah diakui sebagai Situs Warisan Dunia oleh UNESCO sejak 1991. Selain sebagai situs sejarah, Candi Prambanan juga menjadi tempat perayaan festival seni dan budaya, seperti pertunjukan Ramayana Ballet yang sangat terkenal. Candi ini tak hanya menarik bagi para wisatawan, tetapi juga bagi para peneliti dan arkeolog yang terus menggali lebih dalam sejarahnya.
textTranslated:
Prambanan Temple is the largest Hindu temple complex in Indonesia which is located near Yogyakarta, precisely in Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta Special Region Province. This temple was built in the 9th century AD, during the reign of King Rakai Pikatan from the Hindu Mataram Kingdom. Prambanan Temple is famous for its magnificent and artistic architecture, and has reliefs depicting stories from the epics Ramayana and Bhagavata Purana.

The main temple complex consists of three large temples dedicated to the Trimurti, namely Shiva, Vishnu, and Brahma. The Shiva Temple, which is the largest temple of the three, has a statue of Shiva Mahadewa which stands out as a symbol of the majesty of the god in Hinduism. In the surrounding area, there are small temples that also have a similar function, respectively for the gods Vishnu and Brahma.

Prambanan Temple is not only known for its historical value and majesty, but also for the beauty of its design which reflects the ancient Hindu culture of the archipelago. The reliefs carved on the temple walls depict various Hindu mythological stories, such as the very famous Ramayana and the story of the Goddess Durga.

In the 16th century, Prambanan Temple began to be abandoned and neglected due to enemy attacks and natural disasters, including earthquakes which damaged the temple structure. However, in the 19th century, a major restoration began, which continues to this day to maintain the integrity of the site.

Now, Prambanan Temple has become one of the most popular cultural tourist destinations in Indonesia and has been recognized as a World Heritage Site by UNESCO since 1991. Apart from being a historical site, Prambanan Temple is also a venue for arts and cultural festivals, such as the very famous Ramayana Ballet performance. . This temple is not only interesting for tourists, but also for researchers and archaeologists who continue to dig deeper into its history.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia

text:
