Jadi akhirnya jalan kaki ke prambanan utk masuk ke dalam, sth foto2, baru lanjut jalan kaki lumayan utk cari kereta listrik nya ( per orang Rp 20rb)  utk lanjut ke sewu.
Diinfo hanya boleh foto 5 menit, jd kita hanya foto di depannya, tp ada penumpang lain satu keluarga msk ke dlm candi sewu dan foto di dlm agak lama, jd kita lama tungguin di kereta listrik.

Kalo naik golf car cocok buat lansia, tp jd gak bisa msk candi prambanan, tp kalo jalan kaki ke prambanan kemudian cari kereta listriknya, jalan jauh ( jd gak cocok buat lansia).
Saran : kereta listriknya perlu di depan prambanan ya, jd lansia udah ga kuat jln bisa lanjut kereta listrik.

Note : tiket candi prambanan Rp 50rb, tp krn kita beli tiket terusan candi borobudur dan prambanan, jd total tiket utk 2 candi jd Rp 80rb (jika beli tiket masing2 candi @ Rp 50rb).
Kita belinya pas di candi borobudur nya, dan diinfo tiket terusan berlaku 2 hr, tp kita datang di hari yang sama utk 2 candi tsb.
textTranslated:
Initially I wanted to take a golf car (expensive Rp. 200 thousand for 6 people), but was limited to going to Prambanan, only taking photos for 5 minutes and continuing to Sewu, so I couldn't go to Prambanan.

So finally I walked to Prambanan to go inside, after taking photos, then continued walking quite a bit to find the electric train (per person IDR 20 thousand) to continue to Sewu.
We were told that we were only allowed to take photos for 5 minutes, so we only took photos in front of it, but there were other passengers from the same family who entered Sewu Temple and took photos inside for quite a long time, so we waited a long time on the electric train.

If you take a golf car, it's suitable for the elderly, but you can't go to Prambanan temple, but if you walk to Prambanan and then look for an electric train, it's a long way (so it's not suitable for the elderly).
Suggestion: the electric train needs to be in front of Prambanan, so elderly people don't have the strength to walk so they can take the electric train.

Note: the Prambanan temple ticket is IDR 50 thousand, but because we bought a continuous ticket for Borobudur and Prambanan temples, the total ticket for the 2 temples is IDR 80 thousand (if you buy tickets for each temple @ IDR 50 thousand).
We bought it right at the Borobudur temple, and were told that the season ticket was valid for 2 days, but we came on the same day for the 2 temples.

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: VincenSurya Wibisono
text:
Candi Borobudur adalah sebuah candi Buddha yang terletak di Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia. Candi ini merupakan salah satu monumen Buddha terbesar di dunia dan telah diakui sebagai Situs Warisan Dunia UNESCO.
Candi Borobudur pada kenyataannya;
* Arsitektur Unik: Candi Borobudur memiliki bentuk stupa raksasa yang terdiri dari beberapa tingkatan. Setiap tingkatan memiliki makna filosofis dalam ajaran Buddha.
* Relief Mendalam: Relief-relief pada dinding candi menceritakan kisah perjalanan spiritual seorang Buddha menuju pencerahan. Relief-relief ini sangat detail dan indah.
* Stupa-Stupa Kecil: Di puncak candi terdapat ratusan stupa kecil yang berisi patung Buddha. Setiap stupa melambangkan pencapaian spiritual.

Candi Borobudur diperkirakan dibangun pada abad ke-8 dan ke-9 Masehi pada masa pemerintahan Wangsa Syailendra. Candi ini mengalami beberapa kali renovasi dan pemugaran, terutama pada abad ke-20.
Candi Borobudur merupakan:
* Simbol Peradaban: Candi Borobudur adalah simbol peradaban yang tinggi pada masa lalu.
* Karya Seni Agung: Arsitektur dan relief-reliefnya merupakan karya seni yang luar biasa.
* Pusat Spiritual: Candi ini menjadi tempat ziarah bagi umat Buddha dari seluruh dunia.

Kami berkesempatan mengunjungi candi borobudur ini hari ini 28 Des 2024, sampai ke atas candi.

Saat registrasi pengunjung diwajibkan mdmakai sandal Upanat yang disediakan pengelola.

Kali ini pengunjung di bagi waktu kunjungannya menjadi beberapa sesi dengan kurun waktu pembatasan selama 1 jam, dengan di dampingi pemandu.

* bersama pemandu kami Menjelajahi Candi berjalan mengelilingi candi dan menikmati keindahan arsitekturnya. Dengan diberikan penjelasan singkat oleh pemandu
* Pemandu menjelaskan detail relief-relief dan menceritakan kisah perjalanan spiritual Buddha.
* Mendengar Sejarah yang diceritakan pemandu kami mengikuti tur untuk mengetahui sejarah dan makna Candi Borobudur.

Tips Berkunjung:
* Waktu Terbaik: Datang pagi atau sore hari untuk menghindari cuaca panas.
* Pakaian: Kenakan pakaian yang sopan dan nyaman.
textTranslated:
Borobudur Temple is a Buddhist temple located in Magelang, Central Java, Indonesia. This temple is one of the largest Buddhist monuments in the world and has been recognized as a UNESCO World Heritage Site.
Borobudur Temple in fact;
* Unique Architecture: Borobudur Temple has the shape of a giant stupa consisting of several levels. Each level has a philosophical meaning in Buddhist teachings.
* Deep Relief: The reliefs on the temple walls tell the story of a Buddha's spiritual journey towards enlightenment. These reliefs are very detailed and beautiful.
* Small Stupas: At the top of the temple there are hundreds of small stupas containing Buddha statues. Each stupa symbolizes spiritual attainment.

Borobudur Temple is thought to have been built in the 8th and 9th centuries AD during the reign of the Syailendra dynasty. This temple underwent several renovations and restorations, especially in the 20th century.
Borobudur Temple is:
* Symbol of Civilization: Borobudur Temple is a symbol of high civilization in the past.
* Great Works of Art: The architecture and reliefs are extraordinary works of art.
* Spiritual Center: This temple is a place of pilgrimage for Buddhists from all over the world.

We had the opportunity to visit Borobudur temple today, 28 Dec 2024, all the way to the top of the temple.

When registering, visitors are required to wear Upanat sandals provided by the manager.

This time, visitors are divided into several sessions with a time limit of 1 hour, accompanied by a guide.

* with our guide Exploring the Temple walking around the temple and enjoying the beauty of the architecture. With a brief explanation given by the guide
* The guide explains the details of the reliefs and tells the story of Buddha's spiritual journey.
* Listen to the history told by our guide. Take a tour to find out the history and meaning of Borobudur Temple.

Visiting Tips:
* Best Time: Come in the morning or evening to avoid the heat.
* Clothing: Wear modest and comfortable clothing.
title: Borobudur Temple

text:
Setelah mengunjungi Candi Borobudur, aku masih terpesona dengan keindahan dan kemegahannya.  Bayangan relief-relief yang rumit dan detail, serta pemandangan matahari terbit yang mempesona dari puncak candi, masih terukir jelas di benakku.

Aku masih bisa merasakan aura spiritual yang kuat di sekitar candi.  Suasana hening dan khidmat membuatku merasa damai dan tenang.  Aku juga terkesan dengan arsitektur candi yang begitu kompleks dan rumit,  membuktikan kecerdasan dan kreativitas para leluhur kita.

Yang paling berkesan adalah saat aku menaiki anak tangga menuju puncak candi.  Setiap langkah terasa sakral dan menuntunku pada sebuah pencerahan.  Pemandangan dari puncak candi benar-benar menakjubkan,  hamparan hijau sawah dan pegunungan yang luas terlihat begitu indah.  Rasanya seperti berada di surga dunia.

Kunjungan ke Candi Borobudur bukan hanya sekadar wisata,  tapi juga sebuah pengalaman spiritual yang tak terlupakan.  Aku merasa terhubung dengan sejarah dan budaya bangsa,  serta mendapatkan inspirasi dan ketenangan batin.  Aku berharap suatu hari nanti bisa kembali mengunjungi Candi Borobudur dan merasakan kembali keajaibannya.
textTranslated:
After visiting Borobudur Temple, I was still amazed by its beauty and splendor.  The images of the intricate and detailed reliefs, as well as the enchanting view of the sunrise from the top of the temple, are still clearly etched in my mind.

I can still feel the strong spiritual aura around the temple.  The quiet and solemn atmosphere made me feel peaceful and calm.  I was also impressed by the complex and intricate architecture of the temple, proving the intelligence and creativity of our ancestors.

The most impressive thing was when I climbed the stairs to the top of the temple.  Every step felt sacred and led me to enlightenment.  The view from the top of the temple is truly amazing, the vast green expanse of rice fields and mountains looks so beautiful.  It feels like being in heaven on earth.

A visit to Borobudur Temple is not just a tourist attraction, but also an unforgettable spiritual experience.  I feel connected to the nation's history and culture, and gain inspiration and inner peace.  I hope one day I can return to visit Borobudur Temple and experience its magic again.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Yan On The Road
text:
歡看UNESCO的話，人生必到！婆羅浮屠上每幅石刻都不一樣，訴說著佛教故事。石刻保留良好，雕刻精細，圖案生動，叫人歎為觀止！
購買門票：參觀婆羅浮屠的門票分ground ticket和structure ticket。Ground ticket顧名思義，只在婆羅浮屠塔邊四周的地面欣賞，未能踏足建築物。而Structure ticket 則可在指定時段，於導帶領下登塔，而Structure ticket包括Ground ticket。婆羅浮屠於Covid後，每日由8:30am開始分8個時段（注意逢星期一不設登塔)，最多只供1,200人登塔，Structure ticket可以在官網訂購，但即使在較少遊客的十月份，8:30am及9:30am的Structure ticket也迅速被sold out，當地人表示大部分旅行社已壟斷早段的Structure ticket。另外，請留意一日遊旅行團包含的是那一款門票。
入園指引：我買了10:30am的Structure ticket，於網上購買門票後，參加登塔當天最好提早半小時到達入口，取籌拿實體門票，門票還包一雙拖鞋和一瓶水。於指定時間集合後便可以跟隨導遊登塔。雖然此時段又熱又曬，但導遊十分專業，講解清晰外，也會細心解答問題。婆羅浮屠很美，大約一小時的登塔之旅後，捨不得離開，但也滿足了。下塔後可以再在地面以不同角度欣賞婆羅浮屠。出入與入口位置不同，可以於公園內乘坐shuttle 前往出口。出口停車場的地方有大量紀念品店，記得議價。紀念品都大同小異，但這裡算是買紀念品的最佳地點。
textTranslated:
If you enjoy watching UNESCO, you must visit it in your life! Each stone carving on Borobudur is different and tells a Buddhist story. The stone carvings are well preserved, the carvings are fine, and the patterns are vivid, which is amazing!
Buy tickets: Tickets to visit Borobudur are divided into ground tickets and structure tickets. As the name suggests, the ground ticket only allows you to admire the ground around the Borobudur Tower and does not allow you to set foot on the building. The Structure ticket allows you to climb the tower under the guidance of a guide during designated time periods, and the Structure ticket includes the Ground ticket. After Covid, Borobudur is divided into 8 time slots starting from 8:30am every day (note that there is no tower climbing on Mondays). A maximum of 1,200 people can climb the tower. Structure tickets can be ordered on the official website, but even with fewer tourists In October, the 8:30am and 9:30am Structure tickets were quickly sold out. Locals said that most travel agencies have monopolized the early structure tickets. In addition, please pay attention to which ticket is included in the one-day tour package.
Instructions for entering the park: I bought a 10:30am Structure ticket. After purchasing the ticket online, it is best to arrive at the entrance half an hour early on the day of climbing the tower to collect physical tickets. The ticket also includes a pair of slippers and a bottle of water. After gathering at the designated time, you can follow the tour guide to climb the tower. Although it was hot and sunny at this time, the tour guide was very professional, explained clearly and answered questions carefully. Borobudur is beautiful. After about an hour of climbing the tower, I was reluctant to leave, but I was also satisfied. After getting off the tower, you can enjoy Borobudur from different angles on the ground. The entrance and exit are at different locations. You can take a shuttle in the park to the exit. There are a lot of souvenir shops at the exit parking lot, so remember to negotiate the price. The souvenirs are all the same, but this is the best place to buy souvenirs.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: irma sy
text: Setelah sekian lama akhirnya berkunjung lagi ke Candi Borobudur. Sekarang penataannya sudah lebih teratur, bersih, toilet umumnya juga bersih dan terawat. Di area Candi ada jasa foto, jadi pengunjung bisa request untuk difotoin. 1 foto cetak cukup bayar rp15.000.
textTranslated: After a long time, we finally visited Borobudur Temple again. Now the arrangement is more orderly, clean, the toilets are generally clean and well maintained. In the temple area there is a photo service, so visitors can request to have their photo taken. For 1 printed photo you only need to pay IDR 15,000.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: evy diana
text:
Terakhir mengunjungi Borobudur saat liburan bersama di sekolah, dan sekarang revisiting bareng suami dan anak2 kaget banget.. Masuk ke Borobudur kagum dengan bersihnya, dan arsitektur bangunan pendampingnya, begitu apik, dan juga lot utk pedagang UMKM yg rapi bersih dan sopan dalam menawarkan dagangannya.
Tiket masuk weekend kemaren 50k per person yg sdh include shuttle dr pintu masuk menuju area ticketing candi. Kami sempat naik shuttle tour pelataran candi yang harganya 20k/org (sudah free minuman air mineral botol) lumayan naik shuttle bisa keliling plataran candi yg indah dan sejuk. Lalu kita diturunkan di area pintu masuk candi dan disana boleh foto2 baik sendiri maupun dengan fotografer yg menawarkan jasanya. Oya utk masuk ke dalam candi, harus membeli tiket di awal saat di ticketing tadi ya, 120k/orang (for locals). Kereeen!!! Liburan kali ini sangat berkesan krn Borobudur sebagus itu.. Seperti inilah kita seharusnya memperlakukan peninggalan bersejarah yg sangat2 indah and precious (cuman ada di Indonesia lho ini) supaya kelak cucu cicit kita juga bisa menikmatinya..
textTranslated:
The last time I visited Borobudur was on holiday together at school, and now revisiting with my husband and children, I was really surprised... Entering Borobudur, I was amazed at how clean it was, and the architecture of the accompanying buildings, so neat, and also a lot for MSME traders who were neatly clean and polite in offering their wares.
Last weekend's entrance ticket was 50k per person which included a shuttle from the entrance to the temple ticketing area. We took the time to take a shuttle tour of the temple grounds which cost 20k/person (with free bottled mineral water) but by taking the shuttle we could go around the beautiful and cool grounds of the temple. Then we were dropped off at the temple entrance area and there we were allowed to take photos either alone or with photographers who offered their services. Oh yes, to enter the temple, you have to buy a ticket in advance at ticketing, 120k/person (for locals). Cool!!! This holiday is very memorable because Borobudur is that good... This is how we should treat historical heritage which is very beautiful and precious (only available in Indonesia, you know) so that in the future our great-grandchildren can also enjoy it...
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Flo Loulou
text: Très beau temple à l’architecture impressionnante . La visite se fait en petit groupe, accompagné d’un guide (en anglais)
textTranslated: Very beautiful temple with impressive architecture. The visit is done in a small group, accompanied by a guide (in English)
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: witri hasan
text:
Pelayanan di loket cepat, ramah juga, banyak penawaran promo, untuk kebersihan candi dan lingkungan nya terjaga. Kawasan nya asri.
Tp cuaca nya panas, jadi harus sedia payung/topi dan kacamata.
textTranslated:
Service at the counter is fast, friendly too, lots of promo offers, to keep the temple clean and the environment maintained. The area is beautiful.
But the weather is hot, so you have to prepare an umbrella/hat and glasses.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: VincenSurya Wibisono
text:
Candi Prambanan adalah kompleks candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia yang dibangun pada abad ke-9 Masehi. Candi ini didedikasikan untuk Trimurti, tiga dewa utama Hindu yaitu Brahma, Wisnu, dan Siwa.

Candi Prambanan merupakan;
* Warisan Budaya: Candi Prambanan adalah salah satu situs warisan dunia UNESCO, menunjukkan kekayaan budaya dan sejarah Indonesia.
* Arsitektur Unik: Desain candi yang megah dan relief-reliefnya yang indah merupakan contoh luar biasa dari seni arsitektur Jawa Kuno.
* Legenda Menarik: Banyak cerita rakyat dan legenda menarik yang terkait dengan Candi Prambanan, seperti legenda Roro Jonggrang.

Candi Prambanan tetdiri dari;
* Candi Utama: Terdiri dari tiga candi utama yang melambangkan Trimurti.
* Relief-relief: Hiasan relief yang menceritakan kisah-kisah dari kitab suci Hindu.
* Pewayangan: Pertunjukan wayang kulit yang sering diadakan di sekitar candi.

* Sejarah: Candi Prambanan dibangun pada masa Kerajaan Mataram Kuno sebagai simbol kekuatan dan keagungan.

* Legenda: Dengar cerita rakyat tentang Roro Jonggrang dan hubungannya dengan Candi.

Saat kami berkunjung pas ada pasar medang yang menyuguhkan banyak makanan, dan juga banyak acara hiburan yang digelar.

Disana kami berkrsrmpatan mrnyewa pakaian adat untuk berswa foto di sekitar prambanan.
textTranslated:
Prambanan Temple is the largest Hindu temple complex in Indonesia which was built in the 9th century AD. This temple is dedicated to the Trimurti, the three main Hindu gods namely Brahma, Vishnu, and Shiva.

Prambanan Temple is;
* Cultural Heritage: Prambanan Temple is one of UNESCO's world heritage sites, demonstrating Indonesia's rich culture and history.
* Unique Architecture: The temple's majestic design and beautiful reliefs are outstanding examples of Ancient Javanese architectural art.
* Interesting Legends: Many interesting folk tales and legends are related to Prambanan Temple, such as the legend of Roro Jonggrang.

Prambanan Temple consists of;
* Main Temple: Consists of three main temples which symbolize the Trimurti.
* Reliefs: Relief decorations that tell stories from Hindu holy books.
* Wayang: Shadow puppet performances are often held around the temple.

* History: Prambanan Temple was built during the Ancient Mataram Kingdom as a symbol of strength and majesty.

* Legend: Hear folk tales about Roro Jonggrang and his relationship with the temple.

When we visited there was a Medang market which served lots of food, and there were also lots of entertainment events being held.

There we had the opportunity to rent traditional clothes to take selfies around Prambanan.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: K. miura
text: 素晴らしいです、ジョグジャカルタ市内のホテルからGRABで30分ぐらい。チケットは高めですが、インドネシア観光地でよくあるように入り口で水をくれます。敷地は広大、時間があれば一番奥のSEWU 寺院まで行ってみるのをお勧めします。混んでいなく、夕暮れ時がすごくきれいです
textTranslated: It's wonderful, about 30 minutes by GRAB from the hotel in Yogyakarta city. Tickets are expensive, but they give you water at the entrance, as is common in Indonesian tourist spots. The grounds are vast, and if you have time, we recommend going to the SEWU temple at the very back. It's not crowded and it's very beautiful at sunset.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Alfian D
text: Tempat wisatanya sangat direkomendasikan, keindahannya, nilai sejarahnya, kebersihannya, keasriannya, just info tempat wisatanya tutup jam 5 sore . Kebetulan aku nyampe kurang lebih tinggal sejam, tapi aman masih bisa dapat foto, bagus view-nya sore hari sih.. biar dapat sunset
textTranslated: The tourist attraction is highly recommended, its beauty, historical value, cleanliness, beauty, just info the tourist attraction closes at 5 pm. Coincidentally, I arrived in about an hour, but I was safe, I could still take photos, the view was nice in the afternoon... so I could get the sunset
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Junaidatul Munawaroh
text: Candi Prambanan adalah salah satu destinasi wisata terbaik di Indonesia! Kompleks candi ini sangat megah, dengan arsitektur yang mengesankan dan cerita sejarah yang kaya. Setiap detail candi mencerminkan keindahan seni dan budaya Jawa kuno. Lokasinya juga terawat dengan baik, sangat bersih dan nyaman untuk dikunjungi. Sangat direkomendasikan untuk para pecinta sejarah, budaya, atau wisatawan yang ingin menikmati keajaiban dunia!
textTranslated: Prambanan Temple is one of the best tourist destinations in Indonesia! This temple complex is magnificent, with impressive architecture and a rich history. Every detail of the temple reflects the beauty of ancient Javanese art and culture. The location is also well maintained, very clean and comfortable to visit. Highly recommended for history, culture lovers, or tourists who want to enjoy the wonders of the world!
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: 天啓
text:
この日は、学生さんがたくさんいたのでかなり賑わっていました。

プランバナン以外に3つ見るところがありますが、
閑散としていました。

一人もいなかったところもあります。
プランバナン以外は銅像が中に入っていなかったです。

プランバナンは中心とその回りにもいくつかあり、
全部見るだけでも大変です。

ですがとても、
素晴らしかったです。パワーが感じられました。

○トイレが出口付近にあります。
プランバナンの敷地外にもありますが、
そこは2000rpとられます。

○バイクで来た場合、
駐車料金はプランバナンのチケットを買った人は5000rpです。
チケットがないともっと高い。

ガイドを付けることもできます。
敷地内は広大で、
自転車などの貸し出しも有料であります。

ルートが、決められておりプランバナンから行かなければなりません。
プランバナンを見て入口から出ることはできません。

○出口に戻る道中には、
カフェや土産物屋がものすごくたくさんあります。
一つのショッピングセンターのようです。

○チケットはklookで予約して行きました。
スマホをかざすだけで簡単です。
textTranslated:
On this day, there were many students, so it was quite lively.

There are three other places to see other than Prambanan.
It was quiet.

In some places there wasn't even a single person.
There were no bronze statues inside except for Prambanan.

There are several prambanans in the center and around it.
It's hard just to see everything.

But very,
It was wonderful. I felt the power.

○There is a restroom near the exit.
Although it is located outside Prambanan premises,
It will cost you 2000rp.

○If you come by bike,
Parking fee is 5000rp for those who bought a Prambanan ticket.
It's even more expensive without a ticket.

You can also attach a guide.
The premises are vast;
Bicycle rentals are also available for a fee.

The route is decided and you have to go from Prambanan.
You cannot leave the entrance after seeing Prambanan.

○On the way back to the exit,
There are so many cafes and souvenir shops.
It's like a shopping center.

○I reserved the ticket through Klook.
It's as easy as just holding your smartphone up.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Ihdatus Sholikhatin Nisa
text:
Salah satu tempat wisata edukasi yang ada di Jogja, selain mendapat pengetahuan sejarah juga bisa lihat view yang indah. Di area dekat candi ada pusat perbelanjaan, museum, kafe, tempat pijat, serta zoo mini yang berisi hewan rusa, burung unta dan merak.
Kalau capek jalan, bisa keliling pake skuter/kereta yang di sediakan. Harga per-orang beda-beda, sesuai item kendaraan yang di pilih. Oh ya, ternyata ada penyewaan payung juga, biar kalau panas ngga kepanasan, kalau hujan ngga kehujanan.
textTranslated:
One of the educational tourist attractions in Jogja, apart from gaining historical knowledge you can also see beautiful views. In the area near the temple there is a shopping center, museum, cafe, massage place, as well as a mini zoo containing deer, ostriches and peacocks.
If you are tired of walking, you can go around using the scooter/train provided. Prices per person vary, according to the vehicle item chosen. Oh yes, it turns out there are umbrella rentals too, so that if it's hot you don't get too hot, and if it rains you don't get caught in the rain.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Asri
text:
Salah satu destinasi wisata sejarah di Jateng, berangkat dari ibukota provinsi Jateng yaitu Semarang membutuhkan waktu ±2 jam perjalanan akses via tol dengan biaya ±130rb-an.

Dikarenakan ke sini pas tgl merah dan libur panjangnya anak sekolah, jadi ada banyak banget wisatawan yg berkunjung.

Pemesanan tiket bisa langsung melalui loket tiket yg ada di lokasi.
Pilihannya juga ada dua, tiket reguler/biasa (hanya candi prambanan) atau tiket terusan (prambanan-ratu boko).

Tapi seriusan, keliling candi prambanan saja sudah puas dan capek banget.
textTranslated:
One of the historical tourist destinations in Central Java, departing from the capital of Central Java province, namely Semarang, takes ± 2 hours to access via toll road at a cost of ± 130 thousand.

Because we came here on Red Day and it was a long school holiday, there were lots of tourists visiting.

Ticket orders can be made directly through the ticket counter at the location.
There are also two choices, regular tickets (only Prambanan temple) or season tickets (Prambanan-ratu boko).

But seriously, just walking around Prambanan Temple is already satisfying and really tiring.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Sam Purwanto (Ipunk)
text: Lokasi mudah diakses dari jogja. Selalu ramai oleh pengunjung terutama saat libur anak sekolah. Harga tiket dewasa 50 ribu, anak dibawah 10 tahun 25.000, masih tergolong murah. Sebaiknya berkunjung sore hari jam 15.00 sd 17.30 karena sangat panas saat siang hari.
textTranslated: The location is easily accessible from Jogja. Always busy with visitors, especially during school holidays. Adult tickets cost 50 thousand, children under 10 years 25,000, still relatively cheap. It's best to visit in the afternoon from 15.00 to 17.30 because it is very hot during the day.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Sulung buana
text: Tempat yang indah. Kompleks percandian dengan arsitektur yang mengesankan. Kita bisa melihat candi besar dan megah. Tour dengan siswa rasanya kurang puas, karena terbatas dengan skedul yang sudah dibuat. Mungkin saya harus kesini lagi sambil menikmati keindahan Candi ini dengan detail.
textTranslated: A beautiful place. Temple complex with impressive architecture. We can see a large and majestic temple. Tours with students feel less satisfying, because they are limited by the schedule that has been made. Maybe I should come here again and enjoy the beauty of this temple in detail.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: ditya purba
text:
Ke sini tanggal 29 Desember 2024. Tiket masuk bukan paket untuk orang dewasa 50k dan anak 25k. Dari parkiran ke loket penjualan tiket dekat. Waktu ke sini lagi ada ibadah umat Hindu di Candi Siwa, untuk candi lain masih bisa dikunjungi. Ada festival juga sepertinya di pelatarannya. Pengunjung masih boleh masuk ke candi-candinya. Makanan ga boleh dibawa masuk.

Di perjalanan ke pintu keluar ada beberapa wahana. Panahan, burung merak, rusa dan museum.
textTranslated:
Come here on December 29 2024. Entrance ticket is not a package for adults 50k and children 25k. From the parking lot to the ticket sales counter close by. When I came here there was a Hindu worship service at the Shiva Temple, other temples can still be visited. There also seems to be a festival in the grounds. Visitors are still allowed to enter the temples. Food cannot be brought in.

On the way to the exit there are several rides. Archery, peacocks, deer and museum.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Ailu
text: Jalan dari pintu masuk ke candinya lumayan jauh, untuk yang udah berumur atau bawa anak kecil kemungkinan bakal capek. Tapi ada opsi pakai golf cart kok, tapi kurang tau harganya, kemaren liat sekilas 200K/pax entah apa salah baca atau emang segitu karna keluarga ku milih untuk jalan aja.
textTranslated: The road from the entrance to the temple is quite far, for those who are older or have small children, they will probably be tired. But there is an option to use a golf cart, but I don't know the price, yesterday I glanced at 200K/pax, I don't know if I misread it or it's really that much because my family chose to just go for a ride.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Erien Miranti
text: Kalau mau dtg mending pagi jadi gk terlalu panas. Lokasinya bersih dan terawat. Kalo capek jalan kaki bisa naik shuttle car, tapi mesti bayar lagi biar bisa liat candi lain selain prambanan. Tapi kalo cuma mw liat prambanan gk perlu naik shuttle. Oya ada penyewaan payung juga 10k worth it buat disewa krna klo dtg siang panas bnget 🥹
textTranslated: If you want to come, it's better to come in the morning so it's not too hot. The location is clean and well maintained. If you are tired of walking, you can take the shuttle car, but you have to pay again so you can see other temples besides Prambanan. But if you're just looking at Prambanan, you don't need to take the shuttle. Oh yes, there is also umbrella rental, it's worth 10k to rent because it's really hot in the afternoon 🥹
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Juhong Kim
text:
외국인은 매표소 광장에서 좌측으로 들어가 40만 루피아(실내이고 에어컨 나옴)
내국인은 광장서 우측으로 감(내국인 5만 루피아)
내외국인 매표소가 다름

중앙에 프람바난외 주변에 3개의 사원 더있음
룸붕사원(Lumbung Temple)
부브라사원(Bubrah Temlpe)
세우사원(Sewu Temple)

프람바난 사원 빼고 나머지중에 세우사원이 12시로 제일 멀지만
볼만하다 관광객도 거의 없음.
나머지 룸붕사원 부브라사원은 너무 작다,
그러나 세우사원 보러 가면 다 보게된다 3개다 붙어있다.

개인적으로 프람바난사원은 관광객이 너무 많았고 세우사원이 오히려 볼만했음.

이동은 자전거,골프카트,전기바이크등이 있다.
골프카트(20만루피아)는 미리 이야기 해야 하는거 같았고
자전거랑 전기바이크는 프람바난사원 지나고 좁은 삼거리길이 나오는대
우측으로 가면 다음 사원 가는길이고 좌측으로 조금만 가면 대여점이 보였음
전체를 공원처럼 꾸며놨고 신기했던게 양궁장도 있었고 사슴우리도 있었음.
전체 사원을 다 볼려면 1시간~1.5시간쯤 걸린다.
시내서 40분정도 걸렸고 바이크 몰고 갔는대 바이크 주차장은 들어가자마자
왼쪽으로 빠져야한다. 버튼 누르면 티켓 나옴.
3시간 있었는대 영수증에 적힌 25,000 그대로 받았음.
입구에 양산을 파는 사람도 있었음.
textTranslated:
For foreigners, go to the left at the ticket office plaza and pay 400,000 rupees (indoor, air conditioned).
For Koreans, go to the right side of the square (50,000 rupees for Koreans)
The ticket office is different for domestic and foreigners.

Apart from Prambanan in the center, there are three more temples around.
Lumbung Temple
Bubrah Temlpe
Sewu Temple

Except for Prambanan Temple, Sewu Temple is the furthest at 12 o'clock.
It's worth seeing, but there are almost no tourists.
The rest of Lumbung Temple and Bubra Temple are too small.
However, if you go to see Sewoo Temple, you will see them all. All three are attached.

Personally, I thought Prambanan Temple had too many tourists and Sewu Temple was more worth seeing.

Transportation includes bicycles, golf carts, and electric bikes.
I felt like I had to discuss the golf cart (200,000 rupiah) in advance.
Bicycles and electric bikes pass Prambanan Temple and come to a narrow three-way street.
If you go to the right, you will reach the next temple, and if you go a little to the left, you will see a rental store.
The entire place was decorated like a park, and what was surprising was that there was an archery range and a deer enclosure.
It takes about 1 to 1.5 hours to see the entire temple.
It took about 40 minutes from the city and I was driving a bike, so the bike parking lot is right after entering.
You must exit to the left. Press the button and a ticket will appear.
I was there for 3 hours and received 25,000 exactly as written on the receipt.
There was also someone selling parasols at the entrance.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Ari Yuda
text: Sangat seru untuk mengunjungi candi pramba kembali. Sedikit capek buat bisa ekplor semuanya tapi Sangat puas bisa melihat mahakarya dari masa Hindu budha di Jawa. Pemandunya juga sangat menjelaskan jadi pas kunjungan bisa tahu informasi terkait candi bukan hanya lihat lihat saja.
textTranslated: It will be very exciting to visit Pramban Temple again. A little tired to be able to explore everything but very satisfied to be able to see masterpieces from the Hindu-Buddhist period in Java. The guide is also very explainable so that when you visit you can find out information related to the temple, not just look around.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Desfia Regita Ningrum
text:
Tempat wisata sejarah yang bisa buat liburan bersama keluarga. Selain bisa melihat candi dan mengetahui sejarahnya dengan bantuan tour guide atau masuk ke museum, banyak atraksi yang ditawarkan setelah puas berkeliling di kompleks candi.

Pengelolaan kompleks candi yang terawat dengan fasilitas pendukung seperti mushola dan toilet yang memadai. Parkiran untuk mobil dan motor juga cukup luas.

Tapi kalau lagi musim liburan, akses menuju candi terpantau padat sehingga untuk menghindari kemacetan better datang lebih pagi. Oiya, kalo dateng siang, mending bawa kacamata atau topi/payung agar tidak kepanasan. Dan sebaiknya pesen tiket terlebih dahulu agar tidak terlalu lama mengantri.
textTranslated:
Historical tourist attractions that can be used as a holiday with the family. Apart from being able to see the temple and find out its history with the help of a tour guide or entering the museum, there are many attractions on offer once you are satisfied touring the temple complex.

Management of a well-maintained temple complex with supporting facilities such as a prayer room and adequate toilets. Parking for cars and motorbikes is also quite spacious.

But during the holiday season, access to the temple can be seen to be busy, so to avoid traffic jams, it's better to come early. Oh yes, if you come during the day, it's better to bring glasses or a hat/umbrella so you don't get too hot. And it's best to order tickets in advance so you don't have to queue for too long.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia

Siapin fisik aja buat jalan plus turun naik candi. Oh iya tiket 50k ada sambungan juga ke Borobudur+Candi Ratu Boko, pas mau keluar banyak juga yang jual oleh-oleh. Oh iya bawa air minum soalnya di dalem mahal 10k/botol 600ml
textTranslated: Crowded, for some reason it's really full on weekdays. There are lots of school children on field trips. Magnificent building, amazed by the people who were able to make buildings as magnificent as this. Just prepare physically for the walk plus going up and down the temple. Oh yes, the 50k ticket also has a connection to Borobudur + Ratu Boko Temple, when you want to go out there are lots of people selling souvenirs. Oh yes, bring drinking water because it's expensive inside, 10k/600ml bottle

text:
Borobudur sekarang makin bagus.. sekarang klo mau naik ke candi harus ganti alas kaki dn ikutin guide.. Tiket masuk pas week day udh include sendal, minum dn guide 240k an klo gk salah itu udah untk berdua 🥰 masyaallah.

Jaman kuliah ke Borobudur blm sperti skrg yg semua serba terarah.. Minesnya, kami ngikutin tukang parkir diluar pagar 5k pdhal udah jelas ada tulisan parkir percobaan didlm kawasan akhirnya kami nyasar dn harus naik ojek keluar kawasan bayar lg 20k.. alhasil bdmood banget sm tukang parkirnya, krn mreka jg udh bohong

Dan masyaallah nya trnyta masuk Borobudurnya itu dri depan udh lumayan jauhnya, terus pintu keluar Borobudur nya lewat blkang, of course jauh banget ya Allah wong halamannya hmpir 80+ hektar CMIIW untg aja gk hilang😂😆🙃

Overall Borobudur indaaah banget masyaallah 7 keajaiban dunia yg selalu buat mikir ttg budaya, sejarah dn cerita rakyatnya♥️🔥
textTranslated:
Borobudur is getting better now... now if you want to go up to the temple you have to change your footwear and follow a guide... Entrance tickets on weekdays include sandals, drinks and a guide, 240k if I'm not mistaken, that's for two of you 🥰 mashaallah.

When I was studying at Borobudur, it wasn't like now where everyone is very focused... Unfortunately, we followed the parking attendant outside the 5k fence even though it was clear that there was a test parking sign in the area. In the end we got lost and had to take a motorbike taxi out of the area and paid another 20k. As a result, the driver was really in a bad mood. parking, because they also lied

And thank God, it turns out that entering Borobudur is quite far from the front, and the exit from Borobudur is through the back, of course it's really far, my God, the yard is almost 80+ hectares. CMIIW, luckily it didn't disappear😂😆🙃

Overall, Borobudur is really beautiful, Masha Allah, 7 wonders of the world that always make you think about culture, history and folklore♥️🔥

title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Ari Setyowati
text:
Candi Borobudur merupakan Situs Warisan Dunia.
Tempat bersejarah yang ramai dikunjungi oleh wisatawa domestik dan mancanegara.

Tiket Masuk Candi Borobudur:
1. Tiket Taman Candi, Dewasa 50.000, anak-anak 25.000
2. Tiket Naik Candi, Dewasa 125.000, anak-anak 75.000, di bawah umur 3th free. Harga tiket naik candi sudah mendapatkan fasilitas Guide, Air Minum, Tas Kantong untuk membawa sepatu/sandal kita dan Sandal Upanat (dipakai saat menaiki candi).

Durasi waktu naik candi 60 menit.

Pelayanan ramah, tempat dijaga baik dan ketat, lingkungan asri dan bersih.

Penjelasan Guide cukup jelas dalam memandu kami.

Hanya saja, jalan keluar yang begitu jauh, ini yang banyak dikeluhkan oleh para wisatawan.
Kalau dari saya pribadi tidah masalah jika diarahkan melewati pada pedagang/UMKM hanya saja perlu diperhatikan jauhnya rute.

Semoga setelah parkiran terbenahi, untuk pintu keluar tidak dibuat sejauhhhhhh saat ini.

Catatan:

Harga tiket naik candi yang dikatakan mahal, bagi saya tentulah tidak mengapa, karena apa yang kita keluarkan tidak sebanding dengan Maha Karya Warisan Leluhur yanng masih bisa kita nikmati keindahan dan sejarahnya.
textTranslated:
Borobudur Temple is a World Heritage Site.
A historical place that is often visited by domestic and foreign tourists.

Borobudur Temple Entrance Ticket:
1. Temple Park Ticket, Adults 50,000, children 25,000
2. Tickets to go up to the temple, adults 125,000, children 75,000, under 3 years old free. The ticket price to climb the temple includes guide facilities, drinking water, a bag to carry our shoes/sandals and Upanat sandals (used when climbing the temple).

The duration of time to climb the temple is 60 minutes.

Friendly service, the place is well and strictly maintained, the environment is beautiful and clean.

The guide's explanation is quite clear in guiding us.

It's just that the exit is so far away, this is what many tourists complain about.
Personally, from me there is no problem if it is directed past traders/MSMEs, you just need to pay attention to the distance of the route.

Hopefully after the parking lot is fixed, the exit will not be made as far away as it is now.

Notes:

The price of tickets to go up to the temple is said to be expensive, for me it is of course okay, because what we spend is not comparable to the masterpieces inherited from our ancestors whose beauty and history we can still enjoy.
title: Borobudur Temple

Saran saya bisa beli tiket via traveloka untuk memilih tanggal dan jam kunjungan untuk naik kecandi. Karena ada jadwal nya
textTranslated:
The largest and most amazing Buddhist temple.
It's best to visit in the morning and evening so the atmosphere is better, it's not sweltering, and the photos and videos are better. There are 2 types of tickets to buy: tickets to enter the temple grounds only, and tickets to go up to the temple. It's just that tickets to go up to the temple are limited, so it's better to book before arrival so you can get tickets to go up to the temple.
My suggestion is to buy tickets via Traveloka to choose the date and time of visit to go up to the temple. Because there is a schedule

text:
El templo es muy bonito y destaca especialmente desde la distancia, ya que su vista al llegar impresiona más que cuando paseas por su base. Sin embargo, el precio de la entrada me pareció excesivo, considerando que la visita a la base se puede realizar en poco más de 30 minutos.

Intentamos conseguir la entrada adicional para subir a la cima del templo, pero estaban agotadas cuando intentamos comprarlas. Aunque, sinceramente, también me pareció excesivo el precio de esta experiencia extra.

Lo más largo de la visita fue la salida, ya que el recorrido te obliga a pasar por una gran cantidad de puestos. Aunque no tengas intención de comprar, el trayecto resulta bastante extenso y un poco pesado.
textTranslated:
The temple is very beautiful and stands out especially from a distance, since the view upon arrival is more impressive than when you walk around its base. However, the entrance price seemed excessive to me, considering that the visit to the base can be done in just over 30 minutes.

We tried to get the extra ticket to go to the top of the temple, but they were sold out when we tried to buy them. Although, honestly, the price of this extra experience also seemed excessive to me.

The longest part of the visit was the exit, since the route forces you to pass through a large number of stalls. Even if you have no intention of buying, the journey is quite long and a bit heavy.
title: Borobudur Temple

title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Nurul Hidayati
text:
Candi ini berfungsi sebagai tempat ibadah dan upacara adat khususnya umat agama budha. Tiket masuk 50 rb, sebaiknya beli tiket terusan, tiket terusan borobudur-prambanan 80 rb, kalau borobudur-ratu boko 75 rb, harga tsb khusus orang dewasa ya, kalau anak² aku lupa tp kelihatannya cuma separuh harga, khusus untuk anak dibawah usia 10 th.

Karena tempat ibadah jadi tolong hargai beberapa aturan yang telah dibuat.

Kawasan candi ini terletak di Magelang, Jawa Tengah, berdiri sejak 775-832 M, bangun peninggalan dinasti syailendra yang telah sah sebagai warisan UNESCO. Candi Borobudur ini berbentuk bujur sangkar dengan ukuran seluruhnya mencapai 123 x 123 meter. Tingginya sekitar 42 meter yang terhitung sampai bagian atas puncak chattra. Tanpa chattra, tinggi Candi Borobudur diperkirakan 31 meter.

Bangunan Candi Borobudur terdiri dari 10 tingkatan. Enam tingkat di bawah berbentuk bujur sangkar dengan ukuran semakin atas semakin kecil. Tingkat 7-9 berdenah hampir bulat, dan tingkat paling atas berupa stupa besar. Adapun di bagian kakinya dapat ditemukan relief cerita Karmawibhangga.

Ketiga pembagian tingkatan Candi Borobudur yang pertama ada kamadhatu, lalu rupadhatu dan arupadhatu.

Kesini jam 07.00-17.00 saja ya
Kalau mau foto² tamannya sangat luas, asri, dan instagram-able juga.
textTranslated:
This temple functions as a place of worship and traditional ceremonies, especially for Buddhists. Entrance ticket is 50 thousand, it's best to buy a season ticket, the Borobudur-Prammbanan season ticket is 80 thousand, for Borobudur-ratu boko 75 thousand, that price is only for adults, I forgot about children but it looks like it's only half the price, especially for children under the age of 10 .

Because it is a place of worship, please respect some of the rules that have been made.

This temple area is located in Magelang, Central Java, founded in 775-832 AD, a legacy of the Syailendra dynasty which has been declared a UNESCO heritage site. Borobudur Temple is square in shape with a total size of 123 x 123 meters. The height is around 42 meters, counting to the top of the Chattra peak. Without chattra, the height of Borobudur Temple is estimated to be 31 meters.

The Borobudur Temple building consists of 10 levels. The six levels below are square in shape with the dimensions getting smaller as they go up. Levels 7-9 have an almost round floor plan, and the top level is a large stupa. At the foot you can find a relief of the Karmawibhangga story.

The three levels of Borobudur Temple are first divided into kamadhatu, then Rupadhatu and Arupadhatu.

Come here at 07.00-17.00 only
If you want to take photos, the garden is very large, beautiful and Instagram-able too.
title: Borobudur Temple

text:
Candi Prambanan

Sepertinya waktu kecil sudah pernah ke Candi Prambanan, tapi waktu itu tidak begitu menikmati. Beda dengan sekarang, sekarang  lebih tertarik untuk belajar tentang sejarah, terutama sejarah Indonesia.

Setelah puluhan tahun datang lagi kesini, sekarang saya lebih menikmatinya. Waktu datang kesini, mereka sedang melakukan restorasi, baik itu bangunan candinya, juga jalanan beralas batunya. Untuk sementara jalanan batunya jadi jalanan pasir, tapi semua candinya masih bisa dikunjungi seperti biasanya. Ada beberapa steger/scaffolding yang sedang dipasang mengelilingi candi untuk tujuan pemugaran, supaya bangunan candi tetap terawat dan bisa tetap berdiri dengan kokoh.

Pintu keluar dari area candi sebenarnya berbeda dengan pintu masuknya, dan kita diharuskan berjalan agak jauh untuk bisa kembali ke gerbang utama, tapi disini bisa sewa skuter listrik ataupun sepeda, dan juga ada kafe untuk yang mau istirahat sambil menikmati minuman di area yang rimbun ini. -Jul 2024
textTranslated:
Prambanan temple

It seems that when I was little I had been to Prambanan Temple, but at that time I didn't really enjoy it. It's different from now, now we are more interested in learning about history, especially Indonesian history.

After decades of coming back here, now I enjoy it more. When I came here, they were carrying out restoration work, both the temple building and the stone-paved roads. For a while the stone roads have become sand roads, but all the temples can still be visited as usual. There are several scaffolding/scaffoldings that are being installed around the temple for restoration purposes, so that the temple building is maintained and can remain standing firmly.

The exit from the temple area is actually different from the entrance, and we have to walk quite a distance to get back to the main gate, but here you can rent an electric scooter or bicycle, and there is also a cafe for those who want to rest while enjoying a drink in this lush area. -Jul 2024

name: Jesús SRM
text:
De los templos más impresionantes allá donde los haya. Tiene muchísima historia.

Nos la contó una chica local de la zona muy simpática, está estudiando inglés. Un abrazo para Aura de la pareja Española :)

Merece mucho la visita, nosotros compramos las entradas por internet, al llegar comprueban la entrada, te dan una botellita de agua y un mapa, disponible en varios idiomas. El recorrido se hace a pie. Puedes ir por libre, no es obligatorio la guiada, pero si muy recomendable si quieres conocer la historia de los templos.

Una particularidad del lugar, al ser nosotros Europeos, altos, y pelo claro, mucha gente te miran extraños, otros se acercan y te piden para una foto con ellos... una situación curiosa.

En nuestro caso hasta los del colegio, tanto profesores como alumnos, una educación y un saber estar digno de mención.
textTranslated:
One of the most impressive temples anywhere. It has a lot of history.

It was told to us by a very nice local girl from the area, she is studying English. A hug for Aura from the Spanish couple :)

It is well worth the visit, we buy the tickets online, when you arrive they check your entry, they give you a bottle of water and a map, available in several languages. The tour is done on foot. You can go on your own, the guided tour is not mandatory, but it is highly recommended if you want to know the history of the temples.

A peculiarity of the place, since we are Europeans, tall, and light-haired, many people look at you strangely, others approach you and ask you for a photo with them... a curious situation.

In our case, even those at school, both teachers and students, an education and a know-how worthy of mention.

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Koko Sensen
text:
Candi Prambanan ini adalah candi yang terdiri dari beberapa candi,seperti: •Candi Siwa,Candi Angsa,Candi  Apit,Candi dan lain lain(candi yang berada di area utama yaitu Candi Siwa,Apit dll itu merupakan candi peninggalan jaman Hindu ketika masih menduduki Nusantara yang berada di Prambanan.
•Candi yang lainnya yang berada di sekitaran Candi Siwa dll itu ada candi Bubrah,Candi Candi Lumbung,Candi Sewu yang merupakan peninggalan jaman Buddha.Terdapat candi Sewu yang menurut cerita legendha nya merupakan candi yang dibuat oleh Raden Bandung Bondowoso yang menjadi syarat permintaan Roro Jonggrang dengan membuat 1000 candi dalam satu hari satu malam.Ketika sudah selesai pembuatan candinya hanya terdapat 999 candi saja yang membuat Raden Bandung Bondowoso tidak disetujui oleh Roro Jonggrang yang membuatnya Raden Bandung Bondowoso marah.Tetapi itu yang sebenarnya hanya terdapat 249 candi saja,terdiri dari 2 patung di gerbang utama,8 candi yang mengapit(kanan kiri depan belakang masing² 2 candi),yang dipinggirnya diberi 200 candi yang mengelilingi.

•Ada juga candi yang lainnya yaitu candi lumbung yang terdapat 17 candi tetapi yang baru ditemukan 7 candi yang dulu itu fungsinya untuk menyimpan pasokan pangan dan logistik dan keperluan yang lain lain.Karena beberapa hancur dan belum diproses pemugaran dan belum ditemukan nya yang beberapa jadi baru terdapat 7 candi yang ditemukan.

•Dan ada juga candi Bubrah yang yang merupakan candi yang cerita nya katanya candi yang ditendang oleh Raden Bandung Bondowoso atas kekesalan dan kemarahan karena tidak disetujui oleh Roro Jonggrang.

Jadi candi utama yang terdapat candi Siwa,Apit,Angsa dan lain lain itu merupakan candi yang dibangun jaman peradaban Hindu dan yang di pinggir sekitaran seperti Candi Sewu,Candi Lumbung,Candi Bubrah merupakan candi yang dibangun ketika jaman peradaban Buddha di Indonesia.Semua candi yang berada di area Prambanan menghadap ke timur arah matahari terbit.

orang

tour guide nya

Jadi disini kita bisa melihat keindahan dan kemegahan dari candi candi yang berdiri sudah dari jaman masuknya Hindu-Buddha betapa kuatnya ketika jaman dulu membuat batu batu kotak yang disusun dibuat menjadi candi.
Kita bisa juga belajar sejarah disini,bagaimana cara.
menyusun(pemugaran) nya,candi itu dibangun pada jaman apa,abad berapa,tujuannya dibangun buat apa dan lain lain.sangat cocok untuk para pemula awal sejarawan,pecinta sejarah apalagi yang menjadi destinasi wisata sejarah yang cocok menjadi rekomendasi buat yang mau liburan apalagi ke Prambanan.
textTranslated:
Prambanan Temple is a temple that consists of several temples, such as: • Shiva Temple, Angsa Temple, Apit Temple, Candi and others (the temples in the main area, namely Shiva Temple, Apit etc. are temples left over from the Hindu era when they still occupied the archipelago who is in Prambanan.
•Other temples in the vicinity of Shiva Temple, etc. are Bubrah Temple, Lumbung Temple, Sewu Temple which are relics from the Buddha era. There is Sewu Temple which according to legend is a temple built by Raden Bandung Bondowoso which was a condition of Roro Jonggrang's request. by making 1000 temples in one day and one night. When the construction of the temples was finished there were only 999 temples which made Raden Bandung Bondowoso disapproved by Roro Jonggrang which made Raden Bandung Bondowoso angry. But actually there were only 249 temples, consisting of 2 statue at the main gate, 8 flanking temples (right, left, front and back of each 2 temples), which has 200 temples surrounding it.

•There are also other temples, namely the Lumbung temple, which has 17 temples, but only 7 temples were discovered, the function of which was to store food supplies and logistics and other necessities. Because some of them were destroyed and have not yet been restored and have not been found, some of them are new. There were 7 temples discovered.

•And there is also the Bubrah temple which is a temple whose story is said to be the temple that was kicked down by Raden Bandung Bondowoso out of frustration and anger because it was not approved by Roro Jonggrang.

So the main temple which contains Shiva, Apit, Angsa and others are temples built during the Hindu civilization era and those on the surrounding edges such as Sewu Temple, Lumbung Temple, Bubrah Temple are temples built during the Buddhist civilization era in Indonesia. is in the Prambanan area facing east towards the rising sun.

Other reviews:
-Make the entrance ticket price around 50k per
person
- Friendly service from the cashier,
the tour guide
-The tourist area is clean
- motorbike parking price 5k
So here we can see the beauty and splendor of the temple which has been standing since the time of Hindu-Buddhism, how powerful it was in ancient times to make square stones that were arranged to make a temple.
We can also learn history here, how to do it.
compiling (restoration), what era the temple was built in, what century, what purpose it was built for and so on. It is very suitable for beginning historians, history lovers, especially as a historical tourist destination which is suitable as a recommendation for those who want to go on holiday, especially to Prambanan.

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Vi Bao
text:
Một quần thể di tích các ngôi đền thờ các vị thần trong Hindu giáo, đặc biệt là 3 vị thần tối cao Brahma-Vishnu-Shiva. Thật sự kinh ngạc về kiến trúc bằng những tảng đá được xếp đặt lên nhau cùng với những điêu khắc tinh vi, thật hùng vỹ và tráng lệ.
Khi bước vào phía trong đền do thiếu ánh sáng nên có chút hơi ẩm và tối nhưng chỉ cần đứng yên lặng hoặc đi vòng quanh pho tượng theo chiều phải, kết hợp với cấu trúc đặc biệt của ngôi đền, một sức mạnh vô hình sẽ bao phủ nhẹ nhàng lên thân và tâm trí bỗng chợt trở nên cao xa và bình lặng, một cảm giác thật khó diễn tả mà chỉ có thể đến và tự mình cảm nhận.
Và có lẽ đó chính là bài học không lời mà các bậc cổ nhân đã dày công tạo dựng để tôn vinh về vòng tròn sự sống - bảo tồn và ẩn tàng như các Vị thần  và truyền lại cho hậu thế.
textTranslated:
A complex of temple ruins worshiping gods in Hinduism, especially the three supreme gods Brahma-Vishnu-Shiva. Truly amazed by the architecture made of rocks placed on top of each other with sophisticated sculptures, so majestic and magnificent.
When entering the temple, due to lack of light, it is a bit damp and dark, but just stand quietly or walk around the statue in the right direction, combined with the special structure of the temple, an invisible power will appear. gently covering the body and mind, suddenly becoming noble and calm, a feeling that is hard to describe but can only be come and feel for yourself.
And perhaps that is the wordless lesson that the ancients worked hard to create to honor the circle of life - to preserve and hide like Gods and pass it on to posterity.
title: Prambanan Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Fajar maulana Wardhana setiawan
text:
Kalau kamu sedang di Yogyakarta, wajib banget mampir ke Candi Prambanan! Tempat ini bukan cuma candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia, tapi juga salah satu yang paling indah di Asia Tenggara. Begitu masuk, kita langsung disambut dengan pemandangan megah candi-candi yang tinggi dan kokoh, dengan ukiran relief yang sangat detail di dindingnya. Di sini, kamu bisa melihat kisah epik Ramayana yang diukir dengan begitu rapi – benar-benar karya seni dari zaman dulu yang luar biasa!

Selain keindahan arsitekturnya, Prambanan juga punya cerita rakyat yang terkenal, yaitu legenda Roro Jonggrang. Konon, ada seorang putri cantik yang dikutuk jadi arca karena menolak lamaran seorang pangeran. Cerita ini bikin suasana di Prambanan terasa semakin magis dan penuh misteri.

lokasinya mudah dijangkau dari kota Yogyakarta, jadi cocok banget buat kamu yang mau liburan singkat tapi tetap dapat pengalaman seru. Pokoknya, Candi Prambanan adalah tempat yang wajib dikunjungi!
textTranslated:
If you are in Yogyakarta, you really must stop by Prambanan Temple! This place is not only the largest Hindu temple in Indonesia, but also one of the most beautiful in Southeast Asia. As soon as we enter, we are immediately greeted with a majestic view of tall and sturdy temples, with very detailed relief carvings on the walls. Here, you can see the epic story of the Ramayana carved so neatly – truly an extraordinary work of art from ancient times!

Apart from its architectural beauty, Prambanan also has a famous folklore, namely the legend of Roro Jonggrang. It is said that there was a beautiful princess who was cursed to become a statue because she refused a prince's proposal. This story makes the atmosphere in Prambanan feel even more magical and full of mystery.

The location is easy to reach from the city of Yogyakarta, so it's really suitable for those of you who want a short holiday but still get an exciting experience. Anyway, Prambanan Temple is a must-visit place!
title: Prambanan Temple

Caṇḍi Prambanan) adalah bangunan candi bercorak agama Hindu terbesar di Indonesia yang dibangun pada abad ke-9 Masehi. Candi yang juga disebut sebagai Rara Jonggrang ini dipersembahkan untuk Trimurti, tiga dewa utama Hindu yaitu dewa Brahma sebagai dewa pencipta, dewa Wisnu sebagai dewa pemelihara, dan dewa Siwa sebagai dewa pemusnah. Berdasarkan prasasti Siwagrha nama asli kompleks candi ini adalah Siwagrha (bahasa Sanskerta yang bermakna 'Rumah Siwa'), dan memang di garbagriha (ruang utama) candi ini bersemayam arca Siwa Mahadewa setinggi tiga meter, dikarenakan aliran Syaiwa yang mengutamakan pemujaan dewa Siwa di candi ini.
textTranslated:
Go on a historical tour with family, entrance ticket when I visited on 1 Jan 2025, adults Rp. 50,000 children max 10 years Rp. 25,000.

Caṇḍi Prambanan) is the largest Hindu temple building in Indonesia which was built in the 9th century AD. This temple, which is also known as Rara Jonggrang, is dedicated to Trimurti, the three main Hindu gods, namely Brahma as the creator god, Vishnu as the preserver god, and Shiva as the destroyer god. Based on the Siwagrha inscription, the original name of this temple complex is Siwagrha (Sanskrit which means 'House of Shiva'), and indeed in the garbagriha (main room) of this temple there is a three meter high statue of Shiva Mahadewa, because the Syaiwa sect prioritizes the worship of the god Shiva in this temple. .

Event pertunjukan juga di adakan pada hari terpilih saja atau jadwal event bisa di pantau di website maupun Instagram yaa. Tersedia juga pedagang makanan, minuman dan souvenir di jalan menuju pintu keluar. Ada toilet atau kamar mandi di beberapa letak tertentu dan juga terdapat mushola bagi beragama muslim.
textTranslated: I came to visit on a weekday to avoid excessive visitors on weekends. Weekday and weekend ticket prices will of course be different. The rules for being able to go up to the top of the temple are also only on selected days, the rest can only be done in the courtyard around the temple. Performance events are also held on selected days only or the event schedule can be monitored on the website or Instagram. The place is still beautiful, the place is flat, there are not many ups and downs, there is a special place for deer and we can feed them vegetables (special deer food is available for sale), and there is a place for playing archery (you can relax and enjoy the atmosphere by playing archery). If you visit during the day, my advice is don't forget to bring an umbrella or wear a hat so you don't get too hot from the sun. There are also food, drink and souvenir vendors on the road leading to the exit. There are toilets or bathrooms in certain locations and there is also a prayer room for Muslims.

And to this day it still amazes my eyes with the beauty and solidity of the building.

And the question at the same time that is my hope, which may come true sometime, is that dozens of small temples that were destroyed in the surrounding area, can they be restored? Hopefully.

name: Aditya Dwi Nugroho
text:
Candi Prambanan, salah satu situs warisan dunia UNESCO, adalah keajaiban arsitektur yang tak hanya memukau, tetapi juga penuh dengan cerita sejarah dan budaya. Terletak di Jawa Tengah, Indonesia, candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia ini dibangun pada abad ke-9 dan masih berdiri kokoh hingga kini, menyuguhkan panorama yang luar biasa.

Dikenal dengan keindahan relief-relief yang mendetail dan menakjubkan, Candi Prambanan terdiri dari beberapa candi utama yang didedikasikan untuk Trimurti—Dewa Brahma, Wisnu, dan Siwa. Keindahan arsitektur dan desainnya yang simetris serta tinggi menjulang memberikan kesan megah dan anggun bagi setiap pengunjung yang datang.

Saat berkunjung, Anda bisa menyusuri komplek candi yang luas dan mempelajari kisah-kisah epik yang terukir di dindingnya, seperti kisah Ramayana dan Mahabharata, yang memukau dengan detail cerita yang ditampilkan dalam relief. Pada malam hari, Anda dapat menyaksikan pertunjukan Ramayana Ballet yang spektakuler di halaman candi, sebuah pengalaman yang tak terlupakan.

Candi Prambanan juga menawarkan suasana yang tenang dan damai, cocok untuk Anda yang ingin menikmati ketenangan sambil merenung di tengah keindahan warisan budaya Indonesia. Terletak tidak jauh dari kota Yogyakarta, candi ini mudah diakses, dan menjadikannya destinasi yang sempurna bagi siapa saja yang ingin merasakan sensasi perjalanan melintasi waktu, dari masa kejayaan kerajaan Mataram Hindu-Buddha.

Jadi, jika Anda mencari pengalaman budaya yang mempesona dan penuh sejarah, Candi Prambanan adalah tempat yang wajib Anda kunjungi. Dapatkan pengalaman tak terlupakan yang menghubungkan Anda dengan masa lalu yang megah!
textTranslated:
Prambanan Temple, a UNESCO world heritage site, is an architectural wonder that is not only stunning, but also full of historical and cultural stories. Located in Central Java, Indonesia, this largest Hindu temple in Indonesia was built in the 9th century and still stands strong today, offering an extraordinary panorama.

Known for its detailed and stunning beauty of reliefs, Prambanan Temple consists of several main temples dedicated to the Trimurti—Gods Brahma, Vishnu, and Shiva. The beauty of the architecture and its symmetrical design and towering height give a majestic and elegant impression to every visitor who comes.

When visiting, you can explore the extensive temple complex and learn about the epic stories carved on the walls, such as the Ramayana and Mahabharata, which are stunning with the details of the stories displayed in the reliefs. At night, you can watch the spectacular Ramayana Ballet performance in the temple grounds, an unforgettable experience.

Prambanan Temple also offers a calm and peaceful atmosphere, suitable for those of you who want to enjoy tranquility while contemplating amidst the beauty of Indonesia's cultural heritage. Located not far from the city of Yogyakarta, this temple is easily accessible, making it the perfect destination for anyone who wants to experience the sensation of traveling through time, from the heyday of the Hindu-Buddhist Mataram kingdom.

So, if you are looking for a cultural experience that is enchanting and full of history, Prambanan Temple is a place you must visit. Get an unforgettable experience that connects you with the glorious past!

Ya no se puede visitar al amanecer.

A partir de setiembre empiezan las obras de restauración en la décima planta, no pudiéndose acceder a las últimas plantas.

Al ser patrimonio de la UNESCO te obligan a descalzarte y llevar una chanclas 🩴 de cáñamo durante todo el recorrido que luego te las puedes llevar como souvenirs. La visita al mismo la haces con un guía en grupos reducidos que te explica perfectamente curiosidades e historias del templo. Puedes explorar las 9 partes del templo ya que la décima altura se reserva para los rezos budistas. Abre a las 09:00 h las visitas al templo porque hasta esa hora se dedica al culto, aunque puedes entrar al recinto antes! El ticket cuesta 445.000 rupias! Es la atracción turística más visitada de Indonesia! 🇮🇩
textTranslated: If you visit this temple you will be visiting the largest Buddhist temple in the world. For me it was a spectacular place. Being a UNESCO heritage site, they force you to take off your shoes and wear hemp flip flops 🩴 throughout the tour, which you can then take with you as souvenirs. You visit it with a guide in small groups who perfectly explains curiosities and stories about the temple. You can explore the 9 parts of the temple as the tenth floor is reserved for Buddhist prayers. It opens at 9:00 a.m. for visits to the temple because it is dedicated to worship until that time, although you can enter the premises earlier! The ticket costs 445,000 rupees! It is the most visited tourist attraction in Indonesia! 🇮🇩

보로부두르 사원과 함께 욕야카르타 필수 관광지입니다.
욕야카르타가 교통체증이 전반적으로 심하다고 생각해서 아예 06시 30분 티켓오피스 오픈할 때 방문했습니다. 이 시간대애 시내에서 택시로 약 25분 걸렸습니다.
보로부두르 사원처럼 여기도 외국인 티켓 요금 (40만 루피아) 현지인들보다 거의 열배 이상 비싸게 받습니다.

사원 내부는 07시에 오픈합니다.
사원입구에서 사원 정면을 바라보고 역광이 아니라서 사진 찍기 좋았습니다.

우측에 므라피 화산도 멋지게 보입니다.

근처에 사원 3군데를 갈 수 있으므로 꼭 방문해보시고 특히 세우사원을 꼭 가보시라고 추천드립니다.

그리고 여기도 출구를 빙둘러서 가게 하는데 역시나 마켓 스트리트가 늘어져 있더군요 ㅎㅎㅎㅎ 사원은 참 멋진데 이런 점이 관광을 오히려 불편하게 합니다. 방콕 왕궁이나 치앙마이 유명 사원을 가도 출구 때문에 이렇게 길게 나가게 하지 않습니다.
textTranslated:
Along with Borobudur Temple, it is a must-see tourist attraction in Yogyakarta.
I thought that Yogyakarta had severe traffic congestion overall, so I visited the ticket office at 06:30 when it opened. It took about 25 minutes by taxi from downtown during this time.
Like Borobudur Temple, tickets here for foreigners (400,000 rupees) are almost ten times more expensive than for locals.

The inside of the temple opens at 07:00.
It was good to take pictures from the entrance of the temple, looking at the front of the temple and not being backlit.

Merapi volcano is also visible on the right.

There are three temples nearby, so I recommend you to visit them, especially Sew Temple.

And here too, you have to go around the exit, but as expected, Market Street is stretched out haha. The temple is really cool, but this makes sightseeing rather inconvenient. Even if you go to the Grand Palace in Bangkok or a famous temple in Chiang Mai, the exits don't make you have to go this long.

text:
大約三個世紀以來，馬塔蘭位於默拉皮火山南坡普羅戈河谷的中心地帶，成為爪哇印度教和佛教文化的中心。這段時期見證了許多宗教建築，包括世界遺產婆羅浮屠和普蘭巴南。

婆羅浮屠為大乘佛教佛寺，建於8-9世紀，至今一千多年，曾掩埋於火山灰中長達數百年，地表叢林叢生，直到1814年由英國人發現而重現於世。婆羅浮屠為現今世界最大的佛教建築，地上9層，下面6層為欲界和色界，富有各式各樣的浮雕，其將佛教書籍故事刻畫出來，長達3公里，講述凡夫眾生，從宮廷生活到村子平民。上面3層為無色界，為從輪迴中解脫、不再執著於世俗的神的世界，因此無任何世俗的雕刻，有72個鐘形小佛塔圍繞中間大佛塔。

門票本國人台幣240元，外國人台幣900元，以當地物價來說並不便宜，但看在古蹟修復還需要大量人力、金錢的份上，還是有錢出錢吧。
textTranslated:
For about three centuries, Matalan, located in the heart of the Progo Valley on the southern slopes of Mount Merapi, became the center of Javanese Hindu and Buddhist culture. This period witnessed many religious buildings, including the World Heritage Sites of Borobudur and Prambanan.

Borobudur is a Mahayana Buddhist temple built in the 8th and 9th centuries for more than a thousand years. It was buried in volcanic ash for hundreds of years and covered with jungles on the surface until it was discovered by the British in 1814 and reappeared in the world. Borobudur is the largest Buddhist building in the world today. It has 9 floors above ground and 6 floors below for the realm of desire and sex. It is rich in various reliefs. It depicts stories from Buddhist books and is 3 kilometers long. It tells the stories of ordinary beings from Palace life to the common people in the village. The upper three floors are the formless realm, which is the world of gods who are freed from reincarnation and no longer attached to the secular world. Therefore, there are no secular sculptures. There are 72 small bell-shaped pagodas surrounding the large pagoda in the middle.

Tickets cost NT$240 for locals and NT$900 for foreigners, which is not cheap according to local prices, but considering that the restoration of historical sites requires a lot of manpower and money, it is better to pay if you have the money.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Nadya Safira
text:
We ready and don't Judge !
Opini saya pribadi, datang kesini kaget karena sudah berubah total. Bener-bener tempat yg sudah di monetisasi. Dua tahun lalu kesini masih normal-normal saja, hari ini kami sekeluarga datang benar-benar kecewa dengan manajemen dari Candi Borobudur.
1. Saat masuk ke parkiran sudah disuguhkan dg pasar oleh-oleh, yg posisinya mau ke pintu masuk jauh sekali. Saran saya kalau mau parkir di blok A1 yg lumayan dekat walaupun sama saja akan diputar-putar. Harus berjalan sejauh 1 km lebih untuk ke loket tiket masuk, diputar-putar di tempat pasar oleh-oleh. Padahal dulu tidak seperti ini manajemennya.

2. Kalau ke candi Borobudur jangan bawa lansia, karena sangat menyulitkan walaupun disediakan kursi roda tapi pasti BAYAR. Tetapi ke tempat penyewaan sangat jauh juga, pokoknya dr parkiran ke tempat masuk sangat sangat jauh. Tidak masuk akal

3.  Dulu saat 2 tahun lalu kesana candi hanya bisa di pelataran untuk naik ke atas ditutup, tapi saat ini bisa ke naik ke atas dg harga 120 RB pertiket. Saya bukan tidak punya uang, tp jujur saya tidak setuju, sangat terlihat di bisniskan. Kalau dulu ditutup alasan karena menjaga agar tidak rusak, tp kalau begini saya rasa itu hanya omong kosong saja.

4. Disediakan shuttle bus sampai ke pintu masuk ke arah candi tapi di bis nya di tulis (GRATIS selama masa uji) maksudnya kalau sudah berjalan mau berbayar lagi??

5. Saat sampai dipintu masuk naik glf car/shuttle bus/ andong  berbayar 20 RB /orang . 2 tahun lalu saya berbayar tetapi hanya sekali saat berangkat sampai depan candi, tapi sekarang bahkan pulang pun masih ditawari dan berbayar 20 RB lagi. Kenapa manajemen nya tidak sekalian saja pulang pergi 20 RB??
Dulu pintu keluarnya sangat dekat JD ga perlu naik shuttle bis lagi . Dan langsung masuk pasar oleh-oleh.

5. Kami keburu lelah belum ke loket tiket sudah lelah harus berjalan kaki sejauh itu dputer-puter dipasar oleh-oleh, masuk masih harus berbayar dan naik shuttle bus muter-muter jauuh. Sudah kesel duluan!

6. Dampaknya apa?? Dampaknya ke pedagang, karena siapa yg mau beli muter-muter pasar oleh-oleh kalau lokasinya sejauh ituu. Kami jadi malas karena sudah lelah mau cepat segera pulang!

Tolong siapapun yg membuat peraturan baru kepada Candi Borobudur saya rasa akan mematikan minat masyarakat untuk datang kesana. Kasian para pedagang pasar oleh-oleh. Dan ini cukup terakhir kalinya kami ke sana. Mau orang berduit pun akan kapok kalo kesana karena CAPEK , JAUH, MUTER-MUTER dan TIDAK RAMAH LANSIA. Duh kapok deh 🙏
textTranslated:
We are ready and don't judge!
My personal opinion, when I came here I was shocked because it had changed completely. It's really a place that has been monetized. Two years ago it was still normal here, today our family came and were really disappointed with the management of Borobudur Temple.
1. When you enter the parking lot, you will be presented with a souvenir market, which is located very far from the entrance. My advice is if you want to park in block A1 which is quite close, even though it's the same, it will be turned around. You have to walk more than 1 km to get to the entrance ticket counter, go around the souvenir market. Even though management wasn't like this before.

2. If you go to Borobudur temple, don't bring the elderly, because it's very difficult even though wheelchairs are provided but you will definitely PAY. But it's very far to the rental place, basically from the parking lot to the entrance is very, very far. Does not make sense

3. In the past 2 years ago, you could only go to the temple in the courtyard to go up to the top which was closed, but now you can go up to the top for 120 RB per ticket. I don't have no money, but honestly I don't agree, it really looks like it's in business. In the past the reason it was closed was to ensure it didn't get damaged, but if it's like this I think it's just nonsense.

4. There is a shuttle bus provided to the entrance to the temple but on the bus it is written (FREE during the test period) meaning that when it is running, do you have to pay again??

5. When you arrive at the entrance, take a glf car/shuttle bus/cart for a fee of 20 RB/person. 2 years ago I paid but only once when leaving to the front of the temple, but now even when I go home I am still offered and I pay another 20 thousand. Why doesn't the management just make a 20K round trip round trip??
Previously, the exit was very close. JD didn't need to take the shuttle bus anymore. And immediately entered the souvenir market.

5. We were tired before we got to the ticket counter, we were tired of having to walk that far to the souvenir market, we still had to pay to enter and take a shuttle bus all the way around. I'm already annoyed!

6. What impact? The impact is on traders, because who wants to shop around at the souvenir market if the location is that far? We became lazy because we were tired and wanted to go home quickly!

Please, whoever makes new regulations for Borobudur Temple, I think will kill people's interest in coming there. Poor souvenir market traders. And this was pretty much the last time we went there. Even people with money will give up on going there because it's tiring, long distance, MUTING and NOT ELDERLY FRIENDLY. Oh, I'm fed up 🙏
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Royan sapta
text:
Seiring bertambahnya usia tidak mengurangai keindahan salah satu candi budha terbesar yang terletak di magelang. Saya pertama kali berkunjung pada tahun 2011 dan tepatnya pada 25 April ini kesempatan kedua untuk berkunjung kembali.

Dari jogja kurang lebih menempuh jarak 1 jam perjalanan. Sampai lokasi pukul 09.40 untuk yang membawa kendaraan R2 disediakan pakir di area luar candi IDR5000.
Kita bisa beli tiket via online IDR120.000 untuk naik ke puncak candi. dan IDR50.000 tiket untuk di pelataran saja.

Sampai di tempat jam 9.40 ternyata sudah ketinggalan rombongan tour jam 9.30, harus nunggu rombongan berikutnya di 10.30.
Barcode tiket ditukar dengan tiket gelang di loket.  Kemudian dikasih kartu nomor tour guide.

Setelah itu kita di arahkan ke penukaran tiket  untuk pengambilan upanat (sandal khusus untuk naik candi, bisa dibawa pulang sandalnya) + dapat air mineral dan juga dapat sejenis tas selempang. Lalu menunggu lagi di ruang tunggu.

Setelah itu kita diarahkan untuk mengikuti rombongan sesuai dengan nomor tour guide. Tour guide mengarahkan rombongan dari pelataran sampai naik ke puncak candi, penjelasan tour guide cukup jelas (cerita/sejarah keunikan candi borobudur). kita juga diberi kesempatan untuk beristirahat dan berfoto-foto di area candi.

Waktu tour di area candi 1 jam dan harus segera turun ke bawah. karna harus bergantian dengan rombongan tour yang lainnya, untuk kelestarian candi agar tetap terjaga. Sampai di bawah bebas dari tour guide (kalo sanggup sampe sore keliling area pelataran candi, ya silahkan.. wkwk..)

Untuk keluar dari area candi selain jalan kaki, bisa juga naik delman seharga IDR100.000 atau naik golf car tayo seharga IDR20.000/orang.
textTranslated:
As age increases, the beauty of one of the largest Buddhist temples located in Magelang does not diminish. I first visited in 2011 and on April 25 to be precise, this was my second opportunity to visit again.

From Jogja it is approximately 1 hour's journey. Arriving at the location at 09.40 for those bringing R2 vehicles, parking is provided in the area outside the temple, IDR 5,000.
We can buy tickets online for IDR 120,000 to climb to the top of the temple. and IDR 50,000 tickets for the grounds only.

Arriving at the place at 9.40 it turned out that we had already missed the tour group at 9.30, had to wait for the next group at 10.30.
The ticket barcode is exchanged for a wristband ticket at the counter.  Then you are given a tour guide number card.

After that we were directed to exchange tickets to pick up upanat (special sandals for climbing the temple, you can take the sandals home) + get mineral water and also get a kind of sling bag. Then wait again in the waiting room.

After that we were directed to follow the group according to the tour guide number. The tour guide directs the group from the courtyard to the top of the temple, the tour guide's explanation is quite clear (the story/history of the uniqueness of the Borobudur temple). We are also given the opportunity to rest and take photos in the temple area.

The tour time in the temple area is 1 hour and you have to go downstairs immediately. because you have to take turns with other tour groups, to ensure the preservation of the temple. Arriving at the bottom, you are free from a tour guide (if you are able to go around the temple grounds until the afternoon, then please... hahaha...)

To leave the temple area, apart from walking, you can also take a carriage for IDR 100,000 or take a Tayo golf car for IDR 20,000/person.
title: Borobudur Temple
