name: Nurhidayat
text:
Bintang 3 dulu, karena walaupun sudah kearah penataan yg jauh lebih baik, tapi masih banyak kesemrawutan dgn sistem baru ini
1. Entrance n exit gate masih banyak error n gate kedikitan klo misal masuk kendaraan berbarengan. Malah pas exit palang pintu jd manual krn katanya error. Jadi bayar parkir manual jg ke petugas dan harga nya ga bisa dipertanggung jawabkan bemer salah nya atau sebagian masuk kantong
2. Kurang signage yg jelas dan permanen mulai dari parkiran seharusnya ada penamaan misal parkir timur, barat dll jd pas keluar ga sulit cari dimana kita parkir. Mkn dikasi juga map lay out parkir. Lalu dr parkiran menuju entrance ada tp sedikit sekali, kecil dan hanya tempelan dr kertas. Knp ga dibikin yg lebih permanen, jelas dan modern dan ada map lay out di sudut2 ruangan. Begitu juga pas balik cari parkir dimana, saking luasnya bikin amat sangat bingung
3. Saya rasa petugas masih kurang melayani dan kurang respek atau ramah kepada pengunjung. Harus lebih profesional krn ini tempat wisata kelas dunia dan dilihat orang dr manapun. Malah pas baru mau naik candi naik ada petugas scan QR code gelang yg menggerutu atau berkata tidak pantas dengan bahasa Jawa ke seorang turis asing hanya karena si turis bingung pas mau naik candi
4. Harus tingkatkan masalah queu line shuttle waktu terutama ketika balik dari candi. Tidak ada queu line atau satupun petugas yg mengatur. Ketika shuttle datang belum berhenti pun pengunjung langsung lari2 berlomba utk naik tanpa peduli keselamatan. Yg datang duluan ada yg sampe nunggu 4-5 kali kelewat shuttle krn kedorong2 pengunjung yg baru datang. Ga ada petugas satupun yg mengatur. Malah sy sempat emosi sekali ketika menunggu lama, ada shuttle yg malah mau berhenti ketika di stop pengunjung yg sedang duduk2 di resto. Padahal yg sudah lama menunggu ada dalam antrian. Ini yang paling berantakan sih. Malu ada wisatawan asing yg ikut antrian lihat tingkah laku pengunjung ga pake antri, petugas yg tidak ada profrional dan bisa dibilang kampungan utk selevel borobudur. Mkn dia lihat seperti itulah orang Indonesia dengan budaya tanpa antrinya. Akhirnya sang wisatawan saya lihat memilih jalan kaki utk balik.

Over all yg diluar itu dengan sistem guide dan pembatasan orang yg naik sampe ke atas sudah sangat bagus. Mudah2an hal2 diatas dapat ditingkatkan lagi. Candi nya sudah kelas dunia, tapi juga harus didukung profesionalitas dan mental petugas dan masyarakat yang kelas dunia juga
textTranslated:
3 stars first, because even though there is a much better arrangement, there is still a lot of chaos with this new system
1. Entrance and exit gates still have lots of errors and there are too few gates if, for example, you enter a vehicle at the same time. In fact, when I exit, the door latch becomes manual because it says there is an error. So you also pay for manual parking to the officer and the price cannot be accounted for if it is wrong or some of it ends up in your pocket
2. There is a lack of clear and permanent signage starting from the parking lot, there should be names, for example east, west parking, etc. so that when we leave it is not difficult to find where we parked. Also provide a parking layout map. Then from the parking lot to the entrance there are some but very few, small and just sticks of paper. Why not make something more permanent, clear and modern and have map layouts in the corners of the room. Likewise, when you come back, look for where to park, it's so wide it makes you very, very confused
3. I think the officers are still not serving enough and are not respectful or friendly towards visitors. You have to be more professional because this is a world class tourist spot and people can see it from everywhere. In fact, when I was just about to go up the temple, there was an officer who scanned the QR code of the bracelet who grumbled or said something inappropriate in Javanese to a foreign tourist just because the tourist was confused when he wanted to go up the temple.
4. Must improve the queue line shuttle time problem, especially when returning from the temple. There is no queue line or a single officer controlling it. When the shuttle arrived, the visitors didn't stop and immediately ran and raced to get on without caring about safety. There were those who came first who waited 4-5 times for the shuttle because they were pushed by visitors who had just arrived. There isn't a single officer to regulate it. In fact, I got very emotional when I waited a long time, there was a shuttle that actually stopped when it stopped visitors who were sitting in the restaurant. Even though those who have been waiting for a long time are in the queue. This is the messiest one. It's embarrassing that there are foreign tourists who join the queue seeing the behavior of visitors who don't use queues, the officers who are not professional and can be said to be plebeian for the level of Borobudur. So that's what he saw as Indonesians with their no-queue culture. Finally, I saw the tourist chose to walk back.

Over all, the outside with the guide system and restrictions on people going up to the top is very good. Hopefully the things above can be improved again. The temple is already world class, but it must also be supported by the world class professionalism and mentality of the staff and community too
title: Borobudur Temple

text:
Schöner geschichtsträchtiger Ort. Uns hat die Doppelbehandlung zwischen indonesischen Touristen und internationalen Touristen allerdings nicht so gut gefallen. Als internationaler Tourist muss man an einer Führung teilnehmen. Man hat nur ein Zeitfenster von 1:30 Stunden. Und faktisch dauert es schon alleine 45 Minuten bis der Guide am eigentlichen Tempel ankommt und man in der Gruppe die Treppen aufsteigen kann. Finde wenn man so viel Geld für den Eintritt verlangt sollte man etwas mehr Zeit auf dem Tempel verbingen dürfen.

Auch ist die Organisation nicht die beste. Wir waren etwas vor unserem Zeitfenster da und haben den unteren Tempel besichtigt bevor unsere Führung los ging. Wir mussten einmal um die ganze Anlage herum um wieder zum Startpunkt zurück zu kommen.
textTranslated:
Beautiful place steeped in history. However, we didn't like the double treatment between Indonesian tourists and international tourists. As an international tourist you have to take a guided tour. You only have a time window of 1:30 hours. And in fact it takes 45 minutes for the guide to arrive at the actual temple and for the group to be able to climb the stairs. I think if you charge so much money for entry you should be allowed to spend a little more time at the temple.

The organization is also not the best. We got there a little before our time slot and visited the lower temple before our tour started. We had to go around the entire complex to get back to the starting point.

name: Andreas (Birnboim)
text: Gut organisierter Eintrittsprozess. Wir hatten einen englischsprachigen Führer, allerdings mit sehr schwer zu verstehendem Akzent. Die Geschichte dieses mehr als 2000Jahre alten Tempels bzw. der gesamten Tempelanlage ist sehr interessant, aber auch etwas komplex. Von daher ist ein Führer ratsam, um auch die ganzen baulichen Besonderheiten und Reliefs/Statuen zu verstehen. Wir waren uns uneins, ob uns nun das hinduistische Borobudur oder aber dieser buddhistische Anlage mehr beeindruckt hat. Auf jeden Fall sollte man dieses Weltkulturerbe besichtigen, wenn man in der Nähe ist!!
textTranslated: Well organized entry process. We had an English speaking guide, although with a very difficult to understand accent. The history of this more than 2000 year old temple or the entire temple complex is very interesting, but also somewhat complex. A guide is therefore advisable in order to understand all the structural features and reliefs/statues. We couldn't agree whether we were more impressed by the Hindu Borobudur or this Buddhist complex. You should definitely visit this world heritage site if you are nearby!!
title: Prambanan Temple

text:
Een mooie tempel, waar je goed kunt zien wat er door de tsunami en de aardbeving is gebeurd. Er zijn nog veel herstelwerkzaamheden te doen, maar ondanks dat is er nog veel te zien van de tempel. Het mooie is dat je op de tempel kunt klimmen naar de eerste etage en je vandaaruit rondom kunt lopen en meerdere kamers kunt bekijken

name: JIE-CHAO YOU
text:
大約三個世紀以來，馬塔蘭位於默拉皮火山南坡普羅戈河谷的中心地帶，成為爪哇印度教和佛教文化的中心。這段時期見證了許多宗教建築，包括世界遺產婆羅浮屠和普蘭巴南。

普蘭巴南建於850年，為僅次於吳哥窟第二大的印度教寺廟。共有240座廟塔，其中最大的六座分別供奉印度教的三位主神：濕婆（毀滅之神）、毗濕奴（秩序之神）和梵天（創造之神）及他們的座騎：牛、老鷹、天鵝。目前已修復22座廟塔，其餘218座處於倒塌狀態，以1年修復1座廟塔，完全修復完成尚需218年。

門票本國人台幣240元，外國人台幣900元，以當地物價來說並不便宜，但看在古蹟修復還需要大量人力、金錢的份上，還是有錢出錢吧。
textTranslated:
For about three centuries, Matalan, located in the heart of the Progo Valley on the southern slopes of Mount Merapi, became the center of Javanese Hindu and Buddhist culture. This period witnessed many religious buildings, including the World Heritage Sites of Borobudur and Prambanan.

Prambanan was built in 850 and is the second largest Hindu temple after Angkor Wat. There are a total of 240 temple towers, the six largest of which are dedicated to the three main gods of Hinduism: Shiva (the god of destruction), Vishnu (the god of order) and Brahma (the god of creation) and their mounts: cows, Eagle, swan. At present, 22 temple towers have been repaired, and the remaining 218 are in a collapsed state. It takes one year to repair one temple tower, and it will take 218 years to complete the complete restoration.

Tickets cost NT$240 for locals and NT$900 for foreigners, which is not cheap based on local prices. However, since the restoration of historical sites requires a lot of manpower and money, it is better to pay if you have the money.
title: Prambanan Temple

name: nao hatto
text: 思った以上に大きく迫力がありました。アンコールワットも観てきていますが違った良さがありこれはこれでいいです。一見の価値がある世界遺産です。アドバイスとしては午前中の訪問をオススメ致します。私は午後に訪問したのですが、プランバナンの正面(看板がある位置)からからだと逆光になり遺跡の写真が映えません…黒くなって微妙な写真となってしまいました。また結構敷地が広くて他の遺跡も徒歩で回ると2時間強くらい掛かりますので熱中症対策は万全にした方が良いです。敷地内に売店が見当たらなかったです(私が気づかなかっただけかもですが)。ちなみに自転車とか電動ボードのレンタルもありましたが貸し出し時間が1時間との事だったのでゆっくり観たい私は徒歩にしました。余談ですが市内からの移動手段はGRUB carでトゥグ駅から40分くらい、110,000ルピアでした。1,000円くらいかな。
textTranslated: It was bigger and more powerful than I expected. I have also seen Angkor Wat, but it has a different quality to it, so this one is fine. It is a world heritage site worth seeing. My advice is to visit in the morning. I visited in the afternoon, but if you were looking from the front of Prambanan (where the signboard is), the backlight would make it difficult to take photos of the ruins...the photos turned out black and looked a little weird. Also, the site is quite large and it will take about 2 hours to visit the other ruins on foot, so it is best to take precautions against heatstroke. I couldn't find any shops on the premises (maybe I just didn't notice). By the way, there were bicycles and electric boards available for rent, but the rental time was only for one hour, so I decided to walk because I wanted to watch the show at a leisurely pace. As a side note, the means of transportation from the city was by GRUB car, which took about 40 minutes from Tugu Station and cost 110,000 Rupiah. Probably around 1,000 yen.

name: SY H
text:
욕야카르타 필수 관광지입니다만 욕야카르타 시내에서 멀어서 가는 길이 그리 만만치 않습니다.

저는 욕야카르타 역에서 그랩 택시를 잡았으나 정말 많은 인도네시아 현지분들도 그랩을 기다려서 정말 혼잡 그자체 였습니다. 그랩 부른지 40분만에 겨우 탔고 (첫번째 그랩기사가 취소를 유도하려고 콜 승인 후 20분이나 아예 이동하지 않았습니다)
1시간 40분 걸려서 Borobudur Ticket Office & Entry Point (여기가 보도부두르 사원 입구입니다. 구글지도에서 찾을 수 있습니다)에 도착했습니다. (그랩 요금 약 250,000루피아)
각 시간마다 소규모로 그룹투어 진행했고 왜 새벽에 주로 가시는지 13시 30분에 진행하는 투어를 참여해서 알게됐습니다. 정말 덥습니다. 우산이든 양산이든 꼭 챙겨가세요.
그래도 힘들게 간 보람이 있습니다. 특히 꼭대기 층에 올라가면 아주 멋진 풍경이 있어서 너무 좋았습니다.

그리고 다른 후기들에서도 많이 지적됐듯이 출구가 아주 긴 상점들이 똬리를 치듯이 포진해있어서 나가는데 한참 걸립니다. 저는 빠른 걸음으로 15분 걸렸는데 보통 걸음으로 20분 걸릴듯합니다. 질릴듯한 상점가가 끝나는 문이 exit post 6이므로 기사님 부를 때 거기서 만나자고 하시면 됩니다.

사원에 갔던 그랩 기사님이 오는 편에 그랩 요금으로 기다렸다가 가주시겠다고 해서 현금 (25만 루피아)과 함께 팁도 더 챙겨드렸습니다. 역시나 사원에서 시내까지 1시간 45분 걸렸습니다.
textTranslated:
It is a must-see tourist destination in Yogyakarta, but it is far from downtown Yogyakarta, so the road to get there is not that easy.

I caught a Grab taxi at Yogyakarta Station, but it was really crowded because there were so many Indonesian locals waiting for Grab. I barely got on board 40 minutes after calling Grab (the first Grab driver didn't move at all for 20 minutes after approving the call in an attempt to get me to cancel).
It took 1 hour and 40 minutes to arrive at Borobudur Ticket Office & Entry Point (this is the entrance to Borobudur Temple. You can find it on Google Maps). (Grab fee is approximately 250,000 rupiah)
Small group tours were conducted at each hour, and I found out why they usually go early in the morning by participating in the tour held at 13:30. It's really hot. Be sure to take an umbrella or parasol with you.
Still, the hard work is worth it. It was especially nice to go up to the top floor because there was a very nice view.

And as pointed out in many other reviews, there are stores with very long exits lined up like a coil, so it takes a long time to get out. It took me 15 minutes at a brisk pace, but I think it would take 20 minutes at a normal pace. The door at the end of the boring shopping street is exit post 6, so when you call the driver, you can ask him to meet you there.

The Grab driver who went to the temple said he would wait and pay the Grab fare on the way back, so I gave him cash (250,000 rupiah) and an additional tip. As expected, it took 1 hour and 45 minutes from the temple to the city.
title: Borobudur Temple

name: Jacopo Burzacchi
text:
COMPRATE I BIGLIETTI PRIMA !!!
N.b. ci sono due tipi di biglietti: quelli "ground", che permettono di entrare nell'area del tempio ma senza salirci e quelli "completi" che includono la guida è vi danno vedere il tempo da sopra.
Comprate, se possibile, i secondi perché è meraviglioso salire e vederlo e fate conto che dei biglietti "completi" ne vendono pochissimi, quindi affrettatevi!

Per visitarlo serve almeno un'ora e mezza / due, perché il parco è grande ed il tempio anche.

Secondo me è il tempio più bello di tutta l'Indonesia (non me ne voglia Prambanan, che è meraviglioso) anche perché risale all'800, mentre di solito i templi indonesiani non sono un granché, risultando spesso è volentieri trappole per turisti.
textTranslated:
BUY TICKETS EARLY!!!
N.b. there are two types of tickets: the "ground" ones, which allow you to enter the temple area but without going up and the "complete" ones which include the guide and give you a view of the weather from above.
If possible, buy the second ones because it is wonderful to go up and see it and keep in mind that very few "complete" tickets are sold, so hurry!

To visit it you need at least an hour and a half / two, because the park is large and so is the temple.

In my opinion it is the most beautiful temple in all of Indonesia (I don't mind Prambanan, which is wonderful) also because it dates back to the 19th century, while Indonesian temples are usually not that great, often resulting in tourist traps.
title: Borobudur Temple

setelah itu dr pintu keluar candi menuju parkiran elf kita diberi fasilitas bis tayo gratis.

textTranslated:
Approximately 1 hour drive from the city of Yogyakarta.
Arrive at 8 am at Borobudur Temple. HTM 50 thousand for local tourists only in the temple grounds and can buy directly on the spot.
For tickets that can go up to Borobudur Temple, it is recommended to buy well in advance because they are limited.
It is forbidden to bring food from outside. If you have already brought it, you can leave it at the entrance guard post and can pick it up at the exit guard post.
From the entrance, the ticket to the temple is quite far, it is recommended to take the Tayo bus per person, pay 18 thousand, get 1 bottle of mineral water free.
You have to be strong to walk, the point is because after we arrive in front of Borobudur Temple to get to the exit we have to walk quite a long way, but the road is shady because there are lots of big trees.
After that, from the temple exit to the Elf parking lot, we were given free Tayo bus facilities.
This parking lot is new, now stands have been neatly arranged for souvenir vendors and food vendor stands.
Overall, enjoying the Borobudur Temple tour was very enjoyable.
Knowing history, preserving and protecting it so that it will continue to exist for our children and grandchildren tomorrow.
Thanks Borobudur Temple

Not suitable for the elderly, because you have to walk from the parking lot and if you want to go up to the temple the stairs are quite steep.
If you bring children, you must pay attention because on each side of the temple there are stairs to go down and up.

text:
Pada saat di Yogyakarta saya memang sudah merencanakan pergi ke Candi Prambanan karena memang pertama kalinya saya ke Jogjakarta. Pertama kalinya ke Candi Prambanan saya takjub dengan keindahan dan kemegahan Candi tersebut.
Saat di Candi Prambanan saya sempat menggambar dengan sepuh gambar yang ada di lingkungan Candi Prambanan, saya sangat bahagia dan bangga karena dapat bertemu dan belajar menggambar secara langsung dengan beliau.

Kemegahan Candi Prambanan memiliki ukuran yang sangat besar dan desain yang sangat kompleks, membuatnya menjadi salah satu candi Hindu terbesar di Asia Tenggara.

Relief yang Indah di Candi Prambanan sangat detail dan menceritakan kisah-kisah yang menarik.

Suasana Spiritual yang tenang dan damai di sekitar candi membuat pengunjung merasa lebih dekat dengan alam dan spiritualitas.
textTranslated:
When I was in Yogyakarta, I had planned to go to Prambanan Temple because it was my first time going to Jogjakarta. The first time I went to Prambanan Temple, I was amazed by the beauty and splendor of the temple.
When I was at Prambanan Temple, I had the opportunity to draw with a picture elder in the Prambanan Temple environment. I was very happy and proud because I could meet and learn to draw directly with him.

The splendor of Prambanan Temple has a very large size and a very complex design, making it one of the largest Hindu temples in Southeast Asia.

The beautiful reliefs at Prambanan Temple are very detailed and tell interesting stories.

The calm and peaceful spiritual atmosphere around the temple makes visitors feel closer to nature and spirituality.

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Donggeon King
text:
인터넷을통해 미리 가이드까지 예약하여 다녀 온 보로부두르사원 가이드분께서 영어를 잘 하셔 너무 좋았고 이해도 쏙쏙되었습니다. 생각보다 시간이 많이부족하여 가이딩시간까지 약 한시간 반 - 두 시간 정도 있다가 나와 너무 아쉬웠습니다.

9세기 초에 세운 석조건축물 사원으로 세계에서 가장 큰 불교 사원으로 알려져 있습니다. 셀렌드라 왕조에 의해 건설되었으며, 약 750년경에 시작되어 850년경에 완공된 것으로 추정된다하며 수백 년 동안 숨어있다 19세기 초 네덜란드 식민지 시대에 재발견된 거대한 사원입니다.

옥상부는 인원제한이있어 꼭 인터넷으로 미리 예약하셔가시는걸 추천드리며 방문할 가치가 있습니다. 또한 친구와 오토바이로 다녀온 길도 무척이나 멋있었습니다. 약 한 시간 - 한 시간 20분 정도 소요되었으며 운전자 동승자 모두 엄청난 체력이 필요합니다. 다소 비싼 입장료가 아쉬웠으며 특히나 나가는 길 또.. 또!! 20여분간의 큰시장이 나와 맘편히 나갈 수 없는점이 좀..
textTranslated:
I booked a guide in advance online and went to Borobudur Temple. The guide spoke good English, which was great and easy to understand. I was very disappointed that I left after about an hour and a half to two hours until the guiding time, as I had less time than I thought.

This stone-built temple was built in the early 9th century and is known as the largest Buddhist temple in the world. Built by the Selendra Dynasty, it is believed to have begun around 750 and was completed around 850. It is a huge temple that was hidden for hundreds of years and rediscovered during the Dutch colonial period in the early 19th century.

The number of people on the rooftop is limited, so we recommend that you make a reservation online in advance. It is worth a visit. Also, the road I took on a motorcycle with my friend was very cool. It took about an hour - an hour and 20 minutes and requires a lot of stamina from both the driver and passengers. It was disappointing that the entrance fee was somewhat expensive, especially on the way out.. again!! There's a big market that lasts about 20 minutes, so I can't leave comfortably...
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Lirta Pinem
text:
Kalau mau naik keatas, jgn lupa beli tiket online via traveloka, cek bbrp hr sebelumnya, kl beruntung bs dpt tiket utk naik ke Candi borobudur sehari sebelumnya. Kl beli tiket di loket lokasi,cuma utk sampai pelataran Candi Borobudur aja, sayang sih. Tp kl cuma foto2 aja, ga salah kok, apalagi sudah terlanjur datang.

Jika kita beli tiket naik ke candi, kita dpt sandal yg hrs dipakai utk naik ke candi, tas spoundbond dan 1 botol aqua 330ml. Nanti juga ada pemandunya yg akan menceritakan ttg Borubudur. Sepanjang jalan atau spot2 tertentu,kita juga dikasih kesempatan utk bs foto,jd jgn takut ga bs foto2.
textTranslated:
If you want to go up, don't forget to buy tickets online via Traveloka, check a few days beforehand, if you're lucky you can get a ticket to go up to Borobudur Temple the day before. If you buy a ticket at the location counter, it's only to get to the grounds of Borobudur Temple, it's a shame. But if it's just taking photos, there's nothing wrong with that, especially if you've already arrived.

If we buy tickets to go up to the temple, we get sandals that must be worn to go up to the temple, a spongebond bag and 1 bottle of Aqua 330ml. Later there will also be a guide who will tell you about Borubudur. Along certain roads or spots, we are also given the opportunity to take photos, so don't be afraid of not being able to take photos.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia

text: Udah beberapa kali ke sini saat belum menikah selalu siang hari yg terik, akhirnya bisa kembali ke sini setelah lebih dari 15th bersama keluarga dapat hari yg sejuk setelah hujan reda & baru nyadar klo Borobudur itu di antara perbukitan yg indah banget. Jika hari libur sekolah sebaiknya beli tiket untuk naik ke candinya minimal 2 hari sebelumnya atau 3 hari sebelumnya biar bisa milih sesi yg diinginkan karena terbatas jadi lebih terjaga lebih teratur...

If it's a school holiday, it's best to buy tickets to go up to the temple at least 2 days before or 3 days beforehand so you can choose the session you want because it's limited so you'll stay awake more regularly...

name: Syd S
text:
Sonnenaufgang Besichtigung ist seit 2022 nicht mehr möglich! Wir waren um 6 Uhr frühs da, leider öffnen die erst ab 08:30 für die Touren, also wer auch nach oben möchte, sollte frühstens um 8 Uhr da sein. Ansonsten kann man ab 06:30 unten im Park seine Seele baumeln lassen. Schöner alter historischer Ort mit viel Geschichte. Restauriert wurde er auch vor kurzem und bezahlt hat es (wer auch sonst) Deutschland! Dafür das Deutschland alles zahlt, bekommen wir deutsche nie Rabatte ;-) der Preis von 455.000k IDR ist schon heftig, vor allem wenn man bedenkt das die Tour nur 1h geht. Des weiteren muss man für Fahrräder, Busse oder sonstige Fortbewegungsmittel extra bezahlen. Im Preis inbegriffen sind die schönen Latschen aus Indonesischer Herkunft (ohne Latschen dürft ihr nicht in  bzw auf dem Tempel rauf), und eine Wasserflasche pro Person gibt es obendrein. Aber es ist ein Ort, den man gesehen haben muss. Am ende waren wir froh darüber dass wir es doch uns angesehen haben.
Tickets kann man online kaufen, muss man aber nicht. Wir waren die ersten und waren ganz alleine, wie man auf den Bildern sehen kann, war es sehr ruhig.
textTranslated:
Sunrise viewing has no longer been possible since 2022! We were there at 6 a.m., unfortunately they don't open for tours until 8:30 a.m., so if you want to go up, you should be there at 8 a.m. at the earliest. Otherwise, you can unwind down in the park from 6:30 a.m. Beautiful old historic place with a lot of history. It was also recently restored and Germany (who else) paid for it! Because Germany pays for everything, we Germans never get any discounts ;-) the price of 455,000k IDR is steep, especially when you consider that the tour only lasts 1 hour. Furthermore, you have to pay extra for bicycles, buses or other means of transport. Included in the price are the beautiful slippers from Indonesian origin (you are not allowed in or on the temple without them), and there is also a water bottle per person. But it is a must-see place. In the end we were happy that we checked it out.
You can buy tickets online, but you don't have to. We were the first and were completely alone, as you can see from the pictures it was very quiet.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Kikyyy Handayani
text: Candi dari jamannya SD smpy skrg 35 thn tetep mempunyai daya tarik magnet yg kuat kental dan ga bosen2 dengan sejarahnya yg saat ini bila mau naik ke atas candi harud dengan guide beda dengan dulu org bebas mau lama2 duduk naik2 sekarang sudah tidak boleh lagi memang untuk melestarikan candi yg sudah puluhan tahun agar tidak rusak
textTranslated: This temple, from the time of elementary school to junior high school, is now 35 years old and still has a strong magnetic attraction and never gets bored with its history. Currently, if you want to go up to the top of the temple, you have to go with a guide, unlike in the past, people were free to sit and climb for a long time. Now it's no longer allowed to preserve a temple that has been around for decades so that it doesn't get damaged.
title: Borobudur Temple

text:
bagus sayangnya harga tiket tdk d jelaskan d awal

good, unfortunately the ticket price was not explained at the start

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia

text: Situs sejarah yg sangat bagus..naik ke candi bayar 120k dewasa, anak 75 k. Bs dapat sandal, guide shg bs tau sejarah tentang candi Borobudur. Tempatnya sangat bersih. Kuota perhari untuk bs naik ke candi hanya 1200 orang

title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Eka Sumpono
text: Tempatnya lebih rapi & tertata sekarang. Pintu masuknya pindah k area lain. Jd kalo mau ke candi mesti naik shuttle bus, sementara free trial, mudah² an ke depannya selalu free shutle bus nya. Karena lumayan jauh antara lokasi parkiran baru ke candi borobudurnya. Pedagang suvenir difasilitasi lapak2 yg cukup memadai cuma harganya lumayan mahal, lebih mahal dibanding prambanan, mungkin krn lapaknya baru. Sistem utk melihat candi lebih tertata rapi skrg. Kunjungan dibasi 150an org per batch, jadi harus antri, tp worth it, krn d pelatarab & di atas candi tdk berdesak2 an seperti dulu. Biaya mengunjungi pelataran candi 50k, kalo sampe puncak candi 120k. Setelah beli tiket dikasih gelang barcode, sendal, serta tour guide. Tiap naik ke 1 lantai tour guide akan menjelaskan sejarahnya. Cocok utk yg suka sejarah.
textTranslated: The place is neater & organized now. The entrance has moved to another area. So if you want to go to the temple you have to take the shuttle bus, while it's a free trial, hopefully in the future the shuttle bus will always be free. Because it is quite far between the new parking location and the Borobudur temple. Souvenir traders are provided with adequate stalls, but the prices are quite expensive, more expensive than Prambanan, perhaps because the stalls are new. The system for viewing the temple is more neatly organized now. Visits are limited to 150 people per batch, so you have to queue, but it's worth it, because in the courtyard & above the temple there's no crowding like before. The cost of visiting the temple grounds is 50k, if you get to the top of the temple 120k. After purchasing tickets, you will be given a barcode bracelet, sandals and a tour guide. Every time you go up to 1 floor the tour guide will explain the history. Suitable for those who like history.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Michel G
text:
Bezocht op een zondag het bezoek is flink gelimiteerd en je moet met een gids mee en je krijgt slippers mee.
De buddhas in de stupa's mogen niet aangeraakt worden.
Een groepje uit CHINA deed het toch
Het is regenseizoen en op de top viel een flinke regenbui.
En zijn er geen regels om tijdens onweer geen mensen boven toe te laten?
textTranslated:
Visited on a Sunday, the visit is very limited and you have to go with a guide and you get slippers.
The Buddhas in the stupas are not allowed to be touched.
A group from CHINA did it anyway
It is rainy season and there was a heavy rain shower at the top.
And aren't there rules against allowing people upstairs during thunderstorms?
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: 2 goNjoy
text:
욕야카르타에 위치한 보로부두르사원
세계3대불교사원
보로부두르(Borobudur) 불교 사원군은 세계에서 가장 위대한 불교 기념물이다.
이 어마어마한 사원은 750년~842년에 세워졌다. 이 시기는 캄보디아의 앙코르 와트(Angkor Wat)보다 300년 앞서고 거대한 유럽 대성당들이 세워지던 때보다 400년이나 앞선 것이다
이것에서 선라이즈 투어도 추천하고 기본패키지는 탑 꼭대기에 오를수 없다
미리 가이드를 통해 추가입장권을 구매하여 보로부두르사원의 건축역사와 내부구조물과 새겨진 조각상의 의미등을 듣는다면 더 기억나는 여행이 될것이다
Borovudur Temple, located in Yokyakarta
the world's top three Buddhist temples
The Borobudur Buddhist Temples are the world's greatest Buddhist monuments.
The enormous temple was built between 750 and 842. This period was 300 years ahead of Cambodia's Angkor Wat, and 400 years ahead of the time when massive European cathedrals were built
I also recommend Sunrise tours from this, and the basic package can't top the tower
It will be a more memorable trip if you purchase additional tickets through the guide in advance and listen to the architectural history of the Borobudur temple and the meaning of the internal structure and the engraved sculpture
textTranslated:
Borobudur Temple in Yogyakarta
World's 3rd largest Buddhist temple
The Borobudur group of Buddhist temples is the greatest Buddhist monument in the world.
This enormous temple was built between 750 and 842. This period predates Angkor Wat in Cambodia by 300 years and predates the construction of the great European cathedrals by 400 years.
The sunrise tour is also recommended here, and the basic package does not allow you to climb to the top of the tower.
It will be a more memorable trip if you purchase an additional admission ticket through a guide in advance and learn about the architectural history of Borobudur Temple, its internal structure, and the meaning of the carved statues.

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Ulrich Lachnit
text:
Waren hier in den Abendstunden 15.30 - 17.30h
Sehr schöne Anlage die im Wechselspiel mit Sonne und Wolken gut zur Geltung kommt. Es ist auch nicht mehr zu heiß dann. Die Gruppen werden in Slots zu jeweils 150Leuten eingelassen dies verläuft sich dann aber gut. Eine wirklich imposante Anlage. Nervig sind die fliegenden Händler am Ein- und Ausgang. Wenn man Sie komplett ignoriert geht es.
"DIDAK" heißt Nein, das hilft auch.
Noch in der Anlage auf dem Weg zum Ausgang sind feste Händler auf ca 1km!
Hier kann man alles bekommen was man sich touristisch so vorstellt.
textTranslated:
Were here in the evenings 3:30 p.m. - 5:30 p.m
Very beautiful facility that comes into its own in the interplay of sun and clouds. It's not too hot anymore either. The groups are admitted into slots of 150 people each, but things go well. A truly impressive facility. The hawkers at the entrance and exit are annoying. If you completely ignore it, it works.
“DIDAK” means no, that helps too.
There are still dealers in the complex on the way to the exit about 1km away!
Here you can get everything you could imagine as a tourist.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: shugi xu
text:
Borobudur sekarang sudah sangat rapi. tempat parkir mobil juga berubah menjadi ke arah utara, cuma papan arah penunjuk dari pintu masuk lama masih sangat minim jadi bagi yang belum tau akan menjadi bingung. Tersedia shuttle juga dari parkiran mobil ke pintu masuk. Tersedia SPKLU juga untuk Mobil Listrik dan SPLU untuk Motor Listrik didalam parkiran. Bagi pengunjung yang capek jalan cuma tersedia penyewaan sepeda engkol yang ukurannya semua sama ( ukuran besar ) sehingga bagi anak2 tidak tersedia. mungkin bisa di sediaakan penyewaan sepeda listrik juga sebagai opsi. Terus untuk delman/ andong juga kapasitas hanya untuk 4 penumpang tidak bisa lebih walaupun 5 orang tidak bisa dibiarkan naik. Sehingga bagi pengunjung 1 grup 5 orng akan kesusahan.
Beberapa list harga yang kami perhatikan
Tiket masuk dewasa 50k dan anak2 25k ( halaman)
Tiket masuk naik ke candi borobudurnya 125k dan terdapat jam dan kuota buat naik keatas.
Andong / delman 100k 1 putaran kurang lebih 2,5km borobudur
Sewa sepeda 20k
Naik shuttle caddy 25k/ orang ( campur pengunjung lain )
Smoga membantu.
textTranslated:
Borobudur is now very neat. The car park has also changed to the north, only the signage from the old entrance is still very minimal so those who don't know will be confused. There is also a shuttle from the car park to the entrance. SPKLU is also available for electric cars and SPLU for electric motorbikes in the parking lot. For visitors who are tired of walking, there is only crank bike rental available which is all the same size (large size) so it is not available for children. Maybe you can also provide electric bicycle rental as an option. Then for carriages/carts, the capacity is only for 4 passengers, there can be no more, although 5 people cannot be allowed to ride. So for visitors in a group of 5 people it will be difficult.
Some price lists that we pay attention to
Admission ticket for adults 50k and children 25k (page)
The entrance ticket to go up to Borobudur temple is 125k and there are hours and quotas to go up.
Andong / delman 100k 1 lap approximately 2.5km Borobudur
Bike rental 20k
Ride a caddy shuttle 25k/person (mixed with other visitors)
Hope it helps.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Andreas Suryadi
text: Area Borobudur telah berubah menjadi lebih baik skrg, semua tertata rapih, perkebunan hijau... Tambah keren....
textTranslated: The Borobudur area has changed for the better now, everything is neatly arranged, green plantations... It's even cooler...
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Namu Kim
text: 앙코르왓보다 300년전에 지어졌다는 이 세계3대 불교유적지중 하나인 보로부두르 사원은 내 오래된 버킷리스트중 하나였음! 세계테마기행에서 본 이후로 가보고싶은곳중 하나였는데 실망하면 어쩌나 했는데 기우였음!! 다만 꼭 탑층까지 올라가봐야 그 진가를 알수있음! 그라운드 티켓으로 아랫쪽만 돌아서는 그 벅찬 감동과 감흥을 절대 느낄 수 없음! 솔직히 가이드와함께 중간정도 올라갈때 까지도 앙코르왓과 비슷하다는 생각과함께 비싼요금에대한 후회가 몰려왔지만 정상에 올라간순간 그 모든 기우가 부는 바람과함께 날아가버렸음!! 욕야카르타에가신다면 보로부두르 사원은 꼭 가보길바람! 정상까지는 인원제한이 있기에 예약은 필수이며 어느정도 공부하고 간다면 아는만큼 보인다고 감동도 두배가 될거임!! 앙코르왓과는 전혀 다른매력과 느낌으로 다가올거임!
textTranslated: Built 300 years before Angkor Wat, Borobudur Temple, one of the world's top three Buddhist ruins, has been on my bucket list for a long time! It was one of the places I wanted to visit ever since I saw it on World Theme Travel, so I thought what I would do if I was disappointed, but it turned out to be wrong!! However, you must go up to the top floor to appreciate its true value! You will never be able to feel the overwhelming emotion and excitement of only going around the bottom with a ground ticket! To be honest, even when I went up halfway with the guide, I thought it was similar to Angkor Wat and regretted the high price, but the moment I got to the top, all the rain was blown away with the blowing wind!! If you go to Yogyakarta, you must visit Borobudur Temple! There is a limit to the number of people up to the summit, so reservations are essential. If you study a bit before going, you will be twice as impressed by seeing as much as you know!! It will have a completely different charm and feel from Angkor Wat!
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: jody rizkys
text: Tidak ada tempat makan, parkiran keloket masuk jauh, antri mobil antar jemput lama padahal sudah tau musim liburan. tidak rekomendasi untuk anak anak, touris asing malah jadi prioritas utama. Harga tiket masuk dibedakan antara lokal dan mancanegara padahal dinegara luar tidak begitu
textTranslated: There is no place to eat, the parking lot is far away, the queue for the shuttle car is long even though you already know it's the holiday season. Not recommended for children, foreign tourists are the main priority. Entry ticket prices are differentiated between local and international, even though this is not the case in foreign countries
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: S M
text:
เจดียบุโรพุทโธ หรือ จันทิโบโรบูโด

เจดีย์ขนาดใหญ่ มี 9 ชั้น บูรณะได้ดีมาก ภาพแกะสลักค่อนข้างสมบูณ์อยู่ เสียดายปิดวันจันทร์ อนุญาตให้เดินรอบๆ ได้ แต่ไม่ให้ขึ้นด้านบน แค่ดูด้านล่างก็รู้สึกถึงความอลังการของที่นี่ละ ที่นี่ไม่ต้องใส่ Sarong ใส่เฉพาะวัดพราหมณ์เท่านั้น

จันทิโบโรบูโด (Candi Borobudur) เป็นคำเรียก บุโรพุทโธ ของคนอินโดนีเซีย "จันทิ" นี้มีความหมายว่า วัด เจดีย์ หรือวิหาร ที่มีขนาดใหญ่ ดังนั้นเมื่อเราไปเที่ยวอินโดนีเซีย เราจึงควรเรียกวัดว่า "จันทิ" Candi ทับศัพท์แทน Temple จะเป็นที่เข้าใจของชาวบ้านทั่วไปได้ดี ในขณะที่คำว่า "เจดีย์" ของคนอินโดนีเซีย จะหมายถึง สถานที่ทางศาสนาขนาดเล็ก ที่ใช้สำหรับครอบครัว ตระกูล หรือภายในหมู่บ้านเล็กๆ

จันทิโบโรบูโด เป็นพุทธสถานโบราณที่ใหญ่ที่สุดในโลก สร้างขึ้นระหว่างปี พ.ศ.1323-1393 (ก่อนนครวัดราว 300 ปี) โดยการอุปถัมภ์ของกษัตริย์ราชวงศ์ไศเรนทร (คำว่า “ไศเรนทรา” แปลว่า เจ้าแห่งขุนเขา)

พุทธสถานแห่งนี้ไม่ได้เป็นที่ประดิษฐานพระบรมสารีริกธาตุ แต่สร้างขึ้นเพื่อแสดงถึงศรัทธาในพุทธศาสนาแบบมหายาน และเป็นที่บรรจุพระบรมศพของกษัตริย์ไว้ที่ฐานชั้นต้นๆ โบโรบูโดจึงเป็นการโยงปูขนียสถานในพระพุทธศาสนาเข้ากับการบูชาบรรพบุรุษตามธรรมเนียมของคนตะวันออก

หากมองจากที่สูงทางอากาศ บุโรพุทโธมีลักษณะเป็น “mandara” (มณฑล) ตามคติพุทธมาหายาน และตันตระยาน บุโรพุทโธ ในทางมหายานจึงเป็นสัญลักษณ์ของ “จักรวาล” และอำนาจของ “พระอาทิพุทธเจ้า” โดยพระเจดีย์องค์ใหญ่บนยอดสูงสุดนั้นแทนองค์ “พระอาทิพุทธเจ้า” ที่ทรงเป็นผู้สร้างสรรพสิ่ง

ถ้ามองจากพื้นดินในระยะไกล บุโรพุทโธ คือ สถูปขนาดใหญ่  มีฐานสี่เหลี่ยมรองรับองค์สถูปและยอดสถูป หากเมื่อมองใกล้เข้ามาจะเห็นได้ชัดขึ้นว่าบุโรพุทโธมีโครงสร้างทางสถาปัตยกรรม 2 แบบ คือ ส่วนบนเป็นองค์สถูป ตั้งอยู่บนลานวงกลม 3 ชั้นลดหลั่นขึ้นไป ได้รับอิทธิพลแบบคุปตะอินเดีย ส่วนด้านล่างเป็นรูปแบบปิรามิดขั้นบันได มีลานสี่เหลี่ยม เป็นอิทธิพลของสถาปัตยกรรมแบบชวาโบราณที่เรียกว่า “punden berundak ”

ผู้เชี่ยวชาญได้วิเคราะห์โครงสร้างของบุโรพุทโธ พบว่ามีลำดับการสร้างอยู่ถึง 5 ขั้นในช่วงเวลาเกือบ 80 ปีของการก่อสร้าง

ขั้นแรกสุด เป็นการสร้างฐาน 3 ชั้นบนเนินดินเก่าที่เป็นขั้นๆ อยู่เดิม สันนิษฐานกันว่าในสมัยโบราณอาจเป็นที่สำหรับทำพิธีบูชาวิญญาณของบรรพบุรุษ การใช้ที่เดียวกันนี้สร้างบุโรพุทโธขึ้นในกาลต่อมานั้น  อาจเพราะเล็งเห็นว่าเป็นบริเวณที่ศักดิ์สิทธิ์อยู่แล้วก็ได้

ขั้นที่สองมีการเปลี่ยนแปลงบันไดทางขึ้นและขยายฐานให้กว้างขึ้น รวมทั้งสร้างชั้นสูงขึ้น คือชั้นที่มีฐานสี่เหลี่ยม 2 ชั้นและฐานวงกลมข้างบนอีกหนึ่งชั้น
ขั้นที่สามมีการดัดแปลงเพิ่มเติม โดยรื้อฐานวงกลมชั้นบนนั้นออก และสร้างฐานวงกลม 3 ชั้นสูงลดหลั่นขึ้นไปแทน นอกจากนี้มีการสร้างเจดีย์บนยอดสุดขึ้นในช่วงนี้ด้วย

ส่วนขั้นที่สี่และห้ามีการเปลี่ยนแปลงเพียงเล็กน้อยซึ่งรวมถึงให้มีการแกะสลักลายนูน และสร้างขั้นบันใดและทางเข้ารูปโค้ง เป็นที่สังเกตกันว่า แม้มีการดัดแปลงต่อเติมโครงสร้างของบุโรพุทโธดังกล่าว แต่สัญลักษณ์สำคัญยังคงอยู่ที่องค์เจดีย์ชั้นบนสุด  ในขณะที่ส่วนอื่นๆ ที่อยู่ตามชั้นต่างๆ ลงมานั้นเป็นส่วนประกอบเพื่อสื่อความหมายของบุโรพุทโธนั่นเอง

บุโรพุทโธสร้างด้วยหินภูเขาไฟประมาณ 2 ล้านก้อน สกัดจากหินขนาดใหญ่ที่อยู่ใกล้แม่น้ำโปรโก  ลากมาสู่ที่ก่อสร้างด้วยแรงม้าและช้าง มหาสถูปมีระเบียงซ้อนกันเป็นชั้นๆ ลดหลั่นไป มีการตกแต่งด้วยภาพสลักที่ชั้นที่ 2 และ 3 แยกเป็นภาพสลักนูนต่ำ 1460 ภาพและแผ่นภาพแกะ (panel) สำหรับประดับ 1212 แผ่น ส่วนที่ฐานล่างอีก 160 ภาพ และ รูปปั้นพระพุทธรูป 504 องค์ พระพุทธรูปแต่ละองค์นั่งอยู่ภายในสถูปเจาะรูปสี่เหลี่ยมข้าวหลามตัด รอบล้อมสถูปเจดีย์ประธาน

เมื่อมองดูรูปภายนอกของบุโรพุทโธ อาจเห็นการแบ่งออกเป็น 3 ระดับ เรื่องนี้ ดร.สตัทเตอร์ไฮม์ ได้สันนิษฐานว่า การที่แบ่งพุทธวิหารแห่งนี้ออกเป็น 3 ตอนนั้น ช่างใกล้เคียงต่อศรัทธาของชาวพุทธที่แบ่งวิถีชีวิตออกเป็น 3 ชั้น เหลือเกิน คือ

Cr: www.norbhoditravel
textTranslated:
Borobudur Pagoda or Chandiborobudo

A large pagoda with 9 floors, very well restored. The carved images are quite complete. Unfortunately closed on Mondays You are allowed to walk around, but not to the top. You can feel the splendor of this place just by looking below. There is no need to wear Sarong here, only at Brahmin temples.

Candi Borobudur is the Indonesian word for Borobudur. "Candi" means a temple, pagoda, or large temple. So when we travel to Indonesia Therefore, we should call the temple "Chandi". Candi transliteration instead of Temple will be better understood by the general villagers. While the Indonesian word "pagoda" refers to a small religious place. used for families, clans, or within small villages

Chandiborobudo It is the largest ancient Buddhist site in the world. Built during the year 1323-1393 AD (about 300 years before Angkor Wat) under the patronage of the kings of the Chairendra dynasty (the word "Chairendra" means lord of the mountain)

This Buddhist site does not house the Buddha's relics. But it was built to show faith in Mahayana Buddhism. and is where the royal remains are placed at the base of the first floor. Borobudo therefore connects Buddhist sites with the worship of ancestors according to the Eastern tradition.

If viewed from a height in the air Borobudur is characterized as a "mandara" (monthon) according to Mahayana and Tantrayan Buddhist beliefs. In Mahayana, Borobudur is therefore a symbol of the "universe" and the power of the "Sun Buddha", represented by a large pagoda on the highest peak. “Phra Athi Buddha” who is the creator of all things

If viewed from the ground in the distance, Borobudur is a large stupa with a square base supporting the stupa and the top of the stupa. If you look closer, it becomes clearer that Borobudur has two architectural structures: the upper part is a stupa. Located on a circular courtyard with 3 levels descending upwards. Influenced by the Indian Gupta style. The bottom part is in the form of a stepped pyramid. There is a square courtyard. It is influenced by ancient Javanese architecture called “punden berundak.”

Experts have analyzed the structure of Borobudur. It was found that there were five stages of construction during nearly 80 years of construction.

The first step involves building a 3-tiered base on top of an old, level mound. It is assumed that in ancient times it might have been a place for ceremonies to worship the spirits of ancestors. The same place was used to build Borobudur later on.  Maybe because they saw that it was already a sacred area.

The second step was to change the stairs and widen the base. including building a higher floor It is a floor with two square bases and a circular base above.
The third step involves additional modifications. By dismantling the upper circular base. and built a 3-story circular base descending upwards instead. In addition, a pagoda at the top was also built during this period.

The fourth and fifth steps had only minor changes, including the addition of relief carvings. and built steps and an arched entrance. It is noted that Even though there were modifications and additions to the structure of Borobudur, But the important symbol remains on the top floor of the pagoda.  while other parts located on various floors It is a component to convey the meaning of Borobudur.

Borobudur is made of approximately 2 million volcanic stones, hewn from large rocks near the Progo River.  Dragged to the construction site by horsepower and elephants. The stupa has cascading tiered terraces. It is decorated with carvings on the second and third floors, consisting of 1460 reliefs and 1212 decorative panels, 160 at the base and 504 Buddha statues. Each Buddha sits within a diamond-shaped stupa. Surrounding the main pagoda

When looking at the exterior of Borobudur It may be seen that this is divided into 3 levels. Dr. Stutterheim It was assumed that The division of this Buddhist temple into 3 sections is very close to the belief of Buddhists who divide their way of life into 3 levels:

text: 世界三大仏教遺跡「ボロブドゥール寺院」。アンコールワットとは違った凄みがありました。2024年8月時点では登頂制限が１日1200人とあり登ってみると多過ぎることない観光客がちょうど良い。チケット予約は必須。当日チケット購入は登れない可能性が高い。私は10日前に予約したときには朝の時間は予約でいっぱいでした。登頂の際は、専用のサンダルもらえます。
textTranslated: Borobudur Temple is one of the world's three largest Buddhist monuments. It had a different kind of awesomeness than Angkor Wat. As of August 2024, the limit for climbing the mountain is 1,200 people per day, which means it's just the right number of tourists without being too many. Ticket reservations are required. If you purchase a ticket on the day, there is a high possibility that you will not be able to go up. When I made a reservation 10 days in advance, the morning time was fully booked. When you reach the summit, you will receive special sandals.
title: Borobudur Temple

text: 看其他評論說可以到現場買登頂的票，但是現場櫃檯表示在線上就賣完登頂的票了，而且不是今天的賣完，是明天、後天、大後天的都賣完。一趟到這，一定要登頂，所以一定要線上買好登頂的票！登頂的票就直接在官網買就好了。我在klook買庭園票，其評論上說可以提早到現場排隊買登頂的票！事實上根本沒辦法。另外，現場叫賣的小攤以及離開時經過的市集，賣的東西的價格都亂喊到非常誇張，建議去印度廟普南巴南（到日惹也必去的）的離場市集時再好好逛好好買，那裡的市集很大，也有明碼標價，也不會一直纏著你要你買，良心建議！
textTranslated: I read other reviews that you can buy tickets to the summit on-site, but the on-site counter said that the tickets to the summit are sold out online, and they are not sold out today, but tomorrow, the day after tomorrow, and the day after tomorrow. If you go here, you must climb to the top, so be sure to buy your tickets online! Just buy your tickets to the summit directly from the official website. I bought a garden ticket from klook, and the reviews said that I could queue up early to buy tickets to the summit! In fact there is no way. In addition, the prices of the things sold at the stalls on site and at the market that you pass by when leaving are very exaggerated. It is recommended to go to the leaving market of the Hindu Temple Punan Banan (a must-visit in Yogyakarta). Go shopping and buy carefully. The market there is very big and the prices are clearly marked. They won’t keep pestering you to buy. It’s a good suggestion!

text:
My very first time visiting Borobudur Temple!

Harga tiket masuk untuk wisatawan domestik 50.000, kalau mau naik candinya 120.000 (sudah termasuk biaya masuk). Kalau menurut saya mending beli tiket naik candinya sekalian karena kalau hanya pelataran candi rasanya kurang, apalagi kalau belum pernah ke Borobudur sama sekali.

Panas! Disarankan bawa payung atau pakai topi. Plus datang mending pagi-pagi biar ngga terlalu ramai, jadi untuk spot-spot ciamik berlatar belakang Borobudur-nya ngga ngantri/foto bocor orang lain hehe.

Buat yang ngga suka jalan, kalau udah ke pintu keluar candi mending naik delman/sejenisnya buat ke parkiran/pintu keluar karena kalau jalan kaki cukup jauh.
textTranslated:
My very first time visiting Borobudur Temple!

The entrance ticket price for domestic tourists is 50,000, if you want to climb the temple it is 120,000 (including entrance fees). In my opinion, it's better to buy a ticket to go up to the temple at the same time because if it's just the temple grounds it doesn't feel like it's enough, especially if you've never been to Borobudur at all.

Hot! It is recommended to bring an umbrella or wear a hat. Plus, it's better to come early in the morning so it's not too crowded, so for the cool spots with Borobudur as the background, there's no queuing/photo leaks from other people hehe.

For those who don't like walking, if you're already at the temple exit, it's better to take a carriage or something similar to get to the parking lot/exit because it's quite a long walk.
title: Borobudur Temple

Coincidentally, my visit was also when it was hot. So I feel quite tired. In the end, this should be a mandatory destination for those on holiday in Yogya. Because it is truly beautiful and majestic.

name: Jacopo Burzacchi
text:
Uno dei tre templi più belli visti in Indonesia, assieme a Borobudur e Besakih.
Prambanan è un complesso di quattro templi, di cui due molto grandi posti ad ingresso e fine, e due più piccoli posti a metà del percorso.
La forma e lo stile ricordano vagamente Siem Reap in Cambogia.
Parco molto ben tenuto ed ordinato, al mattino c'è pochissima gente.
Noi abbiamo preso i biglietti sul sito ma in loco c'è la biglietteria.
Tolgo una stella per lo zoo presente all'interno, dove hanno messo in gabbie piccole due casuari e alcuni cervidi: gli animali devono stare in natura o, nel caso, in strutture controllate (es. Yellowstone, Serengeti... ecc, ecc)
textTranslated:
One of the three most beautiful temples seen in Indonesia, together with Borobudur and Besakih.
Prambanan is a complex of four temples, two of which are very large at the entrance and end, and two smaller ones located halfway along the route.
The shape and style are vaguely reminiscent of Siem Reap in Cambodia.
Very well kept and tidy park, in the morning there are very few people.
We bought the tickets on the site but there is a ticket office on site.
I will remove a star for the zoo inside, where they have placed two cassowaries and some cervids in small cages: the animals must stay in nature or, if necessary, in controlled structures (e.g. Yellowstone, Serengeti... etc, etc)
title: Prambanan Temple

textTranslated:
One of the places you must visit if you go to Jogja. Prambanan Temple offers a view of the largest worship temple in Southeast Asia. Prices are now a bit expensive due to new regulations. To enter from the parking lot is quite a long way to the ticket booth. At certain times there is a Ramayana Ballet performance at Prambanan Temple at night, it is very worth it, the traditional dance performance set against the backdrop of Prambanan Temple at night is very beautiful, ticket prices range from 150-300 thousand and the start usually starts at 19.00.
Overall, Prambanan Temple can still be one of the places you can visit in Jogja with its unique Jogja cultural background.

พรัมบานัน (Candi Prambanan) เทวสถานในศาสนาฮินดูที่ใหญ่ที่สุดในอินโดนีเซีย มี 4 วัดหลักอยู่ด้านใน เป็นวัดฮินดูและวัดพุทธ ใครมาแนะนำว่านั่งรถกอล์ฟ ไม่ก็เช่ามอเตอร์ไซค์ขับด้านในจะลดการใช้พลังงานได้มาก บัตรเข้าชมแนะนำว่าซื้อควบบุโรพุทโธ-พรัมบานัน จะถูกกว่า

สร้างขึ้นเมื่อปี พ.ศ. 1390 ปัจจุบันได้ขึ้นทะเบียนเป็นมรดกโลก สร้างตามคติความเชื่อของศาสนาฮินดู ประกอบด้วยกลุ่มปรางค์ 8 หลัง มีปรางค์ขนาดใหญ่ที่สุด เป็นปรางค์ประธานอยู่ตรงกลาง ซึ่งเป็นที่ประดิษฐานของเทวรูปพระศิวะ รอบ ๆ ปรางค์ประธาน ก็เป็นที่ประดิษฐานของเทวรูปเช่นกัน ฝั่งซ้ายของปรางค์ประธานเป็นของพระพรหม ขวาเป็นของพระวิษณุ รายรอบด้วยวิหารอีก 156 หลัง สร้างจากหิน ประดับตกแต่งด้วยหินสลักลวดลายต่าง ๆ ตามความเชื่อในศาสนาฮินดู เล่าเรื่องราวรามายณะ

Cr: travel.trueid.net
textTranslated:
Prambanan (Candi Prambanan), the largest Hindu temple in Indonesia, has 4 main temples inside. It is a Hindu temple and a Buddhist temple. Who suggested that you ride a golf cart? Otherwise, rent a motorcycle and drive inside, which will greatly reduce energy use. Tickets are recommended to be bought together with Borobudur - Prambanan, it will be cheaper.

Built in 1390, it is now registered as a World Heritage Site. Built according to the beliefs of Hinduism. Consists of a group of 8 prangs, with the largest prang. It is the main prang in the middle. This is where the Lord Shiva idol is enshrined. Around the main prang is also an enshrined idol. The left side of the main prang belongs to Phra Brahma. The right belongs to Vishnu. Surrounded by another 156 temples, built from stone and decorated with stones carved with various patterns according to Hindu beliefs. Tell the story of Ramayana

text: Candi Borobudur sebagai objek wisata menjadi pilihan untuk dikunjungi oleh wisatawan lokal ataupun mancanegara. Pintu masuk dari area parkir terdekat tidak terlalu jauh, jadi kalau bisa jangan parkir terlalu jauh dari pintu masuk. Tiket dewasa masih 50rb per kepala, anak" dibawah 10th 25rb, hanya untuk sampai plataran bawah saya, tidak untuk sampai bisa naik ke atas candi, untuk naik ada charge tambahan. Untuk sampai ke candi dari pintu masuk harus jalan dulu, tapi bisa juga naik mobil golf bayar 20rb pernah orang dapet air minum. Jalur naik ada dua bisa lewat tangga tengah atau jalur yang lebih landai, atau jalur kiri untuk stroller bayi juga bisa. Yang perlu jadi concern adalah lingkungan sekitar di area plataran candi masih banyak yang berupa pasir kuning, kenapa dari pengelola tidak dirubah jadi lebih bersih, karena debu berterbangan kemana-mana. kalau posisi habis hujan sih agak mending yaa, untuk balik ke pintu keluar juga ada fasilitas mobil golf, nanti diarahkan ke museum dahulu baru keluar ke arah pasar atau tempat oleh-oleh, kita hari jalan menyusuri lorong-lorong tsb utk bisa keluar, harap pengelola juga memperhatikan jalur exit ini, kami tidak keberatan kalau suruh jalan didalam pasar, tapi pastikan jalan cukup lebar, bagus, bersih dan terang.
textTranslated: Borobudur Temple as a tourist attraction is a choice for local and foreign tourists to visit. The entrance from the nearest parking area is not too far, so if possible, don't park too far from the entrance. Adult tickets are still 50 thousand per head, children under 10 25 thousand, only to get to my lower platform, not to get to the top of the temple, to go up there is an additional charge. To get to the temple from the entrance you have to walk first, but you can also go up For golf carts you can get drinking water for 20 thousand. There are two routes up, you can take the middle stairs or the more sloping route, or you can also use the left route for baby strollers. What needs to be concerned is that the surrounding environment in the temple area is still mostly yellow sand , why didn't the management change it to make it cleaner, because the dust flies everywhere if it rains, it's a bit better, to get back to the exit there are also golf cart facilities, then you will be directed to the museum first and then go out towards the market or the place by the way. - By the way, today we walk along the alleys to get out, we hope the management will also pay attention to this exit route, we don't mind if we ask you to walk inside the market, but make sure the road is wide enough, good, clean and bright.

title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Любовь Кузнецова
text:
Что понравилось: чувствуется, что место намоленное, величественное, интересно было посетить.

Что не понравилось: чтобы подняться на сам комплекс нужно купить билеты онлайн. Так как мы были проездом, то не смогли купить билеты. Все билеты на ближайшую неделю раскуплены 🤷‍♀️ сидеть тут и ждать - не вариант.
В итоге купили просто на прогулку вокруг храма. У нас есть китасы, поэтому взрослые 50 т.руп., дети от 3х лет - 25 т.р.
150 т.р. - на семью отлично.
Парковки для байков нет. Видимо в процессе стройки. Припарковались у главного входа у магазина (по совету охраны), приехали к 6.30 утра.

Народу ~ 10 человек, одни иностранцы (четверг). Но! вход на вершину комплекса закрыт и открывается в 8:30. Так что в любом случае встретить рассвет - не вариант. Просто закрыто. Берите на последний сеанс - на закат.

Выход из парка - 1 км по торговым рядам. Беспощадно. Благо, что утром часть была закрыта.

И потом ещё долго-долго идти искать место парковки байка.
По парку перемещение тоже пешком. С утра нет никаких повозок и прокатов транспорта.

Конечно было здорово, что практически не было людей с утра, было прохладно и довольно красиво. Все остальные моменты с билетами и парковкой - просто недоразумение какое-то для места такого масштаба....
textTranslated:
What I liked: it felt like the place was sacred, majestic, and it was interesting to visit.

What I didn’t like: to climb the complex itself you need to buy tickets online. Since we were passing through, we were not able to buy tickets. All tickets for the next week are sold out 🤷‍♀️ sitting here and waiting is not an option.
In the end, we just bought it for a walk around the temple. We have kitas, so adults 50 thousand rubles, children from 3 years old - 25 thousand rubles.
150 t.r. - great for a family.
There is no parking for bikes. Apparently under construction. We parked at the main entrance of the store (on the advice of security) and arrived at 6.30 am.

About 10 people, some foreigners (Thursday). But! The entrance to the top of the complex is closed and opens at 8:30. So, in any case, meeting the sunrise is not an option. Just closed. Take it for the last session - for sunset.

The exit from the park is 1 km along the shopping arcades. Mercilessly. Fortunately, that part was closed in the morning.

And then it’s a long, long time to go looking for a place to park the bike.
You can also move around the park on foot. In the morning there are no carts or rental vehicles.

Of course it was great that there were practically no people in the morning, it was cool and quite beautiful. All other issues with tickets and parking are just some kind of misunderstanding for a place of this scale....

Overall, of course worth seeing, but enjoyment is different. But it's difficult to do with so many people.

text:
Prambanan: A Majestic Glimpse into Indonesia's Hindu Past
Prambanan, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, is a sprawling complex of Hindu temples near Yogyakarta, Indonesia. Built in the 9th century, it's a testament to the ancient Mataram Kingdom's power and devotion. The main temple, dedicated to Shiva, is a towering structure adorned with intricate carvings depicting scenes from the Ramayana epic.
Walking through Prambanan is like stepping back in time. The sheer size and scale of the temples are awe-inspiring. Each structure tells a story, from the majestic central shrine to the smaller surrounding temples dedicated to Vishnu and Brahma.
The complex also houses the Prambanan Archaeological Museum, where visitors can learn more about the history and significance of the site. The museum's collection includes artifacts unearthed during excavations, offering a fascinating glimpse into daily life in ancient Java.
While some parts of the complex are still under restoration after a devastating earthquake in 2006, Prambanan remains a must-visit destination for anyone interested in Indonesia's rich cultural heritage. Its blend of history, spirituality, and architectural grandeur is truly unique.
Tips for visiting:
* Go early or late in the day to avoid the midday heat and crowds.
* Hire a guide to get a deeper understanding of the temples' history and symbolism.
* Attend the Ramayana Ballet performance, held on an open-air stage with the temples as a backdrop.

Prambanan: Keagungan Masa Lalu Hindu di Indonesia
Prambanan, sebuah Situs Warisan Dunia UNESCO, adalah kompleks candi Hindu yang luas di dekat Yogyakarta, Indonesia. Dibangun pada abad ke-9, candi ini merupakan bukti kekuatan dan pengabdian Kerajaan Mataram kuno. Candi utama, yang didedikasikan untuk Siwa, adalah bangunan menjulang yang dihiasi dengan ukiran rumit yang menggambarkan adegan dari epik Ramayana.
Berjalan melalui Prambanan seperti melangkah mundur ke masa lalu. Ukuran dan skala candi yang besar sungguh menakjubkan. Setiap struktur menceritakan sebuah kisah, dari candi pusat yang megah hingga candi-candi kecil di sekitarnya yang didedikasikan untuk Wisnu dan Brahma.
Kompleks ini juga menampung Museum Arkeologi Prambanan, di mana pengunjung dapat mempelajari lebih lanjut tentang sejarah dan pentingnya situs ini. Koleksi museum meliputi artefak yang digali selama penggalian, menawarkan sekilas kehidupan sehari-hari di Jawa kuno yang menarik.
Meskipun beberapa bagian kompleks masih dalam pemulihan setelah gempa bumi dahsyat pada tahun 2006, Prambanan tetap menjadi tujuan yang wajib dikunjungi bagi siapa pun yang tertarik dengan warisan budaya Indonesia yang kaya. Perpaduan sejarah, spiritualitas, dan kemegahan arsitekturnya benar-benar unik.
Tips untuk berkunjung:
* Pergi lebih awal atau menjelang sore untuk menghindari panas dan keramaian di siang hari.
* Gunakan jasa pemandu untuk mendapatkan pemahaman yang lebih dalam tentang sejarah dan simbolisme candi.
* Hadiri pertunjukan Ramayana Ballet, yang diadakan di panggung terbuka dengan candi sebagai latar belakang.

name: Reno Delison Bakkara
text:
Candi Borobudur adalah salah satu keajaiban arsitektur dunia yang terletak di Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia. Candi ini dibangun pada abad ke-8 hingga ke-9 Masehi oleh Dinasti Syailendra dan merupakan candi Buddha terbesar di dunia. Terbuat dari batu andesit, Borobudur berbentuk punden berundak yang terdiri dari sembilan tingkat, dengan enam tingkat berbentuk bujur sangkar dan tiga tingkat berbentuk lingkaran, serta satu stupa utama di puncaknya.

Keunikan Candi Borobudur terletak pada relief-relief yang menghiasi dinding candi, menggambarkan cerita-cerita dari ajaran Buddha, termasuk kehidupan Siddhartha Gautama, perjalanan menuju pencerahan, dan hukum karma. Lebih dari 2.600 panel relief dan 504 arca Buddha tersebar di seluruh bangunan ini, menjadikannya salah satu karya seni ukir terbesar dan terindah di dunia.

Borobudur tidak hanya menjadi situs warisan budaya yang diakui UNESCO, tetapi juga merupakan tempat ziarah penting bagi umat Buddha, terutama pada perayaan Waisak. Lingkungan sekitar candi juga dikelilingi oleh pemandangan alam yang memukau, termasuk pegunungan dan hutan hijau.

Dengan daya tarik sejarah, spiritual, dan keindahan arsitekturnya, Candi Borobudur menjadi destinasi wisata budaya yang wajib dikunjungi oleh wisatawan domestik maupun internasional.
textTranslated:
Borobudur Temple is one of the architectural wonders of the world located in Magelang, Central Java, Indonesia. This temple was built in the 8th to 9th centuries AD by the Syailendra Dynasty and is the largest Buddhist temple in the world. Made of andesite stone, Borobudur is in the form of a terraced terrace consisting of nine levels, with six square levels and three circular levels, as well as a main stupa at the top.

The uniqueness of Borobudur Temple lies in the reliefs that decorate the temple walls, depicting stories from Buddhist teachings, including the life of Siddhartha Gautama, the journey to enlightenment, and the law of karma. More than 2,600 relief panels and 504 Buddha statues are spread throughout this building, making it one of the largest and most beautiful works of carving art in the world.

Borobudur is not only a cultural heritage site recognized by UNESCO, but also an important pilgrimage site for Buddhists, especially during Vesak celebrations. The environment around the temple is also surrounded by stunning natural scenery, including mountains and green forests.

With its historical, spiritual appeal and architectural beauty, Borobudur Temple is a cultural tourism destination that must be visited by domestic and international tourists.
title: Borobudur Temple

address: Jl. Raya Solo - Yogyakarta No.16, Kranggan, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55571, Indonesia
name: Daniel Agus
text:
Long weekend juni 2024
Tempat wisata sejarah dan budaya yg sangat rekomended. Lokasi sangat mudah dijangkau krn di tepi jalan raya solo jogja. Maps akurat.
Parkir R4 10k, tempat parkir luas. Usahakan datang agak pagi biar parkir gak jauh2 dari area loket masuk krn ini wisata favorit.
HTM nya 50k/org. Ada paketan prambanan dan ratu boko 85k/org. Bisa diantar jemput pakai mobil pengelola. Kl ratu boko aja 40k/org. Ada jasa guide kl mau belajar lebih.
O ya sblm masuk, siapkan topi atau payung plus air minum yg ckp krn area sangat luas plus jika cuaca terik. Asli kerasa panasnya di area inti candi. Kl males jalan kaki atau bagi yg sepuh bs pakai mobil wisata yg disediakan pengelola untuk keliling c prambanan, c lumbung, c bubrah dan c sewu. Yup, itu semua 1 kawasan. Tiketnya 20k/org kl gak salah dg min 4 penumpang. Yg suka jalan kaki santai sambil menikmati suasana jg ok kq krn area taman di sekitar candi sangat bagus dan terawat sekali. Ada banyak spot untuk duduk2.
Kl mau naik ke 3 candi utama prambanan (c brahma, c siwa dan c wisnu) harap hati2. Tangganya sempit dan terjal. Ikuti papan petunjuk atau arahan petugas.
Ada sewa sepeda angin sm skuter listrik juga. Ada museum. Ada camping ground. Ada area panggung jika pas ada event tertentu. Ada cafe yg menyediakan beragam minuman kopi2 an, ada kedai gelato, ada snack. Untuk makan ada prambanan resto yg wajib dicoba. Masakannya enak dg harga yg boleh dikatakan ckp murah untuk sebuah resto estetik di kawasan wisata internasional. Tp ini kembali ke selera sih. Kl bagi kami ini rekom.
Lalu ada area ketangkasan panahan, ada penangkaran rusa. Bisa kasih makan kerleb 5k an. Ada burung kasuari jg. Di gerbang keluar ada tablet untuk isian kesan dan saran. Lalu setelah keluar area inti ada deretan kedai mamin yg menunya kayak seragam ya? (Lihat foto). Agak disayangkan sih mereka ditaruh di luar area inti krn kami lihat mereka sepi pengunjung. Lalu setelah deretan kedai mamin ada area souvenir dan oleh2 spt umumnya di sebuah tempat wisata.
O ya, di area parkir kita bs naik jeep wisata yg berkeliling daerah sekitar prambanan dg paket paling mahal sktr 500k/jeep.
Pokoknya tempat ini sangat bagus. Candi2 nya bikin wow dan makin wow setelah dilihat dari dekat. Area sangat tertata apik. Gak heran bnyk turis asing ke sini.
Semoga infonya bs sedikit membantu.
textTranslated:
Long weekend June 2024
Highly recommended historical and cultural tourist attractions. The location is very easy to reach because it is on the edge of the Solo Jogja highway. Maps are accurate.
Parking R4 10k, large parking space. Try to come a little early so you can park not far from the entrance counter area because this is a favorite tourist attraction.
The HTM is 50k/person. There are Prambanan and Ratu Boko packages 85k/person. Can be picked up and picked up using the manager's car. Just for Ratu Boko, 40k/person. There are guide services if you want to learn more.
Oh yes, before entering, prepare a hat or umbrella plus adequate drinking water because the area is very large especially if the weather is hot. It was actually really hot in the core area of ​​the temple. If you don't feel like walking or for those who are older, you can use the tourist car provided by the manager to tour C Prambanan, C Lumbung, C Bubrah and C Sewu. Yup, that's all 1 area. The ticket is 20k/person if I'm not mistaken with a minimum of 4 passengers. Those who like to take a leisurely walk while enjoying the atmosphere are also ok because the park area around the temple is very nice and very well maintained. There are lots of spots to sit.
If you want to go up to the 3 main Prambanan temples (C Brahma, C Shiva and C Vishnu) please be careful. The stairs are narrow and steep. Follow the signs or officer's directions.
There are air bikes and electric scooters for rent too. There are museums. There is a camping ground. There is a stage area if there is a certain event. There is a cafe that provides a variety of coffee drinks, there is a gelato shop, there are snacks. For eating, there is a Prambanan restaurant which is a must try. The food is delicious with prices that can be said to be cheap for an aesthetic restaurant in an international tourist area. But this comes back to taste. For us, this is a recommendation.
Then there is an archery skills area, there is a deer breeding area. Can you feed kerleb 5k? There are cassowaries too. At the exit gate there is a tablet for entering impressions and suggestions. Then after leaving the core area there are rows of food and beverage stalls whose menus are similar, right? (See photo). It's a bit of a shame that they are placed outside the core area because we saw that they were empty of visitors. Then, after a row of food and beverage shops, there is an area for souvenirs and souvenirs, as is common in tourist attractions.
Oh yes, in the parking area we can take a tourist jeep that goes around the area around Prambanan with the most expensive package around 500k/jeep.
Anyway, this place is very good. The temples wow and wow even more when seen up close. The area is very well maintained. No wonder lots of foreign tourists come here.
Hopefully the info can help a little.
title: Prambanan Temple

Good place!!!

Entrance ticket only 50,000

name: Wilda Febiani
text:
Salah satu destinasi tempat wisata yg bisa di kunjungi kalau ke Jogja. Bisa di akses naik trans Jogja tapi hanya sampai terminal dekat Prambanan. Bisa lanjut jalan kaki atau naik becak (kemaren di kasih harga 25.000 ada sekali jalan / becak) pulang nya inisiatif naik mobil online, ternyata harus bayar parkir 15.000 (woowww) tips yg mau naik mobil online, titik jemput nya di pintu keluar parkiran aja,biar ngga bayar parkir 😁HTM 50.000/ dewasa 25.000/anak.
Tips lagi, kalau kesana pas hari cerah usahakan bawa payung, topi, kacamata, kipas kecil. Kalau ngga bawa payung bisa sewa 10.000 / payung sampai pintu keluar. Selesai keliling kawasan candi Prambanan, bisa naik buggy car 20.000 / orang bisa melihat candi Bubrah,dll. Sebelum pintu keluar, akan di berhentikan di candi Sewu yg ngga kalah indah dari Prambanan. Arah pintu keluar akan di arahkan ke pasar oleh², kalau ngga ada rencana beli bisa lewat lorong no.5 biar tidak mutar². Jangan lupa mengabaikan moment,ada tukang foto keliling juga.
textTranslated:
One of the tourist destinations that you can visit if you go to Jogja. It can be accessed by Trans Jogja but only to the terminal near Prambanan. You can continue walking or take a pedicab (yesterday they were given a price of 25,000 for one way / pedicab). When you go home, take the initiative to take an online car, it turns out you have to pay 15,000 for parking (woowww). Tips for those who want to take an online car, the pick-up point is at the parking lot exit, so you don't have to pay for parking 😁HTM 50,000/adult 25,000/child.
Another tip, if you go there on a sunny day, try to bring an umbrella, hat, glasses, small fan. If you don't bring an umbrella, you can rent 10,000/umbrella until the exit. After touring the Prambanan temple area, you can take a buggy car for 20,000 per person and you can see Bubrah temple, etc. Before the exit, you will stop at the Sewu temple which is no less beautiful than Prambanan. The direction of the exit will be directed towards the souvenir market, if you don't have plans to buy, you can go through aisle no. 5 so you don't get turned around. Don't forget to ignore the moment, there are traveling photographers too.

Wij hebben gelopen, is ongeveer een half uur over het terrein vanaf Prambanan (je blijft op het tempelterrein). Die Tempel sind sehr beeindruckend und teilweise begehbar. Der große Tempel am Ende der Prambanan Tempel ist umgeben von sehr vielen Ruinen. Dazu gehört ein kleiner Zoo. Die Tiere sind dort in extrem kleinen Käfigen gehalten. Für den Preis von 23€ pro Person sollte der Inhaber die Tiere in größere Käfige oder offen rum laufen lassen. Eine Schande an einem Tempel Tiere in so kleine Käfige einzusperren!!! Das hat mir meine Laune genommen.

Wir sind übrigens so gegen 11/12 Uhr hin. Es war noch übersichtlich. Gegen 14 Uhr war es voll mit Touristen.
textTranslated:
The temples are very impressive and some are accessible. The large temple at the end of the Prambanan Temple is surrounded by many ruins. This includes a small zoo. The animals are kept there in extremely small cages. For the price of €23 per person, the owner should let the animals run around in larger cages or openly. It's a shame for a temple to lock animals in such small cages!!! That took my mood away.

By the way, we got there around 11/12 p.m. It was still clear. By 2 p.m. it was full of tourists.

text: 普兰巴南神庙位于日惹市以北18公里，是联合国教科文组织的一处世界文化遗产，也是东南亚最大的印度教庙宇。它的独特之处在于其高耸的尖顶建筑、印度教建筑的典型风格和高达47米的中心建筑。普兰巴南大约建造于公元850年，建成后很快就被遗弃并开始破败。1918年开始重建，1953年前后人们完成了对其主建筑的重建。
textTranslated: Prambanan Temple is located 18 kilometers north of Yogyakarta. It is a UNESCO World Cultural Heritage and the largest Hindu temple in Southeast Asia. Its uniqueness lies in its towering spire, typical of Hindu architecture, and its 47-meter-high central building. Prambanan was built around AD 850. It was abandoned and began to deteriorate soon after its completion. Reconstruction began in 1918, and the reconstruction of the main building was completed around 1953.

text:
Candi Prambanan adalah candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia yang terletak di Sleman, Yogyakarta. Candi ini merupakan salah satu situs warisan dunia UNESCO dan menjadi salah satu destinasi wisata paling populer di Indonesia. Berikut adalah review tentang Candi Prambanan:
Keindahan Arsitektur:
* Candi Prambanan memiliki arsitektur Hindu yang sangat indah dan megah. Candi ini terdiri dari tiga candi utama yang dikelilingi oleh ratusan candi kecil. Relief-relief yang terukir di dinding candi menceritakan kisah Ramayana dan Krishnayana.

* "Candi Prambanan adalah salah satu candi terindah yang pernah saya lihat. Arsitekturnya sangat megah dan detail-detailnya sangat indah. Relief-relief di dinding candi juga sangat menarik untuk dilihat." - Wisatawan dari Semarang
Pemandangan Alam:
* Candi Prambanan terletak di dataran tinggi dengan pemandangan alam yang indah. Dari pelataran candi, pengunjung dapat melihat Gunung Merapi dan Gunung Merbabu.

* "Pemandangan dari Candi Prambanan sangat menakjubkan. Kita bisa melihat gunung-gunung dan persawahan hijau yang luas. Udara di sana juga sangat sejuk dan segar." - Wisatawan dari Surabaya
Suasana Spiritual:
* Candi Prambanan merupakan tempat suci bagi umat Hindu. Banyak pengunjung yang datang ke candi ini untuk berdoa dan bermeditasi. Suasana di candi terasa tenang dan damai.

Tips:
* Waktu terbaik untuk mengunjungi Candi Prambanan adalah pada pagi hari atau sore hari. Udara pada saat itu tidak terlalu panas dan pengunjung dapat menikmati suasana yang lebih tenang.
* Gunakan pakaian yang sopan saat mengunjungi Candi Prambanan. Pengunjung tidak diperbolehkan memakai pakaian yang terbuka atau minim.
* Sewa guide untuk membantu Anda memahami sejarah dan budaya Candi Prambanan. Guide-guide di Candi Prambanan sangat ramah dan informatif.
* Jangan lupa untuk mencoba kuliner khas Yogyakarta saat mengunjungi Candi Prambanan. Ada banyak kuliner lezat yang dapat Anda coba di sekitar candi.
textTranslated:
Prambanan Temple is the largest Hindu temple in Indonesia, located in Sleman, Yogyakarta. This temple is a UNESCO world heritage site and is one of the most popular tourist destinations in Indonesia. The following is a review of Prambanan Temple:
Architectural Beauty:
* Prambanan Temple has very beautiful and magnificent Hindu architecture. This temple consists of three main temples surrounded by hundreds of small temples. The reliefs carved on the temple walls tell the story of the Ramayana and Krishnayana.

* "Prambanan Temple is one of the most beautiful temples I have ever seen. The architecture is very magnificent and the details are very beautiful. The reliefs on the temple walls are also very interesting to look at." - Tourists from Semarang
Panorama:
* Prambanan Temple is located on a plateau with beautiful natural views. From the temple grounds, visitors can see Mount Merapi and Mount Merbabu.

* "The view from Prambanan Temple is amazing. We can see mountains and vast green rice fields. The air there is also very cool and fresh." - Tourists from Surabaya
Spiritual Atmosphere:
* Prambanan Temple is a holy place for Hindus. Many visitors come to this temple to pray and meditate. The atmosphere in the temple feels calm and peaceful.

Tips:
* The best time to visit Prambanan Temple is in the morning or afternoon. The air at that time is not too hot and visitors can enjoy a calmer atmosphere.
* Wear polite clothing when visiting Prambanan Temple. Visitors are not allowed to wear revealing or skimpy clothing.
* Hire a guide to help you understand the history and culture of Prambanan Temple. The guides at Prambanan Temple are very friendly and informative.
* Don't forget to try typical Yogyakarta culinary delights when visiting Prambanan Temple. There are many delicious culinary delights that you can try around the temple.

name: Elyoga Andri S
text:
Situs candi yang wajib untuk dikunjungi, wisata sejarah & budaya yang sangat menarik.
Lokasi & aksesnya mudah dijangkau, panduan arah dari google maps juga presisi.
Tersedia area parkir yang sangat luas dan terdiri dari beberapa sektor, fasilitas2 pendukung seperti mushola & kamar kecil tersedia cukup banyak, bagus dan bersih.
Tepat berdampingan dengan tempat2 parkir terdapat pasar cindera mata & food court yang terdiri dari beberapa blok yang secara otomatis akan dilalui pengunjung saat menuju loket tiket.
Sayangnya penunjuk arah menuju sepertinya memang dirancang agar pengunjung menjelajahi pasar2, sehingga terkesan berputar putar dan untuk sebagian orang mungkin akan terasa cukup melelahkan.
Sampai di loket ada 2 jenis tiket yang ditawarkan, tiket untuk masuk ke area pelataran candi dan tiket untuk masuk ke dalam candi. Sangat disarankan untuk memesan tiket di hari sebelumnya jika ingin masuk ke dalam candi supaya tidak kehabisan karena kuotanya terbatas, sedangkan untuk tiket ke pelataran candi bisa dibeli di loket.
Selepas beli tiket, pengunjung kemudian menunggu di halte untuk kemudian dijemput oleh armada khusus yang akan mengantar kita ke area pintu masuk candi.
Secara keseluruhan berwisata di borobudur cukup menyenangkan, karena selain candinya sendiri yang megah lingkungan sekitar candi yang asri juga menawarkan wisata alam yang menyegarkan.
textTranslated:
A must-visit temple site, very interesting historical & cultural tourism.
The location & access is easy to reach, the directions from Google Maps are also precise.
There is a very large parking area available and consists of several sectors, there are quite a lot of supporting facilities such as prayer rooms & toilets, nice and clean.
Right next to the parking lots there is a souvenir market & food court which consists of several blocks which visitors will automatically pass through on their way to the ticket counter.
Unfortunately, the directions seem to be designed for visitors to explore the markets, so it seems like they are going in circles and for some people it might feel quite tiring.
Arriving at the counter there are 2 types of tickets offered, tickets to enter the temple grounds and tickets to enter the temple. It is highly recommended to order tickets the day before if you want to enter the temple so you don't run out because the quota is limited, while tickets to the temple grounds can be purchased at the counter.
After purchasing tickets, visitors then wait at the bus stop to be picked up by a special fleet who will take us to the temple entrance area.
Overall, traveling to Borobudur is quite enjoyable, because apart from the magnificent temple itself, the beautiful environment around the temple also offers refreshing natural tourism.
