address: Jl. Badrawati, Kw. Candi Borobudur, Borobudur, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Tyas Kurniawan
text:
Salah satu candi Budha terbesar di dunia. Terletak di Magelang, Jawa Tengah. Jadi bukan di Jogja. Akssenya dapat dijangkau dari beberpa kota, tinggal ikutin google map.
1. Parkiran sangat luas, bisa menampung ratusan kendaraan, baik roda dua maupun roda empat. Untuk tarif parkir mobil, di weekend Rp. 15.000. Hari biasa Rp. 10.000
2. Tiket masuknya terbagi menjadi dua jenis, tiket yang hanya sampai ke pelataran candi, Rp. 50.000 per orang. Dan satu lagi tiket yang naik ke puncak candi, Rp. 120.000 per orang. Kedua nya bisa dibeli secara online, maupun dibeli langsung di tempat.
3. Untuk tiket yang naik ke puncak candi, kuota nya dibatasi hanya 1200 orang per hari. Jadi sangat disarankan untuk membeli secara online, agar tidak kehabisan kuota.
4. Untuk tiket yang naik ke puncak candi, sudaj termasuk tas, sandal khusus yang harus dipakai untuk naik ke puncak candi, dan tur guide yang akan menjelaskan tentang candi Borobudur. Kita bisa bertanya tanya seputar candi, dan sejarah maupun kisah yang terpahat di relief candi.
5. Pastikan membawa minuman, payung atau topi, karena di pelataran candi cukup panas dan tidak ada penjual yang dibolehkan masuk.
Untuk di pelataran, ada jasa sewa payung dengan tarif Rp.10.000
textTranslated:
One of the largest Buddhist temples in the world. Located in Magelang, Central Java. So not in Jogja. Access can be reached from several cities, just follow Google Map.
1. The parking lot is very large, can accommodate hundreds of vehicles, both two-wheeled and four-wheeled. For car parking rates, on weekends Rp. 15,000. Normal day Rp. 10,000
2. Entrance tickets are divided into two types, tickets that only reach the temple grounds, Rp. 50,000 per person. And another ticket that goes up to the top of the temple, Rp. 120,000 per person. Both can be purchased online, or purchased directly on the spot.
3. For tickets to climb to the top of the temple, the quota is limited to only 1200 people per day. So it is highly recommended to buy online, so as not to run out of quota.
4. For tickets to climb to the top of the temple, it includes a bag, special sandals that must be worn to climb to the top of the temple, and a tour guide who will explain about Borobudur temple. We can ask questions about the temple, and the history and stories carved on the temple reliefs.
5. Make sure to bring a drink, umbrella or hat, because it is quite hot in the temple grounds and no sellers are allowed to enter.
For the courtyard, there is an umbrella rental service at a rate of IDR 10,000
title: Borobudur Temple

text: 1998年の研究論文にも書いた事がその建築には初めて現物を参観しました。二日間三度現地入りし、二度の登頂をさせていただきました。やっぱり人類が残せた貴重な構造物の奇跡でした。この立体曼荼羅を美しく眺めるのがやっぱり空中からしかありません。少し残念でしたが、今度機会が有ればヘリを使って、撮影してみたいと思います。
textTranslated: It was my first time to see the actual building, which I wrote about in my 1998 research paper. I visited the site three times in two days and climbed the summit twice. After all, it was a miracle of a valuable structure that humanity was able to leave behind. The only way to view this three-dimensional mandala beautifully is from the air. I was a little disappointed, but if I have a chance next time, I would like to take pictures using a helicopter.

text:
Assalamualaikum Wa Rahmatullahi Wa Barakatuh, ijin review jujur..
1. Masuknya parkir mahal 15.000 1 mobil padahal cuma sebentar.
2. Masuknya harga dewasa 50.000 anak 25.000
3. Pakai shutel naik setelah loket dan diturunin sebelah utara candi, harus jalan lagi...tapi disediakan delman dgn harga 100.000, turun depan candi, harus jalan lagi mendekati candi. Naik tanggal yg tinggi...
4. Jasa foto 35.000 rb, kirim file foto 15 per foto...itu mahal menurut sy...
5. Trus turun keluar candi turun tangga, ada 2 pilihan pakai shutel yg harus bayar 20.000 perorang atau pakai delman yg bayar 100.000 lagi...

Menurut sy itu termasuk mahal untuk melihat sejarah Candi...

Pertanyaaan sy:
Kenapa harus naik shutel dari parkiran dan diturunkan yg jaraknya lumayan  dr candi untuk jalan kaki...sehingga mengaharuskan jalan kaki atau pakai delman yg harus bayar lagi....kasian yg bawa anak2...
Kenapa harga delmannya harus 100.000, knp tdk 50.000 saja untuk harga bersahabat...

Intinya, yah klo mau liburan dicandi borobudur siapkan uang yg lumayan hanya untuk melihat candi dan berfoto foto...
Just it.
TERIMAKASIH
textTranslated:
Assalamualaikum Wa Rahmatullahi Wa Barakatuh, permission for an honest review..
1. Entrance to parking is expensive at 15,000 per car even though it's only for a short time.
2. Entry price for adults 50,000 children 25,000
3. Use a shuttle, go up after the counter and get off to the north of the temple, you have to walk again... but a carriage is provided at a price of 100,000, get off in front of the temple, you have to walk again to get closer to the temple. Up to a high date...
4. Photo services 35,000 thousand, send photo files 15 per photo... that's expensive in my opinion...
5. Then go out of the temple down the stairs, there are 2 options: use a shuttle which you have to pay 20,000 per person or use a carriage which pays another 100,000...

In my opinion, it is quite expensive to see the history of the temple...

My question:
Why do you have to take a shuttle from the parking lot and get dropped off at a distance from the temple to walk... so you have to walk or use a carriage which you have to pay for again... poor people who bring children...
Why does the carriage have to cost 100,000, why not just 50,000 for a friendly price...

The point is, if you want to vacation at Borobudur Temple, prepare enough money just to see the temple and take photos...
Just that.
THANK YOU
title: Borobudur Temple

Mixue which is near Prambanan is really good, you can charge PB at the shop..
Jogja's people are that good

Ahh, but I was unlucky, I was cheated out of more than 700 out of money, ahh, it's sad, but never mind, maybe it's not my luck and I hope the person who cheated me can eat for the next few days...
And thank God I was able to go home safely, I wasn't killed or harassed, thank God I was still protected...

Message: don't believe too much in the stories of people who have just met themselves, they often lie to themselves, especially to other people, and when traveling solo, it's okay to be selfish, but it turns out it's okay to not care about people...

And I love myself from that day on, I care more about myself..

Yep, what a lesson and maybe Jogja I need someone so I don't get fooled again...hehee

I'm still a little traumatized until the day that at first I always took something good, now I've completely changed my perception...
But its okay

So for those of you who may be traveling solo, don't get too close to people to make friends, be more careful...

name: P. S.
text:
English:
Title: A Mix of Beauty and Crowds - A Review of Prambanan Temple in Java, Indonesia

Rating: 3/5 stars

Prambanan Temple in Java, Indonesia, is undoubtedly a sight to behold. As one of the most magnificent Hindu temples in Southeast Asia, its intricate architecture and historical significance attract tourists from around the world. However, one aspect that left me with mixed feelings was the expensive entry fee, which might be a deterrent for budget-conscious travelers.

Upon arriving at the temple complex, I was awe-struck by the sheer beauty and grandeur of the structures. The detailed carvings and towering spires are a testament to the architectural brilliance of the past. Exploring the temple grounds and learning about its rich history was a fascinating experience.

Yet, the beauty of Prambanan comes with a drawback - it's a popular destination, and the crowds can be overwhelming. Navigating through the sea of tourists can be challenging, and finding moments of tranquility to truly appreciate the temple's majesty can be difficult.

One of the highlights of my visit was witnessing the sunset at Prambanan. The way the golden hues adorned the ancient stone structures created a surreal and captivating ambiance. It was undoubtedly a magical moment and one that I'll cherish.

In conclusion, Prambanan Temple is undeniably a captivating destination with its rich history and stunning architecture. However, the high entry fee and the overwhelming crowds somewhat detract from the overall experience. If you can overlook these aspects, witnessing the beauty of Prambanan and the mesmerizing sunset is well worth the visit.

--------------------

Indonesian (Bahasa Indonesia):
Judul: Campuran Keindahan dan Keramaian - Sebuah Ulasan tentang Candi Prambanan di Pulau Jawa, Indonesia

Penilaian: 3/5 bintang

Candi Prambanan di Pulau Jawa, Indonesia, merupakan pemandangan yang memukau. Sebagai salah satu candi Hindu paling megah di Asia Tenggara, arsitektur yang rumit dan signifikansi sejarahnya menarik para wisatawan dari seluruh dunia. Namun, ada satu aspek yang membuat saya bingung, yaitu harga tiket masuk yang mahal, yang mungkin menjadi halangan bagi para pelancong dengan anggaran terbatas.

Ketika tiba di kompleks candi, saya terkesima oleh keindahan dan kemegahan struktur bangunannya. Ukiran detail dan menara tinggi menjadi bukti kecerdasan arsitektur masa lalu. Menjelajahi halaman candi dan mempelajari sejarahnya yang kaya merupakan pengalaman yang menarik.

Namun, keindahan Candi Prambanan datang dengan hambatan - ini adalah tujuan populer, dan kerumunan orang bisa sangat mengganggu. Menavigasi kerumunan wisatawan bisa menjadi tantangan, dan menemukan momen ketenangan untuk benar-benar menghargai keagungan candi bisa sulit.

Salah satu momen puncak kunjungan saya adalah menyaksikan matahari terbenam di Prambanan. Cara cahaya emas mempercantik struktur batu kuno menciptakan suasana yang magis dan memukau. Tanpa ragu, momen itu sangat indah dan akan saya kenang.

Kesimpulannya, Candi Prambanan adalah tujuan yang menarik dengan sejarah yang kaya dan arsitektur yang memukau. Namun, harga tiket masuk yang tinggi dan keramaian yang mengganggu agak mengurangi pengalaman secara keseluruhan. Jika Anda dapat mengabaikan aspek ini, menyaksikan keindahan Prambanan dan matahari terbenam yang mempesona sangat layak untuk dikunjungi.
